BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:2026 Spring Baby Show
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T170000
UID:blogto-233030@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/02/original_image35714d68-9df4-4c66-9852-91f924b4b4
 39.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The Spring Baby Show\, presented by The Canadian Scholarship T
 rust Foundation (CST)\, returns to the Enercare Centre\, Exhibition Place 
 from Saturday April 11 to Sunday April 12. The two-day event brings togeth
 er over 200 local and national brands\, making it a one-stop shop for ever
 ything from strollers and car seats to the latest in nursery decor and clo
 thing. Visitors will have the opportunity to preview the latest trends\, w
 atch live demonstrations and prioritize health and wellness\, with complim
 entary sleep consultations and massages.\nThe CST Seminar Stage serves as 
 a vital resource for navigating the complexities of a baby’s first year 
 with confidence and compassion. From managing the realities of sleep depri
 vation and reflux to prioritizing postpartum recovery\, industry experts w
 ill provide a practical roadmap for balancing a structured routine with th
 e necessary flexibility of early parenthood. At the CST Savings Booth\, pa
 rents can gain life-saving skills through daily\, hands-on CPR demonstrati
 ons led by Ryan Wilbee\, National Construction Safety Officer (IHSA)\, Cer
 tified Standard First Aid & CPR Instructor. With recent changes to Ontario
 ’s OSAP and provincial funding\, planning and starting to save early for
  postsecondary education is more important than ever. CST representatives 
 will be on site to help parents get started and learn more about Registere
 d Education Savings Plans (RESPs).\nThe Volvo Safety Stage features essent
 ial demonstrations and car seat safety workshops. On the Health & Wellness
  Mat\, guests can join interactive pre and post-natal fitness sessions des
 igned for every stage of motherhood. For those seeking specialized support
 \, the Sleep of Mind Sleep Clinic offers free one-on-one consultations wit
 h certified sleep consultants to help you prepare a sleep strategy\, while
  Protege School provides complimentary prenatal and postnatal massages on-
 site.\nUnique to the show\, pregnant attendees can stop by the Tiny Hearts
  3D Ultrasound Studio and get their very own 3D Ultrasound performed onsit
 e and leave with a precious photo keepsake. For those attending with young
  children\, the show offers meet & greets with Bluey and Bingo\, Peppa and
  Mummy Pig!
LOCATION:Enercare Centre
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/2026-spring-baby-show-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:2 - Day Songkran Event @ PAI Uptown and Thai Tavern
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T163000
UID:blogto-232854@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/30/original_image9ef296e8-446f-430b-8c4d-f71e333d5e
 ec.jpg
DESCRIPTION:💦 HAPPY THAI NEW YEAR! 🇹🇭 This year\, we are going 
 BIG for Songkran!\nWhether you are celebrating a piece of home\, reminisci
 ng about your favourite memories from a past trip to Thailand\, or wanting
  to experience our vibrant culture for the very first time\, absolutely ev
 eryone is welcome! ✨\nWe’ve curated a 2-DAY event to show you every si
 de of the holiday—from a vibrant artisan market to a festive beer garden
 . It’s all about connecting people through food\, play\, and fun while 
 sharing the beauty of Thai culture.\nHere is what we have planned:\n🛍
 ️ DAY 1: PAI UPTOWN — Market & Vendors 🗓️ Saturday\, April 11 
 | 12:00 PM - 4:30 PM Start the holiday with a fun-filled daytime pop-up f
 eaturing street food specials\, games\, and a market full of unique local 
 vendors! Shop for vintage clothing\, ceramics\, jewelry\, and crafts. Trea
 t yourself to a Thai massage\, participate in the traditional pouring of B
 uddha water\, and taste Chef Nuit’s exclusive Songkran dishes—includin
 g the beautifully colourful Kanom Jeen Se Pak(4-region noodles)\, Grille
 d Pork Jowl\, and crispy Thai Fried Banana.\n🍻 DAY 2: THAI TAVERN —
  Food Market & Beer Garden 🗓️ Sunday\, April 12 | 1:00 PM - 9 PM T
 he celebration continues with a full-day beer garden experience! We’re b
 ringing the street food vibes to Thai Tavern with brewery booths\, a speci
 al Singha promo\, games\, and karaoke. Feast on iconic street food favour
 ites like our Crispy Wrapped Wontons\, Esan Sausage\, and Chicken Pop w
 ith Tom Yum seasoning while you toast to the New Year!\n✨ FESTIVAL HIG
 HLIGHTS: ✨\n🛂 The Songkran Passport: Pick up a passport and collec
 t special stickers at our participating locations for a chance to win exci
 ting prizes!\n📸 Thai Costume Photo Booth: Try on stunning traditional
  Thai outfits for FREE\, snap a pic with our festive props\, and enter our
  photo competition for a chance to win a prize! (Dressing up is optional\,
  but highly encouraged!)\n🐘 Match the Spirit: We invite you to wear y
 our favourite Thai elephant pants or colourful Thai shirts to help us shar
 e the holiday spirit!\nWe can’t wait to bring a piece of Thailand to you
 ! 🇹🇭❤️
LOCATION:Multiple Venues
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/2-day-songkran-event-pai-uptown-and-thai
 -tavern-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
