BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:A Lebanese Table by The Singing Mama
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T210000
UID:blogto-231565@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/02/original_image69e636c0-7be5-4e07-921a-625482e202
 d5.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a night of delicious food\, lovingly prepared and 
 shared\, accompanied by a selection of contemporary international pop\, ja
 zz\, soul and blues vocals performed by The Singing Mama herself.\nIn Nayl
 a's words: "This menu is built around the dishes that raised us. The ones 
 that simmer slowly while stories are told\, the ones that taste like Sunda
 y at home. These are not restaurant dishes\; they are gathering dishes\, 
 “please have seconds” dishes.\nEvery plate comes from memory — from 
 women in aprons\, from lemon squeezed by hand\, from yogurt whisked gently
  over low heat\, from heart to table. This is comfort food from the Levant
 : generous\, soulful\, and meant to be shared."\n-----\nTabouleh\nA bright
 \, herb-forward salad of finely chopped parsley\, tomatoes\, bulgur\, mint
 \, and plenty of fresh lemon. Served with romaine lettuce for scooping\nHa
 rak Osbao\nA beloved Syrian dish — so close to Lebanese kitchens that it
  feels like family — this hearty\, plant-based classic layers lentils\, 
 dough bites\, caramelized onions\, crispy pita chips\, herbs and pomegrana
 te seeds\, and both tamarind and pomegranate molasses for a tangy depth. I
 t’s rustic\, bold\, and full of textures — sweet\, sour\, and savoury 
 all at once.\nDjej w Batata (Lebanese Lemony Baked Chicken & Potato)\nTend
 er chicken baked with golden potatoes\, fresh garlic\, and bright lemon ju
 ice. As it roasts\, the pan fills with rich citrusy drippings that Lebanes
 e families fight over with pieces of bread.Vegetarian option available\nCo
 ussa Ablama bil Laban\nDelicately hollowed zucchinis filled purely with se
 asoned minced beef. They are gently simmered and finished in a warm garlic
 -coriander yogurt sauce topped with fried nuts. This version is deeply sav
 oury and luxurious\, with the yogurt bringing balance and softness. A dish
  of care\, patience\, and quiet elegance — the kind served when you want
  to nourish someone properly. Vegetarian option available\nMhallabiyeh\nA 
 delicate Arabic milk pudding\, scented with orange blossom water\, silky a
 nd nostalgic\, with a subtle Canadian twist — a maple syrup glaze\, a sm
 all reflection of my journey and the blending of two homes. Served with se
 lection of halaweh\, dates and cookies for nibbling & sharing.\n------\nNa
 yla Ghandour’s love of food and song began as a heartfelt lockdown proje
 ct in Dubai\, where she shared videos of herself cooking and singing to sp
 read joy during Covid. While preparing to emigrate to Canada\, a temporary
  return to Beirut led to an unexpected leap into the restaurant world with
  The Singing Mama\, a warm\, vibrant space built around the dishes she lov
 ed to cook for her family. As conditions in Lebanon worsened\, Nayla and h
 er family made the difficult decision to close the restaurant after receiv
 ing their Express Entry visas\, determined to give their children a safer 
 future. Now in Canada\, she hopes her cooking and singing will continue to
  create community\, friendship\, and a bridge to cherished traditions.\nth
 esingingmama.com | @the.singing.mama
LOCATION:The Depanneur
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/a-lebanese-table-by-the-singing-mama-tor
 onto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
