 gto.com/events/2026/04/05/original_image2ce37d2b-56e1-430b-b1ca-4f67ba389a
 86.jpg
DESCRIPTION:April 11th – Double Contra Dance on the Danforth!\nWondering
  whether you should join us for the advanced dance? At this dance\, it is 
 assumed that you are comfortable with all the common moves and can dance t
 hem on the fly (even if called without the caller walking the dance throug
 h beforehand). A hey should feel fun (not scary or disorienting) and it sh
 ould be rare that anyone would need to help you get reoriented during a da
 nce. If that sounds like you\, please come!\nIf you're thinking of bringin
 g a beginner that day\, we'd love to see them at the evening dance. Make s
 ure they attend the intro to contra lesson at 7pm so that they have the mo
 st fun possible during the dance (and get free entry to the next regular e
 vening dance).\n✨ On stage:\nCaller Bev Bernbaum guiding the dances\, wi
 th Elise Boeur + Adam Iredale-Gray - setting the groove and keeping the fl
 oor in motion all day long.\n🕖 Evening timeline:\nAfternoon - Advanced 
 dance (2pm to 5pm)\nEvening - Regular dance (Intro lesson 7pm\, dance 7:30
  to 10:30pm)\n😷 Mask-Optional\n💧 Bring a refillable water bottle\n
 🥟 Samosas will be ready (arrive early if you want one!)\nAfternoon & Ev
 ening dances are priced separately.\nSliding scale: $7–$35 (kids 16 & un
 der free)\nIt costs about $22 per dancer to make these nights happen—you
 r support\, generosity\, and word-of-mouth keep the community strong.\n
 📍 St. Barnabas Church Hall\n175 Hampton Ave (near Chester Station)\n
 🌐 www.tcdance.org\nWhether it’s your first dance or your fiftieth\, w
 e’d love to see you there.
LOCATION:St. Barnabas Church Hall
