BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mangue Circle: Body & Water Workshop at Underscore Projects
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T173000
UID:blogto-233035@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/02/original_image211a29f2-9dd4-492e-9311-fc706e6d42
 86.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a creative workshop by Studio Mangue exploring our
  affective relationship with bodies of water through conversation\, moveme
 nt\, and collective artistic expression.\nWe live in a city whose name car
 ries a deep connection to water. Yet\, through its planning and urban desi
 gn\, it has created a rupture in our embodied relationship with water. Acc
 ess is limited\, swimming is restricted\, and many of us experience water 
 as something scenic rather than fully connected to our everyday lives.\nTh
 is workshop invites us to reflect on our bodies as water and on our relati
 onship with it. It also prompts us to imagine our city’s bodies of water
  as living spaces where we can play\, swim\, gather\, and reconnect with o
 urselves and each other.\nThis gathering will take place in a circle forma
 t\, creating space for reflection\, shared dialogue\, and creative explora
 tion. The session will include moments of movement\, paired and group conv
 ersations\, and a guided artistic activity in collaboration with DrawingTO
 .\nWhen: Saturday - April 11th\, 2026 from 2pm to 5:30pm\nWhere: Underscor
 e Projects - 1468 Dundas St W - 2nd floor - Toronto\, ON M6J 1Y6 (Dundas/D
 ufferin)\;\nTickets: $10 (if cost is a barrier\, please reach out - we wan
 t this to be accessible!)\nParticipants will be invited to sit primarily o
 n the floor\, fostering a more grounded and intimate environment. Chairs w
 ill be available upon request\, and we are happy to accommodate different 
 needs to ensure everyone feels comfortable.\nIf you have any questions or 
 accessibility needs\, please reach out:\nvivian@studiomangue.com\nThis wor
 kshop is part of Mangue Circle\, a series of gatherings exploring our embo
 died relationship with the city. Studio Mangue is a creative platform expl
 oring the relationship between people\, land\, memory\, and cultural space
 s. Through art\, storytelling\, and collaborative workshops\, Studio Mangu
 e invites communities to imagine shared spaces as places of care\, encount
 er\, and belonging.\nAbout Us\nUnderscore Projects is a cultural platform 
 rooted in a physical\, community-oriented space that includes multi-functi
 onal studios\, an artist residency\, and a gallery.\nOur mission is to sup
 port underrepresented artists\, particularly those from the Brazilian and 
 Latin American diaspora\, by providing opportunities for collaborative art
 istic creation\, mentorship\, and public presentation. We also engage chil
 dren and the wider community through inclusive art education and dialogue.
 \nUnderscore Projects strives to connect artists to resources\, profession
 al support\, and audiences\, offering a more supportive approach compared 
 to traditional art spaces.\nLocated in the heart of Little Portugal\, Toro
 nto\, we serve as a hub for public exchange - encouraging open conversatio
 ns\, cultural connection\, and creative learning that reflect the diverse 
 communities we work with.
LOCATION:Underscore Projects
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/mangue-circle-body-water-workshop-at-und
 erscore-projects-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mindful Spaces: A Creative Journey through ROM Architecture
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T170000
UID:blogto-232003@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/10/original_image82a65568-149a-4acb-85f9-1ea41788a6
 34.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Mindful Spaces: A Creative Journey through ROM Architecture of
 fers a different entry point into mindfulness by focusing on how architect
 ural environments shape our inner experience.\nThe architecture of the Mus
 eum is exquisite. It spans Neo-Romanesque\, Neo- Byzantine\, Art Deco\, Mo
 dernist and Deconstructivist styles\, with some spaces combining multiple 
 designs.\nOn this mindfulness journey\, participants will be led through f
 our unique architectural locations in the Museum that spark a sense of awe
 \, curiosity\, and beauty. Participants will be creatively guided on how t
 o connect to their senses in each location\, and then to their own persona
 l inner world. Leaning into carefully selected themes\, and allowing perso
 nal associations and meaningful memories to emerge\, participants will exp
 lore how architecture\, their senses\, and their own creativity can nouris
 h a mindfulness awareness\, allow for grounding\, and inspire self-discove
 ry.\nThe program will culminate with participants being led through a crea
 tive visualization to find their own inner sanctuary\, and time to share t
 heir reflections or create an art piece to take home and remember the expe
 rience.\nThis program will be offered three times in April.
LOCATION:Royal Ontario Museum
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/mindful-spaces-a-creative-journey-throug
 h-rom-architecture-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
