 ON — From the producers of The Bowie Lives\,\nOutShout Entertainment pre
 sents\n"A show in the spirit of CBGB"\nStop Making Sense & Nothing but Blo
 ndie.\nThe double bill returns to Toronto for a high-energy night\nof new 
 wave perfection at The Duke Live.\nStop Making Sense delivers the songs yo
 u know by heart—performed loud\, crisp\, and unapologetically fun. Front
 ed by singing sensation Michael Bell (star of The Bowie Lives)\, the band 
 brings the kind of live show that turns a venue into a party: tight musici
 anship\, big choruses\, and a dance-forward set that never lets up.\nClosi
 ng the night is\nNothing But Blondie which features Toronto's Jaclyn Serre
  as Blondie\, bringing the iconic Blondie catalogue to life—packed with 
 attitude\, style\, and hit-after-hit singalongs.\nTogether\, it’s a full
 -throttle tribute night built for fans of classic new wave\, punk-pop\, an
 d the downtown cool that never really went away.\nEVENT DETAILS\nStop Maki
 ng Sense Talking Heads Tribute (opening)\n+ Nothing But Blondie\nSaturday\
 , April 11\nThe Duke Live at 1225 Queen St East TORONTO\nTickets: https://
 www.eventbrite.ca/e/double-bill-nothing-but-blondie-stop-making-sense-tick
 ets-1984330260225\nDoors: [7pm | Show: [8:30]\nAges: [19+]
LOCATION:The Duke
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/stop-making-sense-and-nothing-but-blondi
 e-double-bill-tributes-ap-11th-the-duke-live-to-toronto/
