BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:U.S. College Expo Returns to T.O. April 11
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T140000
UID:blogto-232962@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/31/original_imagefd70eb0e-991f-4631-8c54-408c2c318a
 73.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The U.S. College Expo returns to Toronto on Saturday\, April 1
 1\, 2026\, bringing together thousands of students and families with repre
 sentatives from leading American colleges\, universities\, and preparatory
  schools.\nAs Canada’s only event dedicated exclusively to U.S. college 
 access\, the free one-day Expo provides direct access to admissions guidan
 ce\, scholarship opportunities\, and student-athlete pathways all under on
 e roof. Many leave feeling inspired after discovering the possibilities fo
 r financial aid and other funding opportunities.\nCanadian Demand for U.S.
  Education Continues to Rise\nFounded in 2012 by Severino\, the Expo conti
 nues to grow alongside increasing interest in U.S. education\, driven by e
 xpanded program availability\, scholarship opportunities\, and competitive
  academic and athletic pathways.\nAccording to the latest data from the In
 stitute of International Education\, Canadian enrollment at U.S. post-seco
 ndary institutions rose 3.1 per cent in 2024–2025. Data from Statistics 
 Canada further confirms the United States remains the top destination for 
 Canadians studying abroad.\n“The U.S. College Expo debunks the myth that
  a U.S. Ivy League school is out of reach\, or that a sports scholarship i
 s out of reach\,” added Severino\, who also runs PREPSKILLS®\, Canada
 ’s premier Education Admissions Consultants focusing on holistic admissi
 ons\, test preparation (SSAT\, SAT)\,  applications\, networking connectio
 ns\, and finding the right school fit.\nGuest Speakers: Student-Athlete\, 
 Admissions and Financial Aid Experts\nFeatured guests include Becky Kellar
 \, a Brown University graduate and 4x Olympic medalist\; Mathew V\, a Vanc
 ouver-born singer and performer\; Dr. Benjamin Grant of D’Youville Unive
 rsity\, a higher education leader focused on student engagement and cultur
 e change\; and Henry Wong\, CPA\, CA\, author\, educator and wealth struct
 urist\, who will share insights on education financing and cross-border pl
 anning for Canadian families.\nWhy Attend the U.S. College Expo\nMeet U.S.
  College Representatives – Speak directly with admissions teams about pr
 ograms and campus life.\nScholarships & Financial Aid – Learn how to acc
 ess merit-based and athletic funding.\nStudent-Athlete Pathways – Unders
 tand NCAA recruitment and eligibility requirements.\nAdmissions Guidance 
 – Navigate applications\, timelines\, and testing requirements.\nAll in 
 One Place – Connect with experts across academics\, athletics\, and fina
 ncing.\nEvent Details\nToronto | Saturday\, April 11\, 2026\nLocation: Roy
  Thomson Hall\nTime: 10:00 AM – 2:00 PM\nLocation: Roy Thomson Hall\nAdm
 ission: Free\nRegister: www.uscollegeexpo.com
LOCATION:Roy Thomson Hall
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/us-college-expo-returns-to-to-april-11-t
 oronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
