BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:A Married Couple - with Chandler Levack
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260412T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260412T205500
UID:blogto-232084@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/12/original_image72b7f790-15a1-44be-ac04-39aa98fbf7
 39.jpg
DESCRIPTION:One of the most celebrated works from one of Canada's most bel
 oved directors\, 1969's A Married Couple from filmmaker Allan King reveals
  a romantic relationship on the verge of unraveling. Set in Toronto and fi
 lmed in an intimate\, observational manner\, the documentary is more akin 
 to a fiction film with its larger-than-life performances and volatile repr
 esentation of marriage. By embedding his crew in the Edwards household for
  seven weeks\, King was able to capture intermarital dramas as they unfold
 ed\, raw and unfiltered. Uncomfortable moments linger\, revealing how mism
 atched expectations and power shaped the dynamic between Billy and his wif
 e Antoinette. Uniquely capturing Canadian life in the late 60s\, A Married
  Couple is a fascinating look at a once-bohemian couple straining under th
 e weight of their now middle-class existence with its financial stresses a
 nd inflexible gender roles. Following on the heels of King’s breakout hi
 t\, Warrendale\, A Married Couple cemented the director as a lead figure i
 n North America’s direct cinema movement.\nFeaturing a pre-recorded intr
 o by Canadian writer/director Chandler Levack.\nPresented as part of Natio
 nal Canadian Film Day.\nPresented in partnership with Reel Canada.
LOCATION:Hot Docs Ted Rogers Cinema
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/a-married-couple-with-chandler-levack-to
 ronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
