 f9.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Pruning Seminar for Spring : What\, When & How to Prune\nJoin 
 us for an informative and hands-on pruning seminar led by a former Superin
 tendent of the Humber Arboretum with over 40 years of horticulture experie
 nce.\nThis practical workshop will walk you through the why\, when\, and h
 ow of pruning common landscape plants\, from shrubs and trees to evergreen
 s\, perennials\, hedges\, and ornamental grasses. Learn the right tools to
  use\, seasonal pruning strategies\, and tips to keep your plants healthy 
 and beautiful year-round.\nThe presentation includes live demonstrations w
 ith real plant samples\, followed by a Q&A session where you can get exper
 t advice on your own garden questions.\nExamples include pruning hydrangea
 s\, lilacs\, roses\, ornamental trees\, junipers\, rhododendrons\, hedges\
 , ornamental grasses\, fruit trees & more\, plus tool tips and seasonal ti
 ming advice.\nPerfect for gardeners of all levels looking to gain confiden
 ce in pruning their plants.\nFor more details & to sign up\, visit our web
 site! www.angasfarm.ca
LOCATION:Anga's Farm & Nursery
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/angas-farm-pruning-seminar-for-spring-to
 ronto/
