 gto.com/events/2026/04/02/original_imageb37ee890-e6eb-4ebf-a8e6-bf4aa35b25
 aa.jpg
DESCRIPTION:☕️ FREE TO ATTEND! ⚽\nOn Sunday\, April 12\, Toronto26 i
 s bringing Coffee\, Pints & Prem: Man City vs Chelsea to West Cork Irish P
 ub (701 Queen St E) for a proper football morning in Riverside.\nMan City 
 are chasing glory\, Chelsea are looking to spoil it\, and this one has all
  the ingredients for a big-time Premier League clash. 🔵\nBig screens. C
 offee flowing. Pints ready. A pub built for matchday energy. Whether you
 ’re backing City\, rolling with Chelsea\, or just showing up for high-st
 akes footy\, this is where you want to be.\nFirst table through the door g
 ets a round on us\, no matter the size. 🍻\nPlus\, you could win a jerse
 y\, and everyone in attendance gets extra entries toward our 2026 ticket g
 iveaway. 🎟️\nGet there early. Lock in your spot. Let the atmosphere b
 uild.\nSunday mornings are better with proper football and good people.\nW
 ho is Toronto26?\nWe run Toronto’s top soccer watch parties\, building h
 ype for 2026 while helping grow the city’s soccer culture. Through high-
 energy events and community collaborations\, we bring fans\, local busines
 ses\, and neighbourhoods together around the game.\nToronto26 is also part
  of the Matchday Social network\, a growing movement that connects support
 ers beyond the stadium by turning local pubs and community spaces into mat
 chday hubs where football culture can thrive.\nBecause the game isn’t on
 ly played on the pitch. It lives wherever fans gather.\nToronto is a socce
 r city.\nwww.toronto26.com | info@toronto26.com | info@matchdaysocial.com 
 | #TorontoIsASoccerCity
LOCATION:The West Cork
