BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Greek Easter at estiatorio Milos
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260412T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260412T223000
UID:blogto-233329@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/08/original_imagebc5983ac-6260-4edd-b255-4c3ee053a4
 a0.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Greek Easter is the most sacred celebration in Greece\, a time
  of renewal and gratitude\, cherished with family. estiatorio Milos is hon
 ouring this tradition with a festive Greek Easter feast on Sunday\, April 
 12th for $125/pp.\nThe restaurant will be serving timeless dishes like Mag
 iritsa and red-dyed eggs\, prepared with the same reverence found in Greek
  homes. It’s not just a meal\; it’s a ritual passed down through gener
 ations. From Tzatziki and artisanal Greek cheeses to hand-selected olives\
 , every element of Milos' Easter table reflects its unwavering commitment 
 to authenticity. Greek Easter is about gathering around honest\, pure ingr
 edients — a philosophy that defines Milos year-round. The lamb on the sp
 it is the heart of the Greek Easter feast\, symbolizing celebration\, abun
 dance\, and community. The roasted Spring lamb with lemon potatoes honours
  this centuries-old custom while showcasing the simplicity and excellence 
 that define the Milos culinary approach through exceptional sourcing. Trad
 itional desserts like Koulourakia and Tsoureki represent hospitality\, or 
 ‘philoxenia\,’ the Greek spirit of welcoming others. Paired with Greek
  yogurt and fresh fruit\, the final course reflects the warmth and generos
 ity that Milos extends to every guest.\nGreek Easter Menu:\nRed Dyed Eggs\
 n1st Course:\nMagiritsa\nTraditional Greek Easter Soup\n2nd Course:\nTzatz
 iki\nArtisanal Greek Cheeses\nGreek Olives\n3rd Course:\nRoasted Lamb\nRoa
 sted Spring lamb served with oven-roasted lemon potatoes\nEaster Salad\nRo
 maine Salad\, crumbled feta\, dill\nDesserts:\nKoulourakia (Easter cookies
 )\nTsoureki (Greek Easter bread)\nGreek Yogurt with assortment of fresh fr
 uit
LOCATION:estiatorio Milos
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/greek-easter-at-estiatorio-milos-toronto
 /
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
