ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/02/24/original_imaged9b29e3b-b7ea-421a-b801-6375a0b751
 34.jpg
DESCRIPTION:This immersive classical concert is transforming Daniels Spect
 rum into a living art gallery this Spring.\nFor one afternoon only\, Danie
 ls Spectrum is turning into a 360-degree art and music experience.\nToront
 o visual artist Paula Arciniega is teaming up with the Hannaford Street Si
 lver Band to reimagine Modest Mussorgsky’s iconic Pictures at an Exhibit
 ion as a fully immersive spectacle.\nThe one-time-only event surrounds aud
 iences with 15 large-scale paintings while a live 30-piece brass band perf
 orms Mussorgsky's sweeping score under the baton of renowned maestro\, Jam
 es Sommerville.\nThe afternoon opens with pianist Jamie Parker performing 
 Gershwin’s Rhapsody in Blue with a companion canvas from Arciniega\, tre
 ating audiences to yet another layer of artistry.\nIt’s part concert\, p
 art art installation\, and unlike anything else happening in Toronto this 
 Spring!\nNot to be missed\, tickets are now on sale for $45+.
LOCATION:Daniels Spectrum
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/pictures-at-an-exhibition-reimagined-a-s
 ymphony-of-sight-and-sound-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
