BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Queen Out Fem & Queer Open Mic Comedy
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260412T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260412T203000
UID:blogto-233285@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/07/original_image3c7fac8a-afb2-4a61-83a0-5a211c2d04
 14.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Looking for stage time to try out your silly lil jokes? Want t
 o hang with other fem and / or queer comedians? Just want to cure your Sun
 day scaries with some comedy?\nWELL you are in luck! Join us for the first
  edition of Queen Out Open Mic Comedy! <33\nThe list goes out at 6 pm\, wi
 th sign up on a first come\, first serve basis. The show starts promptly a
 t 6 30 pm\, and will run to approximately 8 30 pm (depending on the number
  of sign ups).\nThis mic is open to anyone that identifies as a woman\, fe
 m\, and / or member of the 2SLGBTQIA+ community. Sorry cis het dude comics
  - this one's not for you.\nYou are welcome to perform\, attend as an audi
 ence member to support fem and queer comedy\, or both!!\nThe fine print:\n
 - 5 minute sets\, "warning light" at 4 minutes\n- Free to attend with no p
 urchase required\, BUT please support the amazing venue if you can. There 
 are a range of nonalcoholic and alcoholic beverages for purchase as well a
 s food\n- The venue is fully accessible for mobility aid users including c
 ommunal and single stall gender neutral washrooms at-grade\n- All ages wel
 come but parental / guardian company is recommended for younger performers
 \n- All are welcome to watch / support this event\, including cisgender he
 terosexual men\, but performance spaces are open only to fem and / or quee
 r folx\n- Community guidelines are in place for this show and will be disc
 ussed at the top. This includes no "punching down"\, no "isms" or phobias\
 , and no aggressive crowd work. This mic is hosted and produced by a queer
 \, nonbinary comedian who takes this seriously AF\, and who is committed t
 o keeping the vibes cute and inclusive. If content of a performance isn't 
 aligned with the guidelines\, the set will be ended early.\n- We all want 
 a sexy\, healthy time! You are totally welcome to wear a mask. If you are 
 feeling sick\, please stay home!\nQuestions? Want to come out but are a li
 l nervous? Totally feel free to reach out to the producer Anna Sebastien o
 n Instagram at @annasebastiencomedy - its all about community!
LOCATION:Society Clubhouse
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/queen-out-fem-queer-open-mic-comedy-toro
 nto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Queer Self Defense TO Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260412T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260412T210000
UID:blogto-233078@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/02/original_image25551ec3-6d76-4be5-95aa-f0fe8ab89b
 8f.jpg
DESCRIPTION:We're hosting another self-defence class\, tailored specifical
 ly for the queer community! No registration is required! Just show up!\nWe
  teach you everything you need to know in an emergency. From laws to first
  aid to\, of course\, striking\, we teach it all!\nWe're hosting another s
 elf-defence class\, tailored specifically for the queer community! No regi
 stration is required! Just show up! A place for anyone to learn precious s
 kills that ultimately make you more confident and your loved ones safer.\n
 Hosted in the oldest queer theatre in the world\, we don't just teach you 
 how to punch. We teach you everything you need to know in an emergency. Fr
 om laws to first aid to\, of course\, striking\, we teach it all.\nInstruc
 tion is led by Aidan McKendrick (He/Him)\, a security professional and Kat
 y SB (She/They)\, a black belt martial artist.\nBy the end\, you’ll have
  important knowledge and physical skills to protect yourself and others at
  the most affordable price around!\nThe venue is fully accessible except f
 or the washrooms\, which require staff to run the elevator. Class is major
 ity sit-down lecture style\, with the last third being physical practice. 
 Instructors will make every effort to accommodate accessibility needs.\nPl
 ease contact us if you have specific needs or have questions. We are plann
 ing a masked and accessibility focus class in the near future.
LOCATION:Buddies in Bad Times
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/queer-self-defense-to-workshop-toronto-2
 /
X-SOURCE:blogTO
