BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:REVERIE Presents: Rae Spoon's Album Release w/ Louie Sanchez & Lee
  Waylon
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260412T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260412T210000
UID:blogto-232025@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/10/original_imagee0da2495-441c-4130-8c83-b53983e55c
 1b.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Rae Spoon Assigned Country Singer At Birth album launch joined
  by their band and incredible guests Louie Sanchez and Lee Waylon. Over by
  9pm\nRae Spoon Assigned Country Singer At Birth album launch joined by th
 eir band and incredible guests Louie Sanchez and Lee Waylon. Over by 9pm!\
 nApril 12 doors 6pm show 6:30 to 8:30pm EST\nIt's Ok* Studios\nQueen Stree
 t West\, Toronto\, ON\, Canada\nAll Ages\nDoors at 6pm Show at 6:30pm\nLee
  Waylon 6:30 to 7:00pm\nLouie Sanchez 7:10pm to 7:40pm\nRae Spoon with ban
 d 7:50pm to 8:30pm\nGeneral Admission $25 or PWYC\nChildren\, Elders\, Sup
 port People (Free) 50 available\n(embed the fees)\nLouie Sanchez is the so
 lo project of Eirene Cloma\, a Toronto-based musician originally from Nort
 h Vancouver\, BC. They are a member of nationally acclaimed kulintang ense
 mble Pantayo whose debut album was shortlisted for the Polaris Music Prize
  in 2020. Cloma is also a session musician who has worked with artists suc
 h as Kimmortal\, and Austra.\nLouie is Cloma's return to their roots as a 
 singer-songwriter trained in classical and jazz guitar. Their sound is inf
 luenced by their love for country\, folk\, and R&B. Louie narrates stories
  of labor\, loss\, and longing through their experiences as a working-clas
 s Filipino-Canadian.\nRae Spoon is a musician\, songwriter\, producer\, mu
 lti-instrumentalist\, and author. They have released thirteen solo albums 
 spanning folk\, country\, indie rock\, and electronic genres and published
  three books (Arsenal Pulp Press). Rae has been nominated for two Polaris 
 Prizes\, a Lambda Literary Award\, and a Western Canadian Music Award. The
 y have toured internationally (Canada\, Europe\, the USA\, Australia\, Chi
 na). Rae is a non-binary\, trans artist who lives with multiple disabiliti
 es. Rae’s upcoming album\, Hyper Country (2026)\, celebrates their retur
 n to country music.\nAssigned Country Singer At Birth\, an album that is e
 qually subversive and relatable\, a testament to the fact that country mus
 ic is as expansive as the people who are connected to it. Songs about tran
 s folks\, harm reduction\, disability\, inclusion\, religious trauma\, sol
 idarity and opposing colonial land occupation may seem antithetical to tra
 ditional country\, but they are as much a part of Spoon’s experiences as
  love songs\, trucks and beer.\nOn Assigned Country Singer At Birth\, Spoo
 n’s musical influences from traditional country\, to pop\, gospel\, blue
 grass\, electronic and experimental coalesce into unique combinations. Pro
 ducer and drummer\, Alaska B producer of Yamantaka Sonic Titan and Pantayo
  (both short-listed for the Polaris Prize twice). Collaborators are Robyn 
 Grey\, Evelyn Charlotte Joe\, Laurie Torres\, Thanya Iyer\, Christine Boug
 ie and Gambletron deliver nuanced performances that gel seamlessly with Ra
 e's humour and heartbreak. Vocalists Lydia Persaud\, Kimmortal\, Cassia Ha
 rdy\, Theodore Walker\, Louie Sanchez\, Rosina Kazi\, Kue Varo\, Lianne Ha
 ll and Stewart Legere form a chorus of vocal support that illustrate the v
 isceral power of people coming together to sing for change.\nACCESS:\n468 
 Queen St W. has a double door with no steps at the entrance. Once inside t
 he venue there are steps leading to the second floor\, performances will b
 e held on the first floor. There is a single-person washroom located on th
 e first floor of the venue to the back right. There are additional (2) sin
 gle-person washrooms located on the second floor of the venue at the back.
  Masks requested. Will have a CO2 meter present and one large HEPA filter 
 fan.\nemail raespoon@gmail.com with any access requests or questions
LOCATION:It's Ok* Studios
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/reverie-presents-rae-spoons-album-releas
 e-w-louie-sanchez-lee-waylon-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
