BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:South Indian Dosa by Ekta Maheshwari
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260412T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260412T143000
UID:blogto-231544@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/01/original_image140b8c99-ec2a-407b-a8a7-6b1a406012
 2e.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Discover the craft and joy of making dosa (aka dosai/thosai) 
 — South India’s iconic gluten-free\, fermented rice and lentil crepes 
 loved by so many around the world. Though they appear in every South-India
 n state with their own regional variations\, dosas share a common identity
 : delicate\, nourishing\, and endlessly versatile. This masterclass is you
 r invitation to explore this culinary tradition from the ground up.\nThis 
 is a hands-on workshop designed to deepen your understanding of gluten-fre
 e fermentation and elevate your everyday cooking. While sipping on a hot c
 up of chai and enjoying some freshly prepared snacks\, you’ll learn how 
 to work confidently with spices\, understand the nuances of dosa batter\, 
 and master the techniques needed to create beautifully thin\, golden dosas
  on a cast-iron pan. From ladling and spreading\, to flipping and serving\
 , you’ll get to practice making dosas yourself—supported by expert gui
 dance\, tips\, and troubleshooting along the way.\nA dosa is never enjoyed
  alone. To complete the experience\, we’ll also demonstrate how to prepa
 re classic South Indian sides that bring balance\, texture\, and flavour t
 o the plate:\nAloo masala (potato filling)\nPeanut chutney\nTomato-onion c
 hutney\nCoconut chutney\nYou’ll also learn how to to confidently work wi
 th spices and elevate your cooking skills with lots of tips and tricks dur
 ing the class. You’ll leave with the confidence to recreate a full dosa 
 meal at home. Every participant will take home a 16 oz container of freshl
 y prepared dosa batter—your starter kit for continuing your dosa-making 
 journey in your own kitchen.\nSome curious\, come hungry!\n-----\nEkta Mah
 eshwari is a  Chef Instructor at George Brown College\, where she shares h
 er passion for bread baking. She is also the Owner and Chef at Arth Toront
 o\, a farmers’ market based business\, where she celebrates slow-cooked\
 , from-scratch dishes inspired by both - traditional Indian home cooking a
 nd Ontario’s vibrant seasonal produce. Her teaching style blends deep cu
 linary knowledge with warmth\, curiosity and a love for sharing food tradi
 tions. @arth.toronto
LOCATION:The Depanneur
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/south-indian-dosa-by-ekta-maheshwari-tor
 onto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Storytelling with Music for Kids all Ages in Portuguese
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260412T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260412T120000
UID:blogto-233036@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/02/original_image32ca164a-d28b-41bf-b565-447432dce7
 48.jpg
DESCRIPTION:✨ Spring Edition ✨\nJoin us in celebrating the arrival of 
 spring with a joyful gathering full of stories\, music and play.\nThere wi
 ll be a storytelling circle\, singing\, and plenty of fun inspired by the 
 beauty and renewal of the season – filled with imagination\, nature and 
 a touch of magic.\nIn this special spring edition\, children and families 
 will enjoy engaging stories\, live music and interactive moments – all i
 n Portuguese!\nCome and share this delightful experience in a warm and wel
 coming environment\, perfect for little ones and grown-ups alike.\nCome an
 d live this experience full of joy and magic while enjoying a delicious co
 ffee and cheese bread from Underscore Project Café!\nIn partnership with 
 Underscore Projects\, the themed storytelling events are hosted by  Camila
  Garcia and Dani Longaray\, from Hi Blue Butterfly. Garcia is a warm and c
 reative soul dedicated to media production\, education and storytelling. W
 ith a wealth of experience as a Waldorf kindergarten teacher and summer ca
 mp leader\, she brings a touch of magic to storytelling events. Alongside 
 Camila\, Longaray brings her experience as a music teacher\, voice coach a
 nd singer\, enriching the sessions with her voice and guitar.\nThis event 
 can be in English or Portuguese in different sessions and is for children 
 of all ages – always accompanied by an adult. See below for next PORTUGU
 ESE session.\nWhen: Sunday – April 12th\, 2026  - two sessions in Portug
 uese: 11am and 2m\nWhere: Underscore Projects - 1468 Dundas St W - 2nd flo
 or - Toronto\, ON M6J 1Y6 (Dundas/Dufferin) (stroller parking is available
  at the back of the building through laneway entrance – please bring you
 r own lock)\nTickets: $10 per family - tickets must be purchased in advanc
 e at underscoreprojects.ca (this event is being co-funded by Storytelling 
 Toronto)\nAfter the event\, feel free to stay and enjoy the space – we l
 ove being a gathering place for the community!\n🌸 Come celebrate spring
  with us! We look forward to welcoming you and your little ones for a joyf
 ul and magical experience. 🌷\nAbout Us\nUnderscore Projects is a cultur
 al platform rooted in a physical\, community-oriented space that includes 
 multi-functional studios\, an artist residency\, and a gallery.\nOur missi
 on is to support underrepresented artists\, particularly those from the Br
 azilian and Latin American diaspora\, by providing opportunities for colla
 borative artistic creation\, mentorship\, and public presentation. We also
  engage children and the wider community through inclusive art education a
 nd dialogue.\nUnderscore Projects strives to connect artists to resources\
 , professional support\, and audiences\, offering a more supportive approa
 ch compared to traditional art spaces.\nLocated in the heart of Little Por
 tugal\, Toronto\, we serve as a hub for public exchange -encouraging open 
 conversations\, cultural connection\, and creative learning that reflect t
 he diverse communities we work with.
LOCATION:Underscore Projects
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/storytelling-with-music-for-kids-all-age
 s-in-portuguese-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
