BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Opera Atelier presents Pelleas et Melisande
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260413T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T170000
UID:blogto-232379@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/18/original_imageb4b3c6d2-0427-4459-b35f-02eef42297
 3d.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Opera Atelier concludes its 2025/26 season with its premiere o
 f Claude Debussy’s Pelléas et Mélisande\, at the TELUS Centre for Perf
 ormance and Learning at Koerner Hall\, from April 15-19\, 2026. Rich with 
 symbolism and dream imagery\, Pelléas et Mélisande is Debussy’s sole o
 pera\, and this uniquely imagined production has long been a dream of Co-A
 rtistic Directors Marshall Pynkoski and Jeannette Lajeunesse Zingg. Based 
 on the symbolist play by Maurice Maeterlinck\, Pelléas et Mélisande foll
 ows a prince lost in a forest who discovers a beautiful woman weeping besi
 de a pool of water – bringing him in contact with a supernatural world f
 rom which there is no escape. Associate Music Director Dr. Christopher Bag
 an enthusiastically embraced the opportunity to realize a unique score of 
 Debussy’s massive opera in a new arrangement for Opera Atelier and 14 el
 ite soloists from Tafelmusik Baroque Orchestra. Pelléas et Mélisande wil
 l feature David Fallis conducting\,and will be directed by Marshall Pynkos
 ki\, choreographed by Jeannette Lajeunesse Zingg\, with set design by Gera
 rd Gauci\, costume design by Michael Gianfrancesco and lighting design by 
 Kimberly Purtell. Full cast details\, tickets\, and information at OperaAt
 elier.com
LOCATION:TELUS Centre for Performance and Learning at Koerner Hall
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/opera-atelier-presents-pelleas-et-melisa
 nde-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
