 8f.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Only $20! Taste of Downtown Yonge: Spring Bites as the second 
 edition of a new year-round food walking tour program\, designed to connec
 t locals to the diverse flavours—and ever-evolving stories—of Toronto
 ’s downtown core.\nMondays from 5:30pm - 7:30pm starting near Gould and 
 Yonge Street.\nTours are capped at 15 participants\, and thanks to BIA sup
 port\, tickets are just $20\,\nPresented by the Downtown Yonge BIA\, Sprin
 g Bites is a 2-hour guided walking food tour running weekly on Monday even
 ings from April though June.  The tour explores Downtown Yonge through int
 ernational foods\, and hidden local landmarks —offering a invigorating w
 ay to experience the area as the weather warms up.\nThis spring edition es
 pecially invites residents of the neighbourhood invites\, along with curio
 us Toronto locals\, to discover Downtown Yonge as a neighbourhood through 
 food.\nEach tour includes visits to 4 local restaurants\, paired with enga
 ging storytelling that connects Downtown Yonge’s past\, present\, and fu
 ture\, and highlights how this ever-changing neighbourhood continues to ev
 olve through food\, culture\, and community.\n(Operated by Tour Guys\, Tor
 onto’s original walking tour company.)
