 gto.com/events/2026/03/27/original_imagec4fa1b8f-ece1-49a9-9ba9-275d4ba9e7
 23.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Life is full of questions—but what happens when the search l
 eads somewhere unexpected?\nJoin award-winning podcast The Story Collider 
 for their live storytelling show where Scientists and storytellers will ta
 ke the stage to share true\, personal stories about the moments that sent 
 them searching. From surprising discoveries to life-changing realizations\
 , these stories reveal the curiosity\, uncertainty\, and humanity behind s
 cience. Funny\, moving\, and deeply relatable\,\nThe Story Collider transf
 orms science from something you learn about into something you experience.
  No lectures. No slides. Just great stories about science and the people b
 ehind it.\nHosted by Misha Gajewski and Sara Mazrouei\, featuring stories 
 from Lexa Graham\, David Manly\, The STEAM Sisters\, Pouria Nazemi\, Emily
  Agard\, and Jen Mehrnoush Zomederis.\n🎟️ Tickets are $20 in advance\
 , or $25 at the door.\n💻 This show will be live-streamed. Live-stream t
 ickets are $20.\nThis event is part of Replay Story Fest. You can also pur
 chase 5-Show Flex Pass\, or Day Passes!\nLearn more about Replay Story Fes
 t at replaystoryfest.com.
LOCATION:Burdock
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/the-story-collider-searching-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
