BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Blue Mountain Film & Media Festival: Aontas
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T190000
UID:blogto-233015@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/01/original_imagec9e1ac90-b5d2-4370-95ac-e5c4195db6
 5d.jpg
DESCRIPTION:What happens when the trademark luck of the Irish turns sour?\
 nAontas tells the story of three women driven to desperate measures in the
 ir small Northern Ireland town. They plan to rob the local credit union\, 
 but the plan goes horribly awry\, pitting neighbours against neighbours in
  a tense standoff. The story of the robbery unfolds in reverse\, though\, 
 as writers Sarah Gordon and Damian McCann find the real drama in the circu
 mstances that forced the women to hatch the plan in the first place.\nThis
  Irish-language noir plays like Widows meets Memento as the pieces of the 
 twisty puzzle fall into place leading up to the end–or beginning.\nAn au
 dience favourite from the 2025 Blue Mountain Film + Media Festival.\nPleas
 e note: this is not a Fox Theatre screening\; regular membership discounts
  and promotions do not apply. Please contact the event organizers directly
  with questions. Thank you.
LOCATION:Fox Theatre
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/blue-mountain-film-media-festival-aontas
 -toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
