 gto.com/events/2026/03/10/original_imageac35bcd0-6ace-48ef-b717-8921c5dd71
 b1.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Experience the Arka Brotherhood: A Transformative Community fo
 r Growth-Oriented Men\nLooking to connect with other men on a deeper level
 ? This gathering is a chance to experience Men’s Work—a powerful space
  for growth\, reflection\, and connection.\nLed by members of the Arka Bro
 therhood\, this free 90-minute session offers a glimpse into the kind of w
 ork we do in our weekly circles.\nWhat to Expect:\nA short intro: “What 
 is Men’s Work?”\nCore practices and activities from our weekly meeting
 s\nOpportunities to share and connect honestly with other men\nEmbodiment 
 processes to help lean into your growth edge\nThis Is For You If:\nAware t
 hat you have much more to offer the world\nReady to overcome your fears an
 d build the life you truly desire\nSeeking genuine friendship and communit
 y with like-minded men\nLooking for self-discipline and focus\nQuestioning
  your life purpose\nWanting to play a bigger game and get out of your comf
 ort zone\nSearching for authentic connections and deeper conversations\nYo
 u’re curious about Men’s Work but not sure where to begin\n***\nEvent 
 Details\n📅 Date: Tuesday\, April 14\, 2026\n🕕 Time: 6:00 pm sharp to
  7:30 pm (Please arrive by 5:45 pm)\n📍 Location: 348 Danforth Avenue\, 
 Room 212\, Toronto\, ON M4K 1P1 (The entrance is on Danforth beside City B
 ooks. Take the stairs to the 2nd floor\, turn left at the top\, and it wil
 l be the first door on the right.)\n🎟️ Free to attend. RSVP required
 —space is limited.\n***\nAbout the Arka Brotherhood\nOur weekly\, action
 -focused circles guide men towards embodying and integrating mature mascul
 inity. We inspire men to improve their relationships\, take accountability
  for their lives\, and become trustworthy leaders.\nThis brotherhood is fo
 r men who want to train and challenge their mature masculine characteristi
 cs. It is for men who are willing to do the work necessary to move their l
 ives forward.\nOur members come from diverse backgrounds and share a commi
 tment to personal growth. We welcome all men—regardless of age\, race\, 
 faith\, or sexual orientation—who are ready to show up honestly and do t
 he work.\nLearn more about our 14 Point Code and values at arkabrotherhood
 .com
LOCATION:Arka @ The Carrot Commons
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/toronto-mens-group-open-house-arka-broth
 erhood-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
