END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Breast Cancer Screening: Understanding the Benefits\, Risks and La
 test Evidence
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T190000
UID:blogto-232681@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/25/original_imagebaffba11-4cbb-44dd-aec0-360e25c6ac
 52.jpg
DESCRIPTION:1 in 8 Canadian women will be diagnosed with breast cancer in 
 their lifetime. Early detection through screening with mammograms can impr
 ove outcomes and save lives\, but it also raises important questions about
  who should be screened\, when screening should begin\, and how to balance
  the potential benefits and harms. Understanding the latest evidence helps
  support informed decisions about breast cancer screening and prevention\n
 What to Expect:\nThe Basics of Breast Cancer: Learn how breast cancer deve
 lops\, how it is diagnosed\, and how the patterns of the disease have chan
 ged over time.\nRisk Factors: Explore the factors that influence a woman
 ’s risk of developing breast cancer\, including genetics\, hormonal fact
 ors and lifestyle.\nBreast Cancer Screening: Understand how mammography sc
 reening works\, what the scientific evidence shows about its benefits and 
 potential harms\, and how screening programs are currently implemented in 
 Canada.\nVasily Giannakeas is a scientist at Women’s College Hospital Re
 search and Innovation Institute and an assistant professor at the Dalla La
 na School of Public Health\, University of Toronto. He combines his expert
 ise in engineering\, epidemiology and public health and focuses on researc
 h in breast and ovarian cancer.\nAbout the Series\nBridging Minds: Health 
 & Science Conversations is a partnership between the Toronto Public Librar
 y and Women’s College Hospital. Through monthly discussions led by exper
 ts from across different clinical areas and scientific disciplines\, this 
 series provides attendees with the opportunity to engage directly with our
  topics and speakers and empowers communities to navigate health and scien
 ce topics confidently\, inspiring a future of informed decision-making.
LOCATION:Virtual Event
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/breast-cancer-screening-understanding-th
 e-benefits-risks-and-latest-evidence-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Daily Dose of Protest: No Kings Here  Music Gang of Four
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T110000
UID:blogto-233253@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/07/original_imageb248f704-940d-4187-80b2-00450b8d42
 09.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Daily Dose of Protest: No Kings Here! – Gang of Four\nFor mo
 re than four decades\, Gang of Four have been synonymous with rebellion\, 
 critique\, and the uncompromising spirit of post-punk. Their music has alw
 ays been more than entertainment—it’s been a weapon\, a manifesto\, an
 d a call to action. With their latest release\, “No Kings Here!”\, the
  band once again delivers a powerful anthem that speaks directly to the po
 litical and cultural turbulence of our times. Framed as a “daily dose of
  protest\,” the track is both a reminder of their legacy and a declarati
 on of their continued relevance.\nLearn More: https://marshawnkneeland.sho
 p/collection/no-kings-protest-day\nA Band Built on Resistance\nGang of Fou
 r emerged in Leeds in the late 1970s\, a period marked by economic upheava
 l\, political unrest\, and cultural transformation. Their debut album Ente
 rtainment! (1979) remains a landmark in post-punk history\, blending jagge
 d guitar riffs with funk-inspired rhythms and lyrics that dissect consumer
 ism\, inequality\, and power structures.\nUnlike many of their contemporar
 ies\, Gang of Four never sought escapism in their music. Instead\, they co
 nfronted reality head-on\, using art as a mirror to society’s contradict
 ions. This ethos has carried through every era of the band\, making them o
 ne of the most enduring voices of protest in modern music.\nNo Kings Here!
  – A Modern Protest Anthem\nThe new single\, “No Kings Here!”\, is a
  bold proclamation. The title alone rejects authoritarianism\, idol worshi
 p\, and the cult of personality that often dominates politics and culture.
  It’s a statement that resonates deeply in today’s climate\, where que
 stions of democracy\, freedom\, and power are more urgent than ever.\nMusi
 cally\, the track is quintessential Gang of Four: angular guitar lines sli
 ce through the mix\, bass grooves pulse with urgency\, and vocals deliver 
 biting commentary with a mix of anger and irony. The refrain “No kings h
 ere!” is direct and confrontational\, while the verses explore themes of
  conformity\, blind obedience\, and the dangers of idolizing leaders.\nIt
 ’s music that makes you move while making you think—a hallmark of Gang
  of Four’s style since their inception.\nThe Concept of a “Daily Dose 
 of Protest”\nBy framing the release as part of a “daily dose of protes
 t\,” Gang of Four emphasize the idea that resistance is not a one-time a
 ct but a continuous practice. Protest\, in their view\, is woven into ever
 yday life—whether through art\, conversation\, or collective action.\nTh
 is concept aligns with the band’s long-standing philosophy. From “Dama
 ged Goods” to “To Hell With Poverty”\, Gang of Four have consistentl
 y challenged listeners to question the systems they live under. “No King
 s Here!” is not just a song—it’s a reminder that protest is ongoing\
 , necessary\, and vital.\nContext in Today’s World\nThe release of “No
  Kings Here!” comes at a moment when global conversations about democrac
 y\, authoritarianism\, and freedom are at the forefront. Across continents
 \, people are grappling with questions of leadership\, power\, and account
 ability.\nGang of Four’s message resonates deeply in this context. Their
  music has always thrived in times of political turbulence\, and this new 
 track feels like both a rallying cry and a reminder: power should belong t
 o the people\, not to kings\, dictators\, or unchecked elites.\nReception 
 and Impact\nEarly reactions from fans and critics suggest that “No Kings
  Here!” is being embraced as a powerful addition to the band’s catalog
 . Longtime listeners appreciate the continuity of Gang of Four’s sound\,
  while new audiences are discovering the relevance of their message in tod
 ay’s world.\nThe track is expected to feature prominently in upcoming li
 ve performances\, where Gang of Four’s reputation for electrifying shows
  will give it even greater impact. Their concerts have always been more th
 an entertainment—they are experiences that blend music\, politics\, and 
 art into a visceral statement.\nGang of Four’s Place in Music History\nI
 t’s impossible to discuss Gang of Four without acknowledging their influ
 ence on generations of musicians. Bands ranging from Red Hot Chili Peppers
  to Rage Against the Machine have cited them as inspirations. Their fusion
  of punk energy with funk rhythms laid the groundwork for countless altern
 ative and indie acts.\nYet Gang of Four have never been content to rest on
  their legacy. Each release\, including “No Kings Here!”\, is a remind
 er that they are not a museum piece but a living\, breathing force in musi
 c. Their relevance lies not just in their past achievements but in their c
 ontinued ability to speak to the present.\nLooking Ahead\nWhile “No King
 s Here!” stands strong on its own\, fans are already speculating about w
 hether it signals a larger project—perhaps a new album or tour. Gang of 
 Four have often used singles as harbingers of broader creative endeavors\,
  and this release feels like the beginning of something bigger.\nRegardles
 s of what comes next\, the track reinforces the band’s commitment to mak
 ing music that matters. In a world saturated with disposable pop and formu
 laic rock\, Gang of Four’s refusal to compromise is refreshing. They rem
 ind us that music can still be dangerous\, still be radical\, and still be
  transformative.\nConclusion\nGang of Four’s “No Kings Here!” is mor
 e than just a new song—it’s a daily dose of protest. It’s a reminder
  that art can challenge power\, that music can inspire resistance\, and th
 at the fight against authoritarianism is ongoing.\nFor longtime fans\, it
 ’s a thrilling continuation of the band’s legacy. For newcomers\, it
 ’s an invitation to join a movement that has been shaking the foundation
 s of culture for nearly half a century.
LOCATION:Virtual Event
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/daily-dose-of-protest-no-kings-here-musi
 c-gang-of-four-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Danu's Power Point Presentation Party XXXIV
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T203000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T223000
UID:blogto-233211@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/06/original_image6e2f23af-b7b0-4e0a-be65-71cd7b969a
 79.jpg
DESCRIPTION:You have just 30 minutes to make a Power Point presentation on
  a bizarre topic you know nothing about ⁠— then just 3 minutes to pres
