 14.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Acclaimed choreographer and performer Guillaume Côté will ho
 st a free dance sword fighting workshop on Thursday\, April 16 in the danc
 e studio of Toronto's historic Elgin Theatre. Joined by cast member Lukas 
 Malkowski\, the class celebrates the return of The Tragedy of Hamlet: Prin
 ce of Denmark to the stage later this month. Côté and Malkowski will tea
 ch movements directly inspired by the production's climactic duel between 
 their characters\, Hamlet and Laertes. Open to all\, this 90-minute experi
 ence will offer participants the unique opportunity to explore the artistr
 y and physicality of dance sword fighting from an expert in Canada's balle
 t scene.\nSpace in the workshop is limited\, email tickets@showoneproducti
 ons.ca or call 647-226-3710 to RSVP.
