 gto.com/events/2026/04/07/original_image6613a5e5-7c0c-4b14-80ca-4c35ff20b5
 cb.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Come check out a line of EXCLUSIVELY trans and / or nonbinary 
 comedians coming together in solidarity to make you belly laugh. All proce
 eds to the Sondos Project\, supporting a family of 13 living in Gaza 🏳
 ️‍🌈🍉\nTea4Tea is all about having a blast while gathering in com
 munity\, celebrating the amazing comedic talent in Toronto\, and getting s
 ome hard earned trans and queer joy! This is an extra special fundraiser e
 dition that is one small part of taking care of each other in hard times.\
 nDoors 7 45 pm\, show 8 pm!\nFeaturing:\nWilly Coombes (@willycoombes\, th
 ey/them\, certified They/Them Maheym)\nOrion Candelma (@xoxosatan\, she/th
 ey\, 0rionsbelt comedy and photography)\nAda Nicolle (@adanicklmao\, she/h
 er\, Vibra Slap Comedy\, "Bags of Ice" streaming everywhere)\nAnna Penner 
 (@somequeerreads\, all pronouns\, Heheheated Rivalry)\nMeg Mackay (@megmac
 kaycomedy\, they/them\, Winnipeg Comedy Festival\, Crave\, Aborigional Peo
 ple's Television Network)\nBee Bertrand (@beerbertrandcomedy\, he/him\, Ju
 st for Laughs\, Pride Radio)\nAva VAl (@avavalcomedy\, she/her\, Just for 
 Laughs\, CBC\, CTV)\nHosted and produced by Anna Sebastien (@annasebastien
 comedy\, they/them\, Just for Laughs Toronto\, Bad Gay Advice\, Fresh Hot 
 Babes All Fem & Queer Comedy)\nAdvanced tickets are $25 but all are welcom
 e regardless of means - DM @annasebastiencomedy on Instagram for Pay What 
 You Can tickets / community pricing.\nAll welcome including respectful all
 ies who understand this is a trans inclusive space where we don't assume a
 nyone's pronouns\, gender\, or orientation 🥰\nAgain\, this show is all 
 about community - if you have any questions or are nervous about coming ou
 t\, please reach out to the producer at @annasebastiencomedy on Instagram 
 or email at anna.sebastien.comedy@gmail.com\nHope to see you there! 😊
