 gto.com/events/2026/03/26/original_image42b9390a-1b81-481f-92fe-78647dd06d
 45.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Toronto’s comedy scene is about to get a little more unpredi
 ctable.\nOn April 16th\, 2026\, a high-energy\, topical comedy show is tak
 ing over the Socap Theatre (154 Danforth Avenue) from 9:30 pm to 11:30 pm.
  The night will feature pro comedians diving into relationships\, embarras
 sing stories\, politics\, and the state of America—nothing is off-limits
 \, and no topic is safe.\nFeaturing Karen Mitches\, host of one of the bes
 t comedy podcasts in Toronto\, The Karen Mitches Podcast\, bringing her sh
 arp perspective and crowd-favorite storytelling style to the stage.\nHeadl
 ining the night is Jared Nathan\, a Kill Tony winner known for his fearles
 s delivery and unpredictable energy that keeps audiences on edge—in the 
 best way possible.\nThis isn’t just another stand-up show. It’s a nigh
 t that promises big laughs\, raw honesty\, and moments you’ll be talking
  about long after it’s over. In fact\, it might be so unfiltered it ends
  up redacted from the Department of Justice.\nIf you’re a billionaire\, 
 you are not welcome—unless you give me a 20 percent cut.
