DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260418T030000
UID:blogto-233052@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/02/original_image4c20afd5-2f5c-415b-bb57-7e1a7c68d9
 ff.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a late night dance party following the earlier sal
 sa set. Light menu available until midnight.\nToronto's Weekly Global Afte
 rparty!\nEvery Friday night at 11 PM\, Lula elevates the party to the next
  level!\nFollowing our weekly live Latin band\, Lula now features local an
 d international bands and DJs playing high-energy global beats to keep the
  dance floor moving late into the night.\nWhere People Stay At\nWhere Peop
 le Stay At is a pop-up event series founded by DJs and cultural producers 
 @La Sappe and @Sudaneeya\, that celebrates the past\, present & future of 
 afro diasporic sounds.\nFrom garden parties to hotel residencies\, panels 
 & exhibitions\, Where People Stay At brings women and gender diverse creat
 ives of color to the forefront in order to cultivate accessible & safe spa
 ces to mingle\, connect and to throw it back\, tastefully...\nIn their Lul
 a Global Late Night debut\, Ladies Take The Lead as La Sappe and Sudaneeya
  cook up a hot pot of diasporic musical influences through genres like afr
 o fusion\, batida\, baile funk\, bouillon\, dembow\, kompa\, kizomba\, kud
 uro\, salsa\, soca and global edits galore!\nBring your waistline and come
  have a good time at Lula Lounge with 'Where People Stay At' on April 17th
  from 11:30 pm to 3:30 am.\nArrive at 11 pm and enjoy some of the Latin or
 chestra before the late-night global party begins!\nBottle Service\nReserv
 ations for bottle service can be made by calling 416 588 0307.\nPlease not
 e that these tickets are general admission and do not guarantee seating. B
 uy early and get the early bird discount!
LOCATION:Lula Lounge
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/global-late-night-featuring-where-people
 -stay-at-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
