BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Collective of Cool Cats: Jazz-Classical from Beyond the Iron C
 urtain
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260417T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260417T210000
UID:blogto-232037@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/11/original_image69b81768-5b56-4626-9e51-a1a07e81a7
 56.jpg
DESCRIPTION:It's likely that the former Soviet Union is not what comes to 
 mind when you think of American Jazz\, this concert will change that.\nJaz
 z had a rocky relationship with the powers that were\, often denounced as 
 counter-revolutionary American bourgeoise decadence. It was even effective
 ly banned alongside saxophones between 1949 to 1953\, with several key fig
 ures in the scene jailed or exiled. Despite it all\, the syncopated rhythm
 s\, flashy improvised solos\, and nasty chords of jazz managed to inspire 
 musicians and listeners all over Eastern Europe and West\, Central and Eas
 t Asia.\nFeaturing Nikolai Kapustin's Viola Sonata & the Canadian premiere
  of Yuri Chugunov's Suite of Moods for Alto Sax and Piano\; as well as gro
 ovy pieces by Alexander Tsfasman\, Arno Babajanian\, Vagif Mustafazadeh\, 
 Andrei Eshpai and more.\nPerformers include:\nWallace Halladay (Saxophone)
 \nIvan Estey Jovanovic (Piano)\nand The Ezra Duo - Jacob Clewell (viola/vi
 olin) and Sasha Bult-Ito (piano)\nFriday\, April 17th\n7:00pm\nHeliconian 
 Hall\, Toronto\nTickets: $20/$30
LOCATION:Heliconian Hall
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/the-collective-of-cool-cats-jazz-classic
 al-from-beyond-the-iron-curtain-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
