 95.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The TO Live Orchestra performs West Side Story’s landmark sc
 ore performed live and perfectly synced to the film.\n“West Side never s
 ounded better.” —Huffington Post\nWith the original film projected on 
 the big screen in high definition\, Leonard Bernstein’s iconic music wil
 l be performed by a full symphony orchestra under the baton of conductor E
 van Mitchell\, with the film’s original vocals and dialogue.\nA timeless
  story of forbidden love\, this Oscar-winning classic is a moving portrait
  of connection in a dangerous\, divided world. Winner of 10 Academy Awards
 ®\, including best picture\, West Side Story is considered one of the gre
 atest achievements in the history of movie musicals.\nDirected by Robert W
 ise and Jerome Robbins\, this modern-day retelling of Romeo and Juliet fea
 tures Robbins’ electrifying choreography\, with lyrics by renowned music
 al theatre legend Stephen Sondheim\, a screenplay by Ernest Lehman based o
 n the stage play produced by Robert E. Griffith and Harold S. Prince adapt
 ed from Arthur Laurents’ book.\nTickets available @ https://eventschaser
 .com/?s=West+Side+Story+In+Concert+Toronto
LOCATION:Meridian Hall
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/west-side-story-in-concert-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
