BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Laugh & Learn - Smart Lectures & Stand-Up Comedy in Toronto
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260418T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260418T210000
UID:blogto-233124@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/04/original_image8d080e17-20e1-4818-bdcb-07fddb87f0
 0c.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Laugh & Learn is where stand-up comedy meets interesting ideas
  - all inside a relaxed bar setting.\nThe night starts with stand-up comed
 y to warm up the room\, followed by a short talk from an expert on a fasci
 nating topic.\nNo lecture halls.\nNo exams.\nJust curiosity\, laughter\, d
 rinks\, and good people.\nLECTURE Topic: The Internet Is Stalking You - Bu
 t It’s Perfectly Legal\nA fascinating talk on how your data is tracked\,
  sold\, and used to shape what you see online and why most of it is comple
 tely legal. Zoe breaks down the hidden systems behind digital marketing\, 
 data tracking\, and algorithmic influence in a way that’s eye-opening\, 
 practical\, and surprisingly entertaining.\nYOU'LL LEARN:\n• How compani
 es collect and use your personal data online\n• Why algorithms shape wha
 t you see - and what you don’t\n• The hidden business model behind “
 free” internet platforms\n• How digital marketing and data influence d
 ecisions without us realizing it\nSPEAKER: Zoe Leung\, Digital Marketing P
 rofessor & Industry Expert\nZoe Leung teaches digital marketing and works 
 with companies to understand how data\, advertising\, and technology shape
  online behavior. She brings both academic insight and real industry exper
 ience to explain how the internet really works behind the scenes and why u
 nderstanding it matters for everyone living in a digital world.\nPERFECT F
 OR:\n• Curious minds\n• Comedy lovers\n• First dates or low-pressure
  date nights\n• Solo attendees who enjoy social events\n• Anyone bored
  with the usual “dinner + drinks” routine\nENJOY:\n😂 Live stand-up 
 comedy\n🧠 A fascinating talk by a professor or expert\n🍸 Drinks + re
 laxed bar vibes\n💬 Audience Q&A + conversation\n🤝 Meet curious\, lik
 e-minded people\nWHERE:\nSociety Clubhouse\n967 College Street\, Toronto\n
