BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:SWaNKfest Toronto 2026
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260418T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260418T203000
UID:blogto-231648@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/03/original_image04918071-4c1f-45a9-956c-1cb242ab0e
 84.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Toronto’s First SWaNKfest Takes Place in April - “Single-W
 omen-and-No-Kids”\nThere is an evolution taking place and this spring th
 e first SWaNKfest will be happening in Toronto to bring 100 SWaNKs togethe
 r in celebration\, sisterhood\, and connection.\nSWaNK and the SWaNK Evolu
 tion was founded by Toronto-born Visionary Artist\, Carolyn Quan\, in 2013
  when she resided in the San Francisco Bay Area. Quan lived in the United 
 States for 36 years\, as a dual citizen of the U.S. and Canada\, and recen
 tly re-established her residency in Ontario where she was born and raised.
  With over 900 members of the SWaNK Toronto Meetup group\, she was inspire
 d to produce the SWaNKfest.\nSWaNK stands for “Single Women and No Kids
 ” and the SWaNK Evolution is taking place right now in today’s modern 
 society. It is a time in human development where more and more women are c
 hoosing to be unmarried and choosing not to have children. We are also in 
 a time where more and more women\, not by choice\, are finding themselves 
 unmarried and childfree\, yet still feel fulfilled in their lives. SWaNKs 
 include both “SWaNKs by Choice” and “SWaNKs by Circumstance”.\nThe
  SWaNKfest will feature musical performances by three dynamic entertainers
 \, an inspirational talk from a motivational speaker\, food\, non-alcoholi
 c beverages\, raffles\, and meaningful connection with other SWaNKs. It wi
 ll be held at Alternity -  a beautiful intimate downtown Toronto venue. (a
 lternity.ca/pages/our-place)\nSWaNKfest Toronto 2026 features the followin
 g.\nFlavia Abadía\, also known as Your Girl Flav\, is an International DJ
  and recording artist based in Toronto\, known for her high-energy\, globa
 l-inspired sound. She performs at major events and professional sports gam
 es\, including regular appearances with the Toronto Blue Jays.\nFlavia wil
 l also be giving a talk at the event. She is an International speaker\, ce
 rtified coach\, and transformational storyteller. After surviving a near-f
 atal car accident and rebuilding her life from the ground up\, she turned 
 adversity into purpose and impact. Today\, Flavia shares the practical min
 dset tools and strategies that helped her heal\, grow\, and achieve her dr
 eams—now performing and speaking for thousands worldwide. Her talks are 
 warm\, empowering\, and action-oriented\, leaving audiences with clarity\,
  confidence\, and the courage to go after what they truly want. (YourGirlF
 lav.com)\nJordana Talsky is a Toronto-based singer and recording artist kn
 own for her versatile voice across jazz\, pop\, soul\, funk\, world music\
 , and a cappella. Trained in opera and classical music\, she incorporates 
 live vocal looping and performs in multiple languages. She has toured inte
 rnationally\, released three albums\, and received\nrecognition from CBC S
 earchlight\, the John Lennon Songwriting Competition\, and the Sarah Vaugh
 an International Vocal Competition. (JordanaTalsky.com)\nGina P. is a Toro
 nto-based singer\, independent artist and live entertainment producer\, kn
 own for her silky-warm tone and soulful delivery. Rooted in R&B\, neo-soul
 \, and jazz\, her sound reflects influences including Anita Baker\, Angie 
 Stone\, Stevie Wonder\, and Jill Scott. Her performances are genuine\, exp
 ressive and deeply engaging. Gina released two singles in 2021\, Magic and
  Charade\, both available on streaming platforms. Gina continues to perfor
 m in the Toronto and GTA with top musicians and is working on new music to
  release in the future.(instagram.com/ginapmusic)\nWhere: Alternity - 333 
 Bloor St. W. (next to the Bata Shoe Museum)\nWhen: Saturday\, April 18 fro
 m 2 pm to 8:30 pm\nTickets can be purchased online at SWaNKevolution.com/t
 ickets\n* Tickets are limited to the first 100 SWaNKs and are $99 per SWaN
 K.\nAbout the Founder of SWaNK:\nCarolyn Quan is a “SWaNK by Choice”\,
  a multiple-award-winning artist\, an advocate for social justice\, solopr
 eneur\, and creative visionary. Her professional background includes art d
 irection and design in the music and entertainment industries in New York 
 and Toronto\, as well as over 20 years as a fine artist in Hawaii\, Califo
 rnia and Arizona. She has been featured in over 20 publications\, on radio
  and television\, and in a documentary film produced by the CBC. Her art i
 s held in the permanent collection of the Kinsey Institute and in private 
 collections worldwide. She is the winner of over 20 international art awar
 ds. (CarolynQuan.com)\nInspired to create a movement that supports women a
 nd disseminates the myth that being a single/unmarried woman without child
 ren is “bad” or undesirable\, she gave birth to the SWaNK Evolution. I
 t is a passionate goal of Carolyn’s to create a higher level of understa
 nding of SWaNKs and the issues faced by them in today’s mainstream socie
 ty.
LOCATION:Alternity
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/swankfest-toronto-2026-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
