BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Welfare
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260418T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260418T175500
UID:blogto-232096@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/12/original_image49754e94-a01d-4c5d-a374-8636832333
 a5.jpg
DESCRIPTION:“His masterpiece” – The Guardian\nWidely recognized as o
 ne of the greatest and most accomplished documentary filmmakers of all tim
 e\, Frederick Wiseman created an unprecedented body of work over the cours
 e six decades\, releasing 45 films up until his recent passing in February
  at the age of 96.\nWith so many highly regarded films to his name\, Welfa
 re is considered to be one his finest\, if not his ultimate masterpiece.\n
 Welfare shows the nature and complexity of the welfare system in sequences
  illustrating the staggering diversity of problems that constitute welfare
 : housing\, unemployment\, divorce\, medical and psychiatric problems\, ab
 andoned and abused children\, and the elderly. These issues are presented 
 in a context where welfare workers as well as clients struggle to cope wit
 h and interpret the laws and regulations that govern their work and life.\
 nIn English and Spanish\, with English subtitles.
LOCATION:Hot Docs Ted Rogers Cinema
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/welfare-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
