 97.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Psychotherapist Ann Schnurr looks at procrastination through a
  new lens. What makes us procrastinate and what is the emotional toll on d
 epression and anxiety? Ways to re-engage and overcome procrastination will
  be discussed.\nIn this talk\, you’ll learn:\n- Why procrastination is a
 n emotional response\, not a character flaw\n- How the nervous system and 
 emotional body contribute to avoidance\n- Common emotional patterns behind
  chronic delaying\n- How unprocessed emotions show\n- Gentle\, practical w
 ays to work with your emotions instead of fighting them\nThis program is f
 ree. Drop-in.
LOCATION:Toronto Public Library - Richview Branch
