BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:A Tribe Called Love
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260419T152000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260419T170000
UID:blogto-233457@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/10/original_imageeff733e7-198f-49a8-a44a-841ea70a1b
 16.jpg
DESCRIPTION:SPECIAL Q&A SCREENING ON SUNDAY\, APRIL 19TH!\nIn attendence: 
 Mohamed Ahmed (writer/director)\, Dalmar Abuzeid (lead actor – Farah)\, 
 Feaven Abera (lead actor – Halima)\, and Andy Marshall (producer).\nSet 
 in a Somali neighbourhood in Toronto\, the film follows teenagers Farah an
 d Halima as they fall in love despite warnings to stay apart because they
 ’re from different tribes. When Farah’s family relocates to Vancouver\
 , the relationship ends abruptly — until they reconnect in their twentie
 s in Toronto. But the same cultural barriers that once divided them soon r
 esurface. Will their love be strong enough to rewrite their fate\, or are 
 some histories destined to repeat themselves?\nThis modern-day Romeo and J
 uliet cautionary tale explores whether cultural barriers can truly be over
 come.
LOCATION:Fox Theatre
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/a-tribe-called-love-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
