 20.jpg
DESCRIPTION:☕️ FREE TO ATTEND! ⚽\nOn Saturday\, April 19\, Toronto26
  is bringing Coffee\, Pints & Prem: Arsenal vs Man City to Loons Pub (416 
 Roncesvalles Ave) for a proper football morning in Roncesvalles.\nThis is 
 a massive title-race clash after Man City got the better of Arsenal in the
  Cup. Now the Gunners have a chance to answer back in one of the biggest m
 atches of the run-in. 🔴🩵\nBig screens. Coffee flowing. Pints ready. 
 A pub built for matchday energy. Whether you’re backing Arsenal\, rollin
 g with City\, or just showing up for high-stakes footy\, this is where you
  want to be.\nFirst table through the door gets a round on us\, no matter 
 the size. 🍻 Plus\, you could win a jersey!\nGet there early. Lock in yo
 ur spot. Let the atmosphere build.\nSunday mornings are better with proper
  football and good people.\nWho is Toronto26?\nWe run Toronto’s top socc
 er watch parties\, building hype for 2026 while helping grow the city’s 
 soccer culture. Through high-energy events and community collaborations\, 
 we bring fans\, local businesses\, and neighbourhoods together around the 
 game.\nToronto26 is also part of the Matchday Social network\, a growing m
 ovement that connects supporters beyond the stadium by turning local pubs 
 and community spaces into matchday hubs where football culture can thrive.
 \nBecause the game isn’t only played on the pitch. It lives wherever fan
 s gather.\nToronto is a soccer city.\nwww.toronto26.com | info@toronto26.c
 om | info@matchdaysocial.com | #TorontoIsASoccerCity\n* Independent watch 
 party. Not affiliated with or endorsed by Arsenal\, Manchester City\, or t
 he league.
