BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Fairy Creek
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260419T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260419T200600
UID:blogto-232090@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/12/original_image9eb70f2d-2e24-49d6-9881-e0f4f04736
 08.jpg
DESCRIPTION:A gripping frontline dive into the lives of activists urgently
  blocking logging roads on Vancouver Island\, Canada\, in a last-ditch att
 empt to stop old-growth logging in the pristine Fairy Creek valley.\nWhen 
 police begin arresting people for standing in the way of forestry workers\
 , thousands more protestors flock to the woods to participate in a dramati
 c and historic stand-off now recognized as Canada’s largest act of civil
  disobedience. Following a cast of blockaders\, Indigenous land defenders 
 and loggers\, the film takes an insider look at the rise and fall of the c
 ontentious Fairy Creek blockade\, creating a searing portrait of contempor
 ary environmental activism.\nPromotional Partner: Planet in Focus
LOCATION:Hot Docs Ted Rogers Cinema
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/fairy-creek-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
