BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Pardon Our French! Music from Ravel & Gershwin
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260419T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260419T170000
UID:blogto-231164@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/02/20/original_imagee39c0ef0-7ec7-4c25-aacc-dea2f6fd08
 8d.jpg
DESCRIPTION:When jazz met impressionism\, the result was a bold new sound 
 that crossed continents and redefined orchestral colour. From the sparklin
 g energy of Tailleferre’s Overture for Orchestra to the sweeping grandeu
 r of Ravel’s Boléro\, this program explores how French and American com
 posers of the early 20th century absorbed and reimagined each other’s mu
 sical languages. Pianist Michael Kim performs Ravel’s Concerto for the L
 eft Hand\, a haunting and virtuosic work composed for a war-injured pianis
 t\, while Gershwin’s An American in Paris brings brassy swagger and rhyt
 hmic vitality to the streets of the French capital.
LOCATION:George Weston Recital Hall\, inside the Meridian Arts Centre
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/pardon-our-french-music-from-ravel-gersh
 win-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
