 0c.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Join us at the AGO for a vibrant a panel discussion exploring 
 how The Beatles distinctive style continues to shape contemporary fashion.
  The conversation brings together Deirdre Kelly\, author of Fashioning the
  Beatles: The Looks that Shook the World\; Joey Gollish\, creative directo
 r of Roots and founder of Mr. Saturday\; Toronto designers Lori Mancuz and
  Catherine Robinson of Call and Response Clothing\; and fashion designer a
 nd advocate David Dixon. Together\, they reflect on the lasting influence 
 of The Beatles’ visual identity and its relevance for designers today. A
 dvanced tickets required. Visit website for details.\nArtwork credit: Paul
  McCartney\, John and George. Paris\, January 1964 © 1964 Paul McCartney 
 under exclusive license to MPL Archive LLP
LOCATION:Art Gallery of Ontario
