 gto.com/events/2026/03/19/original_image1ca39560-adcb-4a47-934f-e395ae5107
 39.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Honouring the Past\, Inspiring the Future: 80 Years of Opera f
 or Everyone\nCelebrate Toronto City Opera's 80th anniversary in a delightf
 ul afternoon of music\, meals\, and merriment at the exclusive\, private D
 onalda Club. All of the proceeds go towards supporting Toronto City Opera'
 s 2026–27 season.\nEnjoy a Greek-themed lunch in anticipation for our Ju
 ne production of Orpheus in the Underworld\, as well as performances from 
 past (and future) TCO cast members.\nAttendees will have the opportunity t
 o participate in a silent auction featuring exclusive prizes from organiza
 tions such as the Canadian Opera Company\, Opera Atelier\, and the Aga Kha
 n Museum. Guests will also enjoy a 50/50 raffle and a chance to win a five
 -night all-inclusive stay at the Bahia Principe Luxury Runaway Bay Resort\
 , Jamaica.\nFeaturing performances by:\nDaniela Agostino\, Soprano\n(Diana
  – TCO’s Orpheus in the Underworld 2026\; Thunder Bay Symphony Orchest
 ra\; Toronto Operetta Theatre)\nJada Alexiou\, Mezzo-Soprano\n(“Public O
 pinion” – TCO’s Orpheus in the Underworld 2026\; The Glenn Gould Sch
 ool – Royal Conservatory of Music\; Breno Italy International Music Acad
 emy)\nRoss Mortimer\, Tenor\n(Canio – TCO’s I Pagliacci 2025\; Canadia
 n Opera Company\; Glenn Gould School – Royal Conservatory of Music)\nMat
 thew Li\, Bass\n(Sarastro – TCO’s The Magic Flute 2017\; Macina Voice 
 Competition Finalist 2025\; Opéra de Montréal\; Pacific Opera Victoria)\
 nwith TCO's Music Director Ivan Estey Jovanovic at the piano.\nAll proceed
 s from the Viva Voce Fundraiser directly support Toronto City Opera’s mi
 ssion to bring vibrant\, high-quality performing arts to the community whi
 le nurturing the next generation of operatic talent.\nTickets are expected
  to sell quickly. Early booking is strongly encouraged.\n﻿
