BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Blood on the Clocktower at Twilight Cafe Downtown Toronto
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T210000
UID:blogto-232897@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/30/original_image7135f8f0-e41b-44d0-be2f-d5d2f0205d
 27.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Whether you're a seasoned gamer or new to the world of social 
 deception games\, this event offers something for everyone. Come solo or w
 ith friends and immerse yourself in a game of Blood on the Clocktower. Our
  events are a great way to connect with members of local communities and a
 re perfect for folks arriving in Toronto looking to make new connections.\
 nWhat is Blood on the Clocktower? - Blood on the Clocktower is an advanced
  version of the game Werewolf\, where crucially\, the dead still have an i
 mportant role to play in the game. The game is run by a Storyteller who ha
 s carefully crafted an experience and facilitates the game for up to 20 pl
 ayers. It is part deduction and part deception. Set in the town of Ravensw
 ood Bluff\, players in the game assume different roles\, each with unique 
 abilities to hunt down evil or manipulate the townsfolk.\nThanks to the ge
 nerosity of Twilight Cafe Downtown\, we will have plenty of space for the 
 night to engage in the social deduction of Blood on the Clocktower. Twilig
 ht Cafe has a menu with food and both alcoholic and nonalcoholic beverages
  that you can order from while we’re having fun deducing and deceiving. 
 Tickets for this event are $20 or $13.50 for Changeling Special Events Mem
 bers.\nIf you have not played before or are newer to the game\, there will
  be a quick tutorial at the top of the event to learn how to play and ask 
 any questions from the Storyteller.\nWe will be playing the custom beginne
 r-friendly script Everyone Can Play at this event.\nAge recommendation\, 1
 6 years +\nTo learn more\, find Changeling Gaming Events Toronto on Eventb
 rite or click the website link to see this event (see right side on deskto
 p/above on mobile).
LOCATION:Twilight Cafe - Yonge & Bloor
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/blood-on-the-clocktower-at-twilight-cafe
 -downtown-toronto-toronto-2/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Death Cafe
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T200000
UID:blogto-231516@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/02/28/original_image53c1e8e7-982a-4fe8-ae25-94498a767b
 ba.jpg
DESCRIPTION:A Death Café is a gathering of people\, often strangers\, who
  will drink tea\, have a snack and discuss death together. The aim is to i
 ncrease the awareness of death with a view to helping people make the most
  of their lives. Discussions will be in small groups with no agenda\, no o
 bjectives and no particular theme. Prepare to hear and tell stories. This 
 is not a grief support or counselling session. The facilitator for this De
 ath Café is Nadine Lavoie.\nDeath Cafés are a global movement. To learn 
 more\, visit the Death Café website. Refreshments will be provided.\nSpac
 e is limited\, please register online\, in person or by phone.
LOCATION:Palmerston Library
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/death-cafe-toronto-7/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Denielle Bassels - LIVE @ Reids Distillery
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T220000
UID:blogto-232467@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/21/original_image38f5d325-cdf8-44b7-87f1-a26df6c64c
 9c.jpg
DESCRIPTION:“Her voice is the voice of a generation of women who don’t
  need apologies and know their value.” — Voxwave Magazine\nJuno nomina
 ted vocalist and songwriter Denielle Bassels is a singular presence on the
  Canadian music scene\, drawing from jazz\, folk\, blues and swing to crea
 te a sound entirely her own. Born in Toronto and forged on international s
 tages\, she first found her jazz wings singing in underground clubs across
  Europe before returning home to captivate audiences with her bold storyte
 lling and genre bending performances.\nHer music moves effortlessly betwee
 n intimate confession and theatrical swing\, earning national radio play a
 nd appearances at major festivals. Critics have praised her “uniquely po
 werful voice” and performances that deliver “solid heart punches” 
 — Tinnitist. Fresh from a three month immersion in Paris studying the Fr
 ench influence on vocal jazz\, Bassels returns with new stories\, fresh in
 spiration and the unmistakable spark that makes every performance an event
 .\n$15 tickets online. All proceeds go to the Artist.\n$20 tickets at the 
 door. $5 increase retained by Reid's Distillery.
LOCATION:Reid's Distillery
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/denielle-bassels-live-reids-distillery-t
 oronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
