BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Division
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260421T213500
UID:blogto-232804@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/28/original_image87cec1b9-4262-4c4a-8bf8-7be6949dd2
 87.jpg
DESCRIPTION:From award-winning Ukrainian Canadian writer/director Andrew K
 ushnir\, The Division puzzles through a family history shaped by war – a
 nd what gets carried forward into today’s battle.\nAfter publishing a eu
 logy for his renowned watchmaker grandfather in a national newspaper\, And
 rew is confronted by an accusation in the comments section. The charge sen
 ds him on a 19\,000-kilometre journey through Ukraine and Europe with daun
 ting questions—and the rare timepiece he's inherited. Retracing his gran
 dfather’s footsteps as a soldier and immigrant\, he unearths a family my
 thology that has astonishing implications for the present.\nIn a landscape
  where history is both weapon and wound\, Andrew’s search pulls him deep
  into the stories of a shrinking Ukrainian village\, into the fallout of R
 ussia’s full-scale invasion\, and into the silence of the dead.\nOrigina
 lly featured at Lincoln Center\, NYC\, The Division is a gripping new work
  on identity\, legacy\, and the slyness of memory. With his acclaimed blen
 d of documentary theatre and deeply personal storytelling\, Kushnir faces 
 the unspoken truths that shape both our individual and collective historie
 s — and our here and now.
LOCATION:Crow's Theatre
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/the-division-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
