 le\nDoors 7pm\nShow 8pm\nAdis Rodriguez takes us on a heartfelt journey th
 rough the classics of Cuban song\, sharing some of her most beloved compos
 itions alongside personal memories of her childhood in Cuba.\nThrough stor
 y and song\, Adis brings to life the romance\, poetry\, and emotional dept
 h that define Cuba’s rich musical tradition — from timeless boleros to
  beloved canción classics.\nJoin us for an evening celebrating the music 
 of Cuba — a country that has given the world some of its most beautiful 
 and soul-stirring melodies — at a moment when this Caribbean nation is o
 nce again facing profound challenges. Together\, we honour its enduring cu
 ltural spirit through the power of song.\nSinger and composer Adis Rodrigu
 ez is the leader of Havana 1950s\, an ensemble that in its fullest formati
 on gathers 13 players forming the largest\, woman-led Cuban group in the c
 ountry! . This special\, intimate version of the project features Juno and
  Latin Grammy winning Cuban artists Papiosco Torres(percussion)\, Roberto 
 Riveron (bass) and Jorge Betancourt (piano).\nPlease note that general adm
 ission tickets do not guarantee seating. Reservations available at lula.ca
  .\nElevate your concert experience by joining us for dinner before the sh
 ow. À La Carte and Prix Fixe dinner options available. To reserve a table
 \, please visit lula.ca/reservations or purchase a dinner and show package
  via Eventbrite.
LOCATION:Lula Lounge
