BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:2026 CDTPS Alumni Show: 365 Days/365 Plays
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T203000
UID:blogto-232735@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/26/original_image993f4fd1-937e-4f22-8c48-3dc61465ab
 6d.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Sunface Collective\, with the support of EJ3Arts\, presents 36
 5 Days/365 Plays by Suzan-Lori Parks as the University of Toronto's Center
  for Drama\, Theatre & Performance Studies (CDTPS) 2026 Alumni Show.\nWrit
 ten as one play a day beginning in November 2002\, Parks’ work responds 
 to the political and social realities of its time from war to systemic rac
 ism\, many of which continue to resonate today. This production reimagines
  selected plays in 2026\, exploring themes of collective grief\, absurdity
 \, anxiety\, and hope.\nRather than staging all 365 plays\, the creative t
 eam has curated 30 plays\, including Parks’ three “Constants\,” crea
 ting a non-linear\, maximalist performance that experiments with movement 
 and sound.\nDirected by Teodora Djuric with dramaturgy by Aria Sharma\, th
 is production is presented as part of the 2026 CDTPS Alumni Performance Pr
 oject\, an initiative supporting recent alumni in developing and presentin
 g new work.\nApril 23–25\, 2026\nHelen Gardiner Phelan Playhouse\, 79 St
 . George Street\n$10 general admission\nVisit: uoft.me/365days\nThe Playho
 use is fully accessible. For wheelchair accessible seating\, please contac
 t 365daysof2026@gmail.com\nThis production is presented by arrangement wit
 h Concord Theatricals on behalf of Samuel French\, Inc.
LOCATION:Helen Gardiner Phelan Playhouse
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/2026-cdtps-alumni-show-365-days365-plays
 -toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
