BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Exhibition Walkthrough: Rui Pimenta on Glorious Catastrophe
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T193000
UID:blogto-233016@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/01/original_image39354774-9482-4e57-984a-5f211f040b
 bd.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Join Rui Pimenta\, writer of texts about the exhibition\, for 
 a walkthrough of Glorious Catastrophe by Toronto artist Gillian Iles. Pime
 nta will share his insights about the whole installation and specific artw
 orks so visitors can engage more deeply with the metaphors and dualities p
 resented in Iles’s work.\n-\nRui Pimenta has been connected to the arts 
 for close to 30 years\, including a visual art practice from 2000-2014 dur
 ing which time he exhibited his work extensively in Canada and Europe. Sin
 ce then his creative focus has shifted towards programming and curation. I
 n 2009 he founded Art Spin\, an arts organization now in its 16th year of 
 presenting site-specific\, multidisciplinary programming in unique/alterna
 tive spaces and best known for its bicycle art tours. He was the Co-Direct
 or for the artist run Median Contemporary (2008-10) and has curated projec
 ts for Eastern Front Gallery\, Toronto Artists Project\, the Toronto Outdo
 or. Exhibition\, and the Government of Portugal. He has served on various 
 arts council juries\, was a member of the City of Toronto’s Public Art S
 trategy Advisory Committee and The Bentway’s Advisory Committee. His cur
 atorial aspirations are largely motivated by the enthusiastic pursuit of c
 reating engaging and accessible ways to present art in public space.
LOCATION:Koffler Gallery
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/exhibition-walkthrough-rui-pimenta-on-gl
 orious-catastrophe-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
