BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:How to Catch Creation
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T073000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T213000
UID:blogto-232079@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/12/original_imageaf15a926-4408-4576-ab64-798d9b57f4
 80.jpg
DESCRIPTION:“an absolute triumph” -Chicago Tribune\n“A gifted playwr
 ight“ - Variety\nWritten by Christina Anderson | Directed by Mumbi Tindy
 ebwa Otu\n\nApril 23 – May 17\, 2026\nYoung Centre for the Arts – The 
 Marilyn and Charles Baillie Theatre\n(50 Tank House Lane)\nThe only way to
  find your voice is to use it. In San Francisco\, four artists and intelle
 ctuals wrestle with creativity\, legacy\, and the complexities of love and
  family. When they uncover the work of a Black queer feminist writer from 
 the 1960s\, her words ripple across time\, intertwining their lives in une
 xpected ways. Bold and imaginative\, Christina Anderson’s latest work ex
 plores the power of artistic expression and the lasting impact of those wh
 o dare to create. A story for dreamers and idealists alike\, it challenges
  us to reconsider who gets remembered and who gets to define the future.\n
 A Nightwood Theatre\, Obsidian Theatre and Soulpepper Theatre co-productio
 n.
LOCATION:Young Centre for the Arts
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/how-to-catch-creation-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
