 esperate\, the hilarious and hyperreal satire from multimedia artist Marti
 ne Syms. Inspired by her own experience as an MFA student at the predomina
 ntly white Bard College\, The African Desperate follows the fictional Pala
 ce Bryant in her dizzying last 24 hours at art school. From critiques to k
 etamine\, Palace takes a final journey through the hedonistic\, contrived 
 and liminal world of the elite institution.\nFree general admission.
