UID:blogto-221806@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2025/07/27/original_image493ffbb7-0372-4e04-98a3-de49332afb
 45.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Celebrated cellist Steven Isserlis and Canadian pianist Connie
  Shih are frequent collaborators\, captivating audiences worldwide at venu
 es like Wigmore Hall\, Carnegie Hall\, and the Berlin Philharmonie. Beyond
  performance\, Isserlis is a passionate teacher\, author\, and broadcaster
 . As Sir John Barbirolli said\, “Steven Isserlis is a musician of immens
 e talent and insight\, whose sound and interpretation leave a deep and las
 ting impression.”\nTheir thoughtfully curated program highlights Isserli
 s’s broad musical interests\, featuring the Ritournelle by Czech compose
 r Vítězslava Kaprálová alongside beloved cello-piano repertoire gems. 
 The program also includes Beethoven’s 12 Variations on a Theme from The 
 Magic Flute\, Op. 66 and Sonata No. 3 in A major\, Op. 69\, Schumann’s 3
  Fantasiestücke\, Op. 73\, and Kabalevsky’s Sonata. Experience an excep
 tional evening of profound musicianship and emotional depth from this outs
 tanding duo.\nTickets: $60-$65\n416-366-7723
LOCATION:Jane Mallett Theatre\, St. Lawrence Centre for the Arts
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/music-toronto-steven-isserlis-and-connie
 -shih-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
