ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/12/original_image8c52cdcb-c8e6-47b6-851d-1b5c06b104
 8e.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Join us on April 23rd!\nOur Open House is an opportunity for a
 nyone interested in becoming a new member of The Garden Club of Toronto.\n
 What to Expect\nThis interactive session is designed to give potential new
  members a "behind-the-scenes" look at our club activities and charitable 
 projects.\n•	Floral Arranging Demo: "Playing with Tulips" Watch our expe
 rts transform simple spring blooms into stunning arrangements. You’ll pi
 ck up professional tips on composition and care that you can use in your o
 wn home.\n•	Meet the Members Our doors are open and our members are read
 y to chat! Ask anything you’d like about our history\, our impact in the
  city\, and what it’s really like to be part of the GCT.\n•	Learn Abou
 t Our Impact Discover the charitable work we do across Toronto and how you
 r membership helps us give back through floral design and horticulture.\n_
 _______________________________________\nWhy Join The Garden Club of Toron
 to?\nAs a member of The Garden Club of Toronto\, you gain access to a weal
 th of botanical knowledge and social opportunities:\n•	Education & Inspi
 ration: Enjoy 9 monthly meetings featuring world-class speakers and expert
 s.\n•	Community & Volunteering: Give back through diverse volunteer oppo
 rtunities and help shape our future by joining GCT committees.\n•	Skill 
 Building: Access exclusive floral design and horticultural courses taught 
 by our very own talented members.\n•	Exclusive Access: Spend your summer
 s exploring private landscapes with Summer Garden Tours of members' homes.
 \n•	Travel: Venture further afield with curated garden visits organized 
 by our specialized travel committee.\n____________________________________
 ____\nReady to grow with us? We can't wait to meet you and share our love 
 for all things green.\nThis event will be taking place at the Toronto Bota
 nical Garden.  This event will start promptly at 11:15 am.\nYou do need to
  register for this event on our website\, www.thegardencluboftoronto.ca. P
 lease email your license plate number to to office@thegardencluboftoronto.
 ca\, to avoid paying the $4.00/hour parking charge .
LOCATION:Toronto Botanical Garden
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/the-garden-club-of-toronto-prospective-m
 ember-open-house-toronto/
