 gto.com/events/2026/03/31/original_image4066ba3e-47ba-469c-b7ba-2c8ad0cf6a
 78.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a hilarious night of stand up comedy featuring TED
  MORRIS & Friends. Plus\, get a comp 13oz beer or pop with your ticket.\nB
 lack Sheep is back at Rorschach Brewing Co. with a hilarious lineup of sta
 nd up comedians\, including the incredible TED MORRIS (Just For Laughs\, A
 merica's Got Talent\, The Comedy Network & more).\nTed Morris is joined by
  Jwalit Bharwani\, Ada Nicolle\, Kristin Doucet & Nathan Griffith!\nPLUS\,
  get a complimentary 13oz beer or pop with your ticket.\nTickets are just 
 $20 in advance\, $25 at the door (if available).\nNote: This is an intimat
 e venue. Advanced ticket purchase is recommended.\nABOUT TED MORRIS\nBorn 
 in Ottawa and now making his home in Toronto\, Ted Morris discovered his l
 ove of stand up comedy while looking for a way to blow off steam while he 
 was studying to become a veterinarian.\nHe has performed at the “We’re
  Funny That Way” \, Halifax\, Winnipeg\, Glasgow and Sudbury Comedy Fest
 ivals\, is a rostered comic for the Yuk Yuk’s chain of comedy clubs and 
 a sought after corporate comedian. In 2016 he made his debut at the presti
 gious Just For Laughs Festival in Montreal where he filmed a set for Kevin
  Hart’s LOL Network.\nHis TV appearances include an hour long “Comedy 
 Now!” stand-up special airing on The Comedy Network and MTV Canada\, The
  Toronto Show\, The Comedy Network’s “Canadian Comedy Shorts” and 
 “Punched Up”\, MuchMoreMusic’s “Heat Meter”\, CBC’s Just for L
 aughs\, Winnipeg and Halifax Comedy Festivals\, Kevin Hart’s LOL Network
  and Out TV’s “PopPorn”. His latest appearance at the Halifax fest n
 ow has over 2 million online views.\nTed can be heard around the world on 
 Sirius XM Radio and in Canada is undefeated on CBC Radio’s “The Debate
 rs”.\nHe was featured in the short film “Parent Teacher” which was a
 n Official Selection of the LA Comedy Film Festival.\nHis recent accomplis
 hments include the release of his long-awaited debut comedy album “Dawn 
 of the Ted” \, being insulted by Simon Cowell on season 14 of “America
 ’s Got Talent”\, his 5th appearance at the Halifax Comedy Festival\, 3
 rd appearance at the Winnipeg Comedy Festival\, a Gala taping at JFL Montr
 eal\, Comedy Night in Canada with Rick Mercer and a Canadian Comedy Award 
 nomination for Best Stand-up Comic.
LOCATION:Rorschach Brewing
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/black-sheep-comedy-rorschach-brewing-co-
 featuring-ted-morris-toronto-2/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:BLEEDING EDGE PRESENTS: &POSITIONS
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260424T203000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260424T223000
UID:blogto-233004@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/01/original_image792e69aa-96b8-4c9a-a90b-559c86533f
 8b.jpg
DESCRIPTION:BLEEDING EDGE is bringing $POSITIONS to The Paradise Theatre f
 or its Toronto premiere. As soon as Brandon Daley’s darkly comedic crypt
 o-thriller premiered at SXSW last year\, $POSITIONS earned widespread prai
 se for its ticking time bomb pacing and the authenticity of its Middle Ame
 rican setting and characters. Join us at Paradise Theatre for the Toronto 
 premiere of this anxiety-inducing Midwestern masterpiece! Director Brandon
  Daley will be IN ATTENDANCE for a live Q&A\nBlue-collar Kansan Mike Alvar
 ado attempts to save his family from the throes of poverty by investing th
 eir savings into speculative cryptocurrencies. However\, as his investment
  strategy decays into a full-blown gambling addiction\, he sends his life 
 into a nightmarish anxiety-inducing downward spiral\, compromising his rel
