BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Hutch & Friends
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260424T210000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260424T223000
UID:blogto-233130@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/04/original_imagef5dd1ea4-1f85-49bc-a147-024ee36303
 49.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Hutch & Friends is back on April 24th @ the Burdock! This is a
  stand-up showcase of some of the best performers the city has to offer. A
 cclaimed comediennes Courtney Gilmour\, Elaine Gold\, Tom Henry and Chris 
 Robinson will all make this an evening to remember. Bios below. Get ticket
 s here:  https://www.showpass.com/hutch-friends/\nBIOS\nCourtney Gilmour i
 s an award-winning comedian and television writer. In 2017 she delivered a
  breakout performance at the Just For Laughs Festival in Montreal by becom
 ing the first female to win the prestigious Homegrown Comics Competition a
 s Canada’s top comedian. Courtney has been featured on multiple national
  broadcasts from festivals including the Winnipeg Comedy Festival\, Halifa
 x Comedy Festival\, Just For Laughs Vancouver as well as Kevin Hart’s LO
 L Network and The Howie Mandel All Stars Gala at Just For Laughs Montreal.
 \nElaine Gold is a comedian and storyteller. She was a featured storytelle
 r on Tinder Tales for 5 years\, performing on storytelling stages all over
  Toronto and Ontario. Elaine loves to honestly tell her hilarious life sto
 ries. She's old AF and loves playing the old lady card. Her last appearanc
 e at a Hutch show she had the audience howling with laughter.\nTom Henry i
 s a comedian\, actor and writer from Toronto. His acclaimed Just for Laugh
 s produced Stand Up Special\, ‘66 Jokes’\, can be found on Crave TV. H
 e's appeared at festivals such as Just For Laughs\, San Francisco Sketchfe
 st and Bridgetown Comedy Festival\, and has opened for comics such as Nate
  Bargatze\, Nikki Glaser and Tim Meadows. He was nominated for a Canadian 
 Comedy Award for Best Stand-Up Newcomer in 2012. His album\, ‘Tom Henry 
 Kills’ reached number one on the iTunes comedy charts.\nChris Robinson i
 s one of the premier comics in Canada. In 2016 he was the runner-up at the
  prestigious homegrown competition at Just For Laughs in Montreal. Later t
 hat year he was crowned Sirius XM's Top Comic. A win that granted him $25\
 ,000--and a return to Just For Laughs Montreal\, an appearance at JFL Nort
 hwest in Vancouver and his solo show at JFL42 in 2017. Chris is a working 
 actor on Netflix\, Amazon\, CMT\, and various TV and internet commercials.
  Now Magazine has described him as having "charisma and raw talent to burn
 ." Catch this rising star live and you will not be disappointed.\nHost\nPa
 ul Hutcheson is a queer comedic performer\, writer and producer. His six s
 olo shows have been produced numerous comedic solo shows which have toured
  Canada and the United States\, playing to sold-out audiences\, glowing re
 views and awards. He produces monthly comedy events Hutch & Friends and Hu
 tch’s Storytime in Toronto. He can be seen on various comedy and storyte
 lling stages in Toronto. His comedy album\, Call Me Hutch\, his first come
 dy recording\, is produced by Howl & Roar Records.  Please visit canuckhut
 ch.com for more information. "Comparable to Jim Carey\, only not obnoxious
 ." -CBC
LOCATION:Burdock
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/hutch-friends-toronto-8/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
