BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Laugh & Learn: Smart Lectures & Stand-Up Comedy in Toronto
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260424T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260424T210000
UID:blogto-233125@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/04/original_image851abe9d-2071-454c-ad0b-83bb86356b
 08.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Laugh & Learn is where stand-up comedy meets interesting ideas
  - all inside a relaxed bar setting.\nThe night starts with stand-up comed
 y to warm up the room\, followed by a short talk from an expert on a fasci
 nating topic.\nNo lecture halls.\nNo exams.\nJust curiosity\, laughter\, d
 rinks\, and good people.\nLECTURE Topic: What Doctors Really Think (But Ca
 n't Say) About Modern Life and Our Bodies\nA fascinating talk on how moder
 n habits\, health myths\, and everyday lifestyle choices are quietly affec
 ting our bodies. Drawing from his experience in medicine and healthcare st
 rategy\, Dr. Aman shares what doctors are seeing behind the scenes of mode
 rn healthcare and why many of the biggest drivers of health today have mor
 e to do with lifestyle than medicine.\nYOU’LL LEARN:\n• The biggest he
 alth myths people still believe today\n• How modern habits like sitting\
 , stress\, and screen time affect our bodies\n• What doctors wish more p
 eople understood about preventing health problems\n• Why modern healthca
 re systems often focus on treatment rather than prevention\nSPEAKER: Dr. A
 man Desai\, Physician & CEO\, Dossier Health\nDr. Aman Desai is a physicia
 n and healthcare entrepreneur who has worked across medicine\, healthcare 
 strategy\, and digital health innovation. As CEO of Dossier Health\, he fo
 cuses on improving how healthcare systems operate and how patients experie
 nce care. Dr. Aman brings both medical insight and industry perspective to
  explain how modern life is shaping our health and what we can do about it
 .\nPERFECT FOR:\n• Curious minds\n• Comedy lovers\n• First dates or 
 low-pressure date nights\n• Solo attendees who enjoy social events\n• 
 Anyone bored with the usual “dinner + drinks” routine\nENJOY:\n😂 Li
 ve stand-up comedy\n🧠 A fascinating talk by a professor or expert\n🍸
  Drinks + relaxed bar vibes\n💬 Audience Q&A + conversation\n🤝 Meet c
 urious\, like-minded people\nWHERE:\nAce of Spades Lounge and Events\n536 
 Manning Ave Lower Level\, Toronto\nWHEN:\nFriday\, April 24\, 2026\nDoors:
  6 PM | Show: 7 PM (sharp)\nHOW:\nmany tickets do you need?\nBring your fr
 iends\, date\, parents or just yourself. Grab a drink\, grab a seat\, and 
 enjoy a night that blends comedy\, learning\, and conversation.\nTickets a
 re limited - grab yours before they sell out.\nNOTE: Tickets at the door a
 re subject to availability and may be sold at a higher price.\nAdvance tic
 kets strongly recommended.
LOCATION:Ace of Spades Lounge and Events
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/laugh-learn-smart-lectures-stand-up-come
 dy-in-toronto-toronto-3/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
