 2b.jpg
DESCRIPTION:One of the biggest arts and fine craft sales of the year is ba
 ck!\nJoin us this spring for a colourful and vibrant one-day shopping even
 t featuring handcrafted work by local artists and artisans. Happening on S
 aturday\, April 25\, 2026\, you’ll find a thoughtful mix of home decor\,
  jewelry\, stained glass\, paintings\, and more just in time for Mother’
 s Day or a little special something for yourself.\nWhile you’re here\, e
 xplore the gallery and get to know the creative community at Neilson Park 
 Creative Centre.\nSale Date: Saturday\, April 25\, 2026\nSale Time: 10 am 
 to 4 pm\nLocation: Neilson Park Creative Centre\nAdmission is Free of Char
 ge!\nFor All Ages\nParking is also free\, see you there!\nFrequently asked
  questions\n1. When and where is the event taking place?\n- The event will
  be held on Saturday\, April 25\, 2026\, at Neilson Park Creative Centre (
 NPCC) from 10:00am to 4:00pm.\n2. Is there an admission fee?\n- No! The ev
 ent is free to attend.\n3. What types of items will be available?\n- You'l
 l find a variety of handmade items by local artists and artisans\, includi
 ng home decor\, jewelry\, stained glass\, paintings\, textiles\, pottery\,
  and more!\n4. Can I pay with a credit/debit card\, or is it cash only?\n-
  Most vendors accept credit and debit\, but some may be cash-only\, so bri
 nging some cash is a good idea.\n5. Is parking available?\n- Yes\, free pa
 rking is available on-site at NPCC. However\, spaces may fill up quickly\,
  so we recommend arriving early.\n6. Will there be food or refreshments?\n
 - There may be light refreshments available\, but we recommend checking ne
 arby options if you're planning to grab a full meal.\n7. Can I bring my ki
 ds or pets?\n- Children are welcome! However\, for the safety of the artwo
 rk and other visitors\, pets are not permitted indoors\, except for servic
 e animals.\n8. Are the artists and artisans selling their own work?\n- Yes
 ! The creators themselves will be at the event\, so you’ll have the chan
 ce to meet them\, learn about their process\, and purchase directly from t
 hem.\n9. Will the gallery be open during the event?\n- Yes! While you're h
 ere\, take some time to explore the NPCC gallery and learn more about our 
 resident art groups.\n10. How can I stay updated or contact NPCC with more
  questions?\n- Follow us on @npccarts or visit neilsonparkcreativecentre.c
 om for updates. You can also call us at (416) 622-5294 for any additional 
 questions.
LOCATION:Neilson Park Creative Centre
