 gto.com/events/2026/04/01/original_image7da46d4c-8e0a-4dd0-a9e5-b8cab92d19
 4a.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Kalmplex’s exhibition\, Blessed and Highly Favoured\, explor
 es identity\, community\, and the power of representation through bold\, e
 xpressive portraits. This engaging walkthrough\, led by culture leader Kar
 en Carter\, offers a unique opportunity to experience the work through con
 versation\, gaining deeper insight into the themes\, stories\, and cultura
 l influences behind the artworks.\n-\nKaren Carter is currently the Direct
 or for Museum and Heritage Services at the City of Toronto. This follows o
 ver 25 years of leadership in a wide range of arts\, culture and heritage 
 settings including roles as Executive Director of Heritage Toronto\; found
 ing Executive Director of Myseum of Toronto (not Museum of Toronto)\; co-f
 ounder of Black Artists' Network and Dialogue (BAND)\; and\, founder of C-
 Art\, a Caribbean Art Experience that connects artists and cultural worker
 s from the Caribbean region to the international art world.
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/stories-in-portrait-an-exhibition-walkth
 rough-by-karen-carter-toronto/
