ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/11/original_image49e621ba-04b2-4b32-ac8c-66c8d0fa91
 45.jpg
DESCRIPTION:🌱🌿 Come to EcoFair Toronto\, April 26! 🌍\nAre you pas
 sionate about protecting our planet and making a positive impact on the en
 vironment? We're excited to invite you to the 2026 EcoFair Toronto at Ever
 green Brick Works! 🌿\nMeet the people behind over 100 green businesses 
 and non-profits who care about our planet\, and enjoy fun\, family-friendl
 y eco-activities and good food. Whether you're a sustainability newbie or 
 a seasoned eco-warrior\, there's something for everyone at this FREE event
 !🌎\nHighlights include:\nExplore over 100 environmental non-profits and
  vendors\nEnjoy family-friendly fun activities\nDelight in delicious food 
 (veg-friendly included!)\nA playground with digital and card eco-games for
  all ages\nNature-focused activities such as seed starting and a worm-pett
 ing zoo\nArt workshops using reusable materials and items from nature\nA M
 etis inspired weaving project\nSafe cycling and basic bike mechanics works
 hops\nEV and e-bike test drives\nAttend a Clothing Swap\nCollection of unw
 anted electronics for rehabilitation or recycling\nDelight in delicious fo
 od (veg-friendly included!)\nParticipate in  a Clothing Swap\nMeet the cas
 t of TVO's Green Squad and view episodes showing passionate and environmen
 tally-savvy young hosts challenging motivated kids and their families to m
 ake fun\, eco-friendly lifestyle changes for a healthier planet.\nPlus man
 y more activities to be announced!\n🗓️ Date: April 26\, 2026 (Sunday)
 \n⏰ Time: 11 am - 4 pm\n📍 Location: Evergreen Brick Works\, (550 Bayv
 iew Ave\, Toronto\, ON)\n🙂Free admission!\nThis event is 100% organized
  by passionate volunteers.\nCo-hosts: Green Neighbours Network of Toronto 
 and Transition Toronto.\nThis event is Bullfrog-powered.
LOCATION:Evergreen Brick Works
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/2026-ecofair-toronto-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
