 50.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Toronto's beloved ecofair has levelled up after 17 years. This
  year\, EcoFair Toronto 2026 is at Evergreen Brick Works\, featuring over 
 100 exhibitors and an expected crowd of more than 3\,000 Torontonians. Adm
 ission is completely free and offers endless fun activities. Visitors can 
 explore booths from local eco-businesses and non-profits to learn about re
 al-life solutions for environment challenges. The crowd can engage in natu
 re activities like seed starting and worm-petting zoo. There are also digi
 tal and card eco-games to enjoy. Free EV and e-bike test-drives will be av
 ailable\, along with bike mechanics workshops. Kids and youth can meet the
  cast of TVO's  Green Squad and watch their episodes. There are free art w
 orkshops\, Metis-inspired weaving projects and much more. We also have a b
 ooth where visitors can drop off unwanted electronics for recycling or reh
 abilitation.
