BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:TFS Presents The Lost World and King Kong
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260426T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260426T170000
UID:blogto-232793@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/27/original_image49bae6e7-fc11-4b2b-96e1-2be5272243
 89.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The Toronto Film Society presents a double feature celebrating
  the birth of cinematic spectacle\, pairing two landmark adventures that d
 efined the movie monster. In The Lost World (1925)\, Arthur Conan Doyle’
 s dinosaurs come thrillingly to life through the pioneering stop-motion of
  Willis O’Brien\, launching a new era of screen fantasy. Eight years lat
 er\, King Kong (1933) built on that breakthrough with one of the most famo
 us creations in film history\, blending awe\, romance\, and tragedy into a
  story that still towers over the genre. Together\, these two films trace 
 the origins of movie magic - and the enduring power of imagination.
LOCATION:Paradise Theatre
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/tfs-presents-the-lost-world-and-king-kon
 g-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
