 a0.jpg
DESCRIPTION:April may have just started\, but it's not too early to get ex
 cited about The Next Toronto Comic Jam! Always held on the last Sunday of 
 the month\, this month's Jam will be on April 26th\, 7:00pm at the Cameron
  House as usual (408 Queen Street West).\nEnjoy the lovely Toronto April w
 eather by by hanging out in the back of a bar and drawing some collaborati
 ve comics with other local artist. It doesn't matter what your drawing ski
 lls are like\, just so long as you're willing to have fun.\nAs always\, we
 'll provide the paper and you can bring your favourite pencils\, pens and 
 erasers (we even have some art supplies for use here). You can then start 
 drawing a comic and let everyone else add to it. Or you can add to other p
 eople's comics. Or you can do neither and just sit back\, listen to music 
 and hangout with people who like comics.\nThis is a FREE event ! Also\, fe
 el free to bring your own zines and comics to sell\, trade or share.\n(Thi
 s month's poster was graciously drawn by Danilo Ursini. Thank you so much 
 Dani!)
