SUMMARY:Wax Carving Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260426T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260426T183000
UID:blogto-231827@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/06/original_image1080b9b2-bf07-4424-ad60-0a0a0bd785
 07.jpg
DESCRIPTION:In our Lost Wax Carving Class\, you’ll step into the world o
 f fine jewellery and learn the foundations of lost-wax design. Wether you 
 join one of our themed classes or an open studio session\, you will be gui
 ded by one of our silversmiths as you design\, cut\, sculpt\, and refine y
 our own wax piece from scratch. It’s a relaxed\, hands-on session perfec
 t for anyone looking to explore jewellery making for the first time or rec
 onnect with their creative side.\nDuration: 2.5 hours\nWhat to Expect: In 
 this 2.5 hour workshop\, you will learn how to cut\, shape\, and finish a 
 wax piece with guidance at every step. After the class\, we can optionally
  also cast your wax model into sterling silver\, polish and ship your fini
 shed piece directly to your home once complete.\nPricing: Please note that
  casting your final wax piece is optional\, and will include additional ca
 sting costs based on the gram weight of the final piece.\nWhile we would l
 ove to offer casting options in non-precious materials\, our casting partn
 ers currently only offer casting in sterling silver\, and 14k and 18k gold
 . Typical sterling silver casting costs ranges from $55 to $125\, dependin
 g on the weight of your design. We’re happy to recommend lighter\, more 
 delicate options if preferred\, however\, choosing to cast your piece is a
 lways optional\, and we’ll be sure to let you know the estimated silver 
 cost before finalizing. Shipping of your finished jewellery piece is inclu
 ded in your course fee.
LOCATION:Studio
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/wax-carving-workshop-toronto-3/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
