SUMMARY:MICHELIN-Recognized Favorites Thai Hosts One-Night Winemaker Dinne
 r with Tenuta Santome
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260427T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260427T220000
UID:blogto-233325@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/08/original_imagee694350b-1841-4fea-b5dd-dae3c0bd11
 33.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Toronto\, ON — April 8\, 2026 — This spring\, four-time MI
 CHELIN Bib Gourmand-recognized Favorites Thai will host a one-night winema
 ker dinner in collaboration with Tenuta Santomè on Monday\, April 27 at 6
 :00 PM. The Ossington restaurant will present a ticketed\, multi-course ta
 sting menu priced at $120 per person (exclusive of tax and gratuity)\, pai
 ring its contemporary Thai cuisine with wines from the Veneto-based produc
 er. Tickets for the event are available through the restaurant's OpenTable
  under 'Experience'.\nDesigned as a one-night-only experience\, the dinner
  brings together bold\, fire-driven Thai flavours with a curated selection
  of Italian wines\, offering a format that is both social and structured. 
 Each course has been developed to highlight contrast and balance\, with pa
 irings that respond to spice\, acidity\, and texture.\nThe evening will be
  hosted in partnership with Tenuta Santomè\, a winery based in the heart 
 of Italy's Treviso province\, known for its focus on expressing local grap
 e varieties through precise\, sustainable viticulture. For the dinner\, gu
 ests will be joined by winery owner William Spinazzè\, who will guide the
  pairings and share insights into the estate's approach to winemaking and 
 its perspective on Veneto terroir.\nThe collaboration builds on Favorites 
 Thai's evolving culinary direction under Head Chef Ronnie Xu\, whose cooki
 ng emphasizes charcoal-driven technique and a refined approach to Thai tra
 dition. The format offers a focused opportunity to explore how Thai cuisin
 e interacts with Italian wine in a curated setting.\nEvent details\nDate: 
 Monday\, April 27\, 2026\nTime: 6:00 PM\nLocation: Favorites Thai\, 141 Os
 sington Avenue\, Toronto\nTickets: $120 per person ++\nExperience: Multi-c
 ourse tasting menu with wine pairings\nNote: Due to the set nature of this
  menu\, Favorites Thai is unable to accomodate gluten\, shellfish\, allium
 \, or seafood allergies\nReservations: Available via OpenTable.
LOCATION:Favorites Thai
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/michelin-recognized-favorites-thai-hosts
 -one-night-winemaker-dinner-with-tenuta-santome-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
