 fc.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Vocalist and violinist\, recognized for recent work with OKAN\
 , Hilario Duran and Munir Hossn\, takes us on a journey exploring some of 
 her favourite Latin jazz\, Cuban and original compositions.\nEvent Schedul
 e\nDoor time 7 pm\nShow time 8 pm\nABOUR ELIZABETH RODRIGUEZ\nHavana-born\
 , classically trained singer\, violinist\, and composer Elizabeth Rodrigue
 z is a Latin Grammy and Grammy nominee\, as well as a two-time Juno Award 
 winner for her work as the co-leader of the Afro-Cuban duo OKAN. A dynamic
  performer\, she has toured globally across North and South America\, Euro
 pe\, and Asia\, captivating audiences with her virtuosic violin work and m
 agnetic stage presence.\nElizabeth’s music blends Afro-Latin\, jazz\, an
 d classical influences in songs that delve into themes of freedom\, justic
 e\, bravery\, and love. Leading her small ensembles\, she offers fresh tak
 es on Latin and jazz classics alongside her striking original compositions
 . She has performed and recorded with internationally acclaimed artists in
 cluding Hilario Durán\, Munir Hossn\, Lido Pimienta\, Daymé Arocena\, an
 d Bomba Estéreo\, among others. Alongside her partner Magdelys Savigne sh
 e has recently collaborated with the Walla Walla Symphony in a concert tha
 t included her own compositions.For this special presentation\, Elizabeth 
 will be joined by multi JUNO Award-winning artists Jeremy Ledbetter on pia
 no\, Roberto Riveron on bass and Matias Recharte on drums.\nTickets are ge
 neral admission and do not guarantee seating. Dinner and drinks reservatio
 ns guarantee seating and are available at www.lula.ca/reservations or by c
 alling (416) 588-0307.
LOCATION:Lula Lounge
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/elizabeth-rodriguez-latin-jazz-explorati
 ons-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
