 66.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Whether you're a seasoned gamer or new to the world of social 
 deception games\, this event offers something for everyone. Come solo or w
 ith friends and immerse yourself in a game of Blood on the Clocktower. Our
  events are a great way to connect with members of local communities and a
 re perfect for folks arriving in Toronto looking to make new connections.\
 nWhat is Blood on the Clocktower? - Blood on the Clocktower is an advanced
  version of the game Werewolf\, where crucially\, the dead still have an i
 mportant role to play in the game. The game is run by a Storyteller who ha
 s carefully crafted an experience and facilitates the game for up to 20 pl
 ayers. It is part deduction and part deception. Set in the town of Ravensw
 ood Bluff\, players in the game assume different roles\, each with unique 
 abilities to hunt down evil or manipulate the townsfolk.\nThanks to the ge
 nerosity of Twilight Cafe Midtown\, we will have plenty of space for the n
 ight to engage in the social deduction of Blood on the Clocktower. Twiligh
 t Cafe has a menu with food and both alcoholic and nonalcoholic beverages 
 that you can order from while we’re having fun deducing and deceiving. T
 ickets for this event are $20 or $13.50 for Changeling Special Events Memb
 ers.\nWherever you are on the sapphic spectrum\, you are invited to join u
 s!\nIf you have not played before or are newer to the game\, there will be
  a quick tutorial at the top of the event to learn how to play and ask any
  questions from the Storyteller.\nWe will be playing our custom script Rav
 enswood Coven at this event.\nAge recommendation\, 16 years +\nTo learn mo
 re\, find Changeling Gaming Events Toronto on Eventbrite or click the webs
 ite link to see this event (see right side on desktop/above on mobile).
LOCATION:Twilight Cafe - Midtown
