BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Alexis Baro Y La Big Band presents Afrokando
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T220000
UID:blogto-233045@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/02/original_image92468796-19dc-4334-82f7-c739cdcf82
 73.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate International Jazz Day in Toronto with JUNO-Nominate
 d Afro-Cuban Big Band Premiere at Glenn Gould Studio\nApril 30\, 2026 — 
 Toronto audiences are invited to celebrate International Jazz Day with an 
 unforgettable night of live music as internationally acclaimed Cuban-Canad
 ian trumpeter Alexis Baró presents Afrokando with his Big Band at the ico
 nic Glenn Gould Studio (CBC Building).\nThis one-night-only performance ma
 rks the debut of Afrokando\, a JUNO Award–nominated recording that reima
 gines the Afro-Cuban big band tradition. Performed by a powerful 19-piece 
 ensemble\, the concert blends Afro-Cuban rhythms\, jazz orchestration\, an
 d contemporary energy in a dynamic large-scale production.\nEvent Details\
 nDate: Thursday\, April 30\, 2026\nTime: 8:00 PM (Doors open at 7:15 PM)\n
 Venue: Glenn Gould Studio\, CBC Building (250 Front St W\, Toronto)\nTicke
 ts : https://www.alexisbaro.com/event-details/alexis-baro-y-la-big-band-pr
 esents-afrokando-1\n🎓 Student tickets available in limited quantity\nLa
 rge-scale Afro-Cuban big band performances are rare in Toronto\, making th
 is a standout cultural event for both residents and visitors. Presented as
  part of International Jazz Day\, a global celebration recognized in over 
 190 countries\, the concert highlights jazz as a unifying art form rooted 
 in cultural exchange.\nAbout Alexis Baró\nCuban-Canadian trumpeter\, comp
 oser\, and arranger Alexis Baró is an internationally recognized artist k
 nown for his dynamic performances and contributions to Afro-Cuban jazz. A 
 JUNO Award–nominated artist\, he has built a distinguished career across
  Cuba and Canada\, leading innovative large-ensemble projects.\nAbout Afro
 kando\nAfrokando is a modern revival of the Afro-Cuban big band tradition\
 , bringing new life to a historic large-ensemble format through contempora
 ry arranging and orchestration.\n📸 Media Kit / Images: [INSERT LINK]\n
 🎧 Music: [Spotify / Bandcamp links]\nMedia Contact:\n[Your Name]\nG-THR
 EE Music\n[Email] | [Phone]\n🔥 What changed (and why this works for blo
 gTO):\nEvent details moved higher + clearly formatted\nAdded doors time (i
 mportant for listings)\nIncluded address (SEO + clarity)\nClear ticket cal
 lout\nShorter\, more scannable paragraphs\n“One-night-only” emphasized
  (drives urgency)\nIf you want\, I can also:\n👉 create a blogTO-specifi
 c submission blurb (they often rewrite—but this increases chances)\n👉
  or a headline that matches their style exactly (this can make a big diffe
 rence)
LOCATION:Glenn Gould Studio
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/alexis-baro-y-la-big-band-presents-afrok
 ando-toronto/
