BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Ceramic Workshop: Build a Candle Holder or Incense Holder
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T210000
UID:blogto-233342@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/08/original_image695b9e62-78bf-45f3-b8fd-78923b25c9
 a7.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Explore hand-building techniques to create one-of-a-kind candl
 e holders or incense burners out of clay with guidance from Emily Elise!\n
 In this 2.5 hour workshop\, we will build a custom incense holder or candl
 e holder using stoneware clay. This class is open to all levels of experie
 nce\, including beginners!\nThe bulk of the workshop will be focused on ha
 nd-building forms\, using slab-rolling techniques and shape language to bu
 ild up our clay into a functional object. A demo will be provided at the b
 eginning of the workshop and guidance will be provided throughout.\nWith o
 ur remaining time we will have the option to glaze/paint custom designs on
  our greenware (semi-hardened clay).\nEach piece will then be taken to a c
 eramic studio to be bisque fired\, and dipped in a clear top coat of glaze
  and then fired once more.\nFinal works will be available for pickup at Lo
 ohoo within 3-4 weeks.\nAbout the facilitator:\nEmily Elise is a visual ar
 tist and ceramicist working out of Kitte Club in the Junction and her home
  studio in Grange Park. Emily has a background in illustration and began h
 er ceramics journey in 2025 and loves to share what she's learned along th
 e way! Check our her portfolio!\nAbout Loohoo:\nLoohoo is a cute concept g
 ift shop in Parkdale\, designed to feel like a dreamy apartment — playfu
 l\, colourful\, and weird. Think: cute stuff for your cute life\, thoughtf
 ully curated with whimsy and a touch of unhinged energy.\nLoohoo is also a
  creative community space\, hosting themed markets\, workshops\, intimate 
 concerts\, and any fun ideas we can dream up to bring the community togeth
 er to play and celebrate local creators.\n💕 Follow along on Instagram @
 shop.loohoo to see what’s new in the shop!
LOCATION:Loohoo
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/ceramic-workshop-build-a-candle-holder-o
 r-incense-holder-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Designing the Movies: His Girl Friday
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T184500
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T210000
UID:blogto-231014@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/02/17/original_image7fedef71-7fe3-4b7b-b2b2-0b133a1339
 ea.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The fast and furiously funny screwball comedy classic! Suave n
 ewspaper editor Walter Burns (Cary Grant) learns his former star reporter 
 and ex-wife Hildy Johnson (Rosalind Russell) is engaged to a boring insura
 nce man (Ralph Bellamy)—naturally\, he plots sabotage. Can Hildy triumph
  in a battle of wills against her old romantic sparring partner and\, more
  importantly\, can she resist the possibility of a scoop? Howard Hawks dir
 ects Charles Lederer’s breathless screenplay with frenzied abandon. Verb
 al wit\, slapstick\, social satire\, farce and absurdity combine with roma
 ntic comedy\, gender politics\, and commentary on corruption in the justic
 e system. From press room card games to jailhouse interviews\, the fast-ta
 lking hijinks are an early example of the overlapping dialogue that influe
 nced Altman\, Sorkin and many others. 4K restoration\, presented with an i
 ntroduction by series host Nathalie Atkinson. $18/$15
LOCATION:Revue Cinema
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/designing-the-movies-his-girl-friday-tor
 onto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Jazz at the Columbus Centre Series Package
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T210000
UID:blogto-232782@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/27/original_imaged71446a1-5510-4b33-9726-d2d89b3c7c
 ec.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Jazz at the Columbus Centre returns with five unforgettable co
 ncerts celebrating the richness\, diversity and enduring appeal of jazz.\n
 Back by popular demand\, Jazz at the Columbus Centre returns with five unf
 orgettable concerts celebrating the richness\, diversity\, and enduring ap
 peal of jazz. This curated series brings together outstanding Canadian mus
 icians and vocalists to explore iconic recordings\, global jazz influences
 \, beloved composers\, and seasonal favourites—all presented in an intim
 ate and elegant concert setting.\nFrom jazz’s greatest hits and Brazilia
 n bossa nova to the timeless music of George Gershwin\, festive holiday sw
 ing\, and Italian classics reimagined\, this series invites audiences to d
 iscover the music they love—performed with artistry\, imagination\, and 
 style.\nWhether you’re a devoted jazz fan or a curious first‑time list
 ener\, this series offers a welcoming and richly rewarding journey through
  the sound\, history\, and spirit of jazz.\nThis 5-concert series includes
  the following performances:\nJazz’s Greatest Hits – Thursday\, April 
 30\nCelebrate International Jazz Day with an all‑star ensemble led by Da
 niel Barnes as they re‑imagine classics by jazz legends.\nNapoli in Jazz
  - Thursday\, May 28\nVocalist Alyssa Giammaria lends her rich\, expressiv
 e voice to nostalgic Neapolitan song favourites reimagined in stylish jazz
  arrangements.\nAn Evening of Bossa Nova – Friday\, September 11\nBacked
  by a stellar ensemble\, acclaimed Brazilian vocalist Fernanda Cunha headl
 ines an intimate evening of classic bossa nova.\nTribute to George Gershwi
 n – Thursday\, October 29\nA musical celebration of one of the most infl
 uential composers in jazz and American popular music: George Gershwin.\nA 
 Very Jazzy Christmas – Thursday\, December 3\nJohn Alcorn and the Daniel
  Barnes Trio bring swing and swagger to musical favourites of the holiday 
 season.\nAll concerts run from 7:30 to 9:00 pm\, without an intermission.\
 nSeries sponsored by Aion Law Partners.
LOCATION:Joseph D. Carrier Art Gallery
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/jazz-at-the-columbus-centre-series-packa
 ge-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
