 cb.jpg
DESCRIPTION:A woman comes to terms with the fragility of her mental health
  while witnessing the demise of her partner through addiction – this is 
 the everyday reality of living with and loving an addict.\nMoving between 
 fantasy and reality\, past and present\, and inspired by equine therapy\, 
 the play explores the deepening bond between a Horse and a Woman: how they
  come together to negotiate their relationship\, re-discover play and how 
 they eventually heal each other in the process.\nA 80-minute high octane r
 ollercoaster with stunning visuals and immersive soundscape\, 12 Litres 88
 00 Steps is for anyone seeking a silver lining in the dark.\nProduced by T
 he Unbridled Theatre Collective and Aluna Theatre\nVenue: Factory Theatre 
 Mainspace\, 125 Bathurst St\, Toronto\, ON M5V 2R2\nRun Time: 80 minutes w
 ith no intermission.\nPerformance Schedule:\nFriday\, May 1 – 7:30pm –
  Preview\nSaturday\, May 2 – 7:30pm – Preview\nSunday\, May 3  – 2:0
 0pm – Preview\nWednesday\, May 6  – 7:30pm – Opening Performance\nTh
 ursday\, May 7  – 7:30pm – Post-Show Talkback\nFriday\, May 8 – 7:30
 pm\nSaturday\, May 9  – 7:30pm\nSunday May 10  – 2pm\nWed May 13  – 
 7:30pm\nThurs May 14  – 7:30pm – Post-Show Talkback\nFriday\, May 15  
 – 7:30pm\nSaturday\, May 16  – 7:30pm\nSunday\, May 17  – 2pm – Cl
 osing Performance\nSenior/Student/Artsworker Tickets are $25.\nRegular Tic
 kets are $35.\nSupporter Tickets are $50.\nAll Previews are $25.\nTickets 
 can be purchased online at purchase.factorytheatre.ca/events\, by phone at
  (416) 504-9971 or by email at boxoffice@factorytheatre.ca
