BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Design Craft Quilt Showcase
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260501T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260501T210000
UID:blogto-232171@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/14/original_imagebc2a73b9-e7b1-46a1-b71e-4cd56d6d92
 b7.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The Toronto Modern Quilt Guild (TMQG) is proud to announce its
  first-ever Modern Quilt Showcase\, an exhibition celebrating the art\, de
 sign and craft of modern quilting. The event takes place May 1–2\, 2026 
 at the historic Wychwood Barns in Toronto\, offering the public an unprece
 dented look at contemporary textile art created by local makers.\nWhat: To
 ronto Modern Quilt Guild Showcase 2026\nWhen: Friday\, May 1\, 2026 6 pm -
  9 pm (Gala Opening) and Saturday\, May 2\, 10 am - 5 pm\nWhere: Wychwood 
 Barns\, Toronto\, ON\nAdmission: $25 Friday and Saturday / $15 for Saturda
 y (only)\nThis landmark exhibition will feature a curated selection of mod
 ern quilts by members of the TMQG - a vibrant community of designers and m
 akers dedicated to exploring quilting as both craft and contemporary art. 
 Quilting enthusiasts\, design lovers\, families and visitors of all ages a
 re invited to explore the unique visual language of modern quilting throug
 h bold colour\, innovative composition\, and craftsmanship.\n“We are thr
 illed to bring the passion and creativity of Toronto’s modern quilting c
 ommunity to a broader audience\,” said Cristina De Miranda\, Quilt Desig
 ner and Co-Chair of the event. “This showcase is a celebration of innova
 tion\, artistic expression and the thriving maker culture right here in ou
 r city.”\nThe Showcase will feature a display of over 100 stunning quilt
 s and visitors can purchase unique art pieces made by members. Visitors of
  all ages can participate in a community quilt project that will benefit a
  family in need and try their hand at different quilting techniques. The s
 howcase also provides opportunities for local businesses\, creatives and s
 ponsors to partner with the Guild\, support the arts\, and connect directl
 y with an engaged audience of makers and craft enthusiasts.
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/art-design-craft-quilt-showcase-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
