BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Indigenous Fashion Exhibition - Always in Fashion
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260501T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260501T193000
UID:blogto-233209@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/06/original_imagea13fd515-8a81-459a-8f82-3ef4b27f61
 dd.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Opening May 1\, 2026\, witness where ancestral knowledge meets
  contemporary fashion design. ‘Always in Fashion’ is an exhibition tha
 t highlights Indigenous designers reclaiming cultural narratives\, challen
 ging colonial frameworks\, and addressing internal community tensions arou
 nd appropriation. It’s a look at how Indigenous couturiers are reshaping
  the industry and redefining fashion on their own terms\, while recognizin
 g that they have always been the blueprint.\nCurated by Amber-Dawn Bear Ro
 be (Siksika Nation)\, ‘Always in Fashion’ will stand as a celebration 
 of Indigenous design and its profound impact on fashion across the lands w
 e call Canada and the United States. Bear Robe is the Founder and Executiv
 e Director of Native Fashion Week\, whose projects converge at the interse
 ctions of Indigenous art practices\, fashion and design.\nThe exhibition w
 ill include Jeremy Arviso (Original Landlords)\, Jason Baerg (Ayimach Hori
 zons)\, Himikalas Pamela Baker (T.O.C. Legends)\, Catherine Boivin\, Maggi
 e Catface-Bear Robe\, Dorothy Grant\, Rebecca Baker-Grenier\, Michel Dumon
 t\, Korina Emmerich (EMME Studios)\, Lesley Hampton\, Shoshoni Hostler\, B
 rian Jungen\, Jontay Kahm\, Justin Jacob Louis\, Alex Manitoypes (SACRD TH
 NDR)\, Patricia Michaels\, Douglas Miles\, Kent Monkman\, Benjamin Nelson 
 (Son of Picasso)\, Randi Nelson\, Nonamey\, Melrene Saloy-Eaglespeaker (Na
 tive Diva Creations)\, Jaylene Tyme\, and Qaulluq (Clara McConnell).
LOCATION:Textile Museum of Canada
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/indigenous-fashion-exhibition-always-in-
 fashion-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:KARMA
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260501T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T151000
UID:blogto-232805@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/28/original_image169084bc-bcfa-47ad-8f54-f80e4db7bf
 6f.jpg
DESCRIPTION:From Pleiades Theatre comes the world premiere of Karma by Aks
 am Alyousef\, on stage at Theatre Passe Muraille from May 2 to 17. The sho
 w will be directed by Ash Knight\, starring Basel Daoud\, Zaynna Khalife\,
  Andrew Iles\, Tony Nash\, and Christina Tannous.\nThe bonds of family\, t
 he trauma of civil war\, the notion of forgiveness and how our circumstanc
 es shape us.\nSet in 2012\, Karma follows Adeeb\, a young man born in Cana
 da who believes that he lived a previous life in Syria. His Syrian mother\
 , Karma\, worries for his mental health\, and forces him to dismiss the no
 tion. Now an adult\, Adeeb travels to Syria\, forcing himself and his moth
 er to confront their past and current lives.
LOCATION:Theatre Passe Muraille
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/karma-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Killer B Cinema Presents: Golden Bat!
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260501T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260501T223000
UID:blogto-233360@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/09/original_image29038e68-5df0-4253-9ba1-441c67018d
 71.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Join us on May 1st for Golden Bat! The world’s first superhe
 ro! You heard that right!\nAdvanced tickets are $5 or $8 at the door (Spac
 e is limited\, and tickets sell out fast)!\nIG: Ticket link in profile.\nF
 B Ticket link: https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/killer-b-cinema-presents-golden
 -bat-tickets-1986713916806?aff=oddtdtcreator\nDoors open at 7:30 pm\, and 
 the movie begins at 8:00.\n*NO outside food or drinks\; please buy food an
 d drinks from the venue.\n*All films have closed captioning.\nMovie info:\
 nGolden Bat is a Japanese superhero created by Suzuki Ichiro and Takeo Nag
 amatsu in the autumn of 1930\, who originally debuted in a kamishibai (pap
 er theater). Some consider Ōgon Bat to be the world's first superhero and
  a precursor to later superhero characters such as the Japanese kamishibai
  character Prince of Gamma (debut in the early 1930s) and the American com
 ic book characters Superman (debut in 1938) and Batman (debut in 1939).\nW
 hen the Earth is threatened by an evil alien\, a group of UN scientists tr
 avels to the lost city of Atlantis\, where they unearth a superhuman mummy
  named The Golden Bat who is prophesied to help the humans survive this te
 rrible attack. {Wikipedia}\nInfo about See-Scape:\nOur movies will be show
 n on the second floor! There are two bars available in See-Scape. The bar 
 is open on the second floor during our event and is cash only. Debit/Credi
 t purchases are available on the main floor.\nSee-Scape also has an amazin
 g menu. To learn more about See-Scape\, please click here! https://www.see
 scapeto.com/\nSee-Scape is located at 347 Keele Street (the closest inters
 ection is Keele/Dundas) and is easily accessible via TTC. (from Keele Stat
 ion or Dundas West Station)\nParking: There is a Green P parking lot besid
 e See-Scape and a few other paid parking lots nearby.\nEach month\, join L
 izzie Violet & Zoltan Du Lac for killer B-moves from the 1930s to the pres
 ent!\nPlease like our Facebook page and Instagram @killerbcinema so you do
 n’t miss an invite.\nThank you to See-Scape and their staff! They make o
 ur monthly event extra unforgettable!\nWe hope to see you at See-Scape.
LOCATION:See-Scape
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/killer-b-cinema-presents-golden-bat-toro
 nto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
