 lled Kimjang.  Participants will learn about the origins and history of tr
 aditional poggi kimchi and the rituals of Kimjang.  They will chop and pre
 pare the kimchi* to take home for fermentation.  Recipes will also be dist
 ributed.\n*Kimchi paste contains fish sauce and fermented baby shrimp.\nFo
 od allergy notice: Please be aware that food will be used in this program.
  Certain food ingredients may cause allergic reactions in some people. Thi
 s program uses a Kimchi paste that contains fish sauce and fermented baby 
 shrimp\nThis is an in-person program for Adults.  Space is limited. *Regis
 tration opens April 3 2026.   Register online or call 416-396-3975.\nMeeti
 ng Room\, S. Walter Stewart Library\nIf you identify as a person with a di
 sability or as a person who is Deaf\, and require an accessibility accommo
 dation to participate in this program\, please contact Accessibility Servi
 ces by email accessibleservices@tpl.ca\, or voicemail\, 416-393-7099\, to 
 make a request. Please contact us at least three weeks in advance.
LOCATION:S. Walter Stewart Library\, Toronto Public Library
