BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Alex Lakusta Album Release w/ Little Jim
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T203000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260503T000000
UID:blogto-232468@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/21/original_imagee96a0f53-8269-467d-a52c-65ec215e6e
 66.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Toronto bassist and composer celebrates the release of his sop
 homore record "Island Ghosts".\nAlex Lakusta brings a rare fluidity to ins
 trumental music—where jazz\, rock\, and electronic sensibilities converg
 e in ways that feel both familiar and freshly imagined. Before releasing h
 is 2022 debut Transmit Slow\, Lakusta spent years collaborating and tourin
 g across a wide range of projects at home and abroad\, carving out a place
  within Canada’s creative circles. His ability to move seamlessly betwee
 n genres and styles has earned him a reputation for playing that is as unr
 elenting as it is intuitive—a hallmark that now defines his work as a co
 mposer and bandleader.\nHis sophomore album\, Island Ghosts\, marks a new 
 chapter—one of expansion\, reflection\, and deepening intent. Written fo
 r a six-piece ensemble\, the record unfolds as what Lakusta calls “an ab
 stract love story without words”: a collection of pieces that move like 
 memory—warm\, fleeting\, and vividly alive. The music pulses with heart 
 and clarity\, tracing his personal evolution while paying tribute to the p
 eople\, places\, and moments that continue to anchor and inspire his sound
 .
LOCATION:Burdock
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/alex-lakusta-album-release-w-little-jim-
 toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
