BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Grief Rest Stop plus
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T200000
UID:blogto-233144@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/05/original_image18fa42bd-234c-4b6e-a954-84205b3992
 ee.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Grief Rest Stop\, for those experiencing grief and bereavement
 \nLet’s let the weight we hold for grief rest a while and have a grief r
 est stop.\n6PM-8PM\n$89\nRegister you spot: https://calendly.com/ladydeath
 doula/griefreststopplus\n6 spots only\n257 Danforth Ave\, The Plant Mystic
 \nToronto M4K 1N2\nEmail ladydeathdoula@gmail.com for any questions\, or h
 elp booking.\nGrief Rest Stop+\nlay down your grief and rest a moment and 
 be supported by a grief release and one-to-one reiki.\nMeet with Adrianna\
 , aka Lady Death Doula\, a death doula and grief educator\, and Esné\, a 
 clinical hypnotherapist and reiki practitioner\, and James a reiki practit
 ioner\, a team who wants to share resources and tools for you to metaboliz
 e your grief and help find ways to shed some of the heaviness that comes w
 ith grief.\nBYOB (bring your own blanket or pillow if you like)\nElectric 
 fireplace and lit by candlelight for extra coziness\nPractice Emotional Fr
 eedom Tapping\nLearn about grief metabolizers\nGentle grief release medita
 tion\n10-12 minutes of Reiki one-on-one\nHot cup of chocolate or tea (for 
 grounding)\nWhat to expect:\n1st hour\n-build a blanket fort with Adrianna
  and your fellow grievers and go through the storytelling of your loss\; s
 hare where you are at in your grief journey and what/who/where you are gri
 eving.\n-And an introduction into Emotional Freedom Tapping (EFT) as a gri
 ef support tool led by Esné to ground into the space and the meditation.\
 n2nd hour\n-40 minute guided meditation on releasing grief led by Adrianna
 \n-Esné and James\, our reiki practitioners\, move around the room for on
 e-to-one reiki support while people relax and release sounds or movement t
 hey feel will help their grief release. *Two practitioners mean longer one
 -on-one time.\nLast 20 minutes\n-debrief should it feel right to share\, g
 rounding with tea or hot chocolate to drink and dark chocolate\nemail lady
 deathdoula@gmail.com for any questions\nYour facilitators:\nEsné is Certi
 fied Clinical Hypnotherapist and Somatic Practitioner who offers grounded\
 , practical sessions focused on revealing and healing the subconscious sel
 f –  otherwise known as the ‘shadow’. Using modalities such as Emoti
 onal Freedom Technique (EFT)\, channeling and hypnosis\, she guides sensit
 ive people to heal old patterns and traumas\, and embark on a new chapter 
 of spiritual evolution. Esné is a twice-certified Master in traditional a
 nd modern Usui Reiki\, and practices shamanic energy work\, in combination
  with Master Plant dieta retreats in the Peruvian Amazon. Esné has ongoin
 g training with the Amazonian jungle ‘Master Plants’ within the contex
 t of the Shipibo shamanic tradition. She facilitates Ayahuasca retreats wi
 thin Peru and abroad. Additionally\, she is deepening her work with the su
 bconscious at the Institute of Interpersonal Hypnotherapy\, licensed by th
 e Department of Education in the US\, as she is a recent graduate as a Cer
 tified Transpersonal Hypnotherapist program. Follow her for more events an
 d service offerings: @Natural.Esne on Instagram\, Facebook\nAdrianna Pross
 er\, aka Lady Death Doula\, Death Doula and Grief Educator\nYou might have
  seen Adrianna on CTV’s The Social as a special guest talking about the 
 Death Positive Movement\, or heard her on CBC Radio One across the country
  talking about grief and bereavement\, or in Canadian Business Magazine as
  a death industry disruptor\, or liked one of her TikTok videos sharing he
 r journey as a Death Doula. Adrianna’s brother Andrew died by suicide in
  2010 and his death catapulted her life into death work and mental health 
 advocacy: she became a suicide awareness trainer and interventionist. She 
 toured her one-woman show Everything But the Cat… for 10 years about sui
 cide loss and bereavement\, utilizing her storytelling background to creat
 e inclusive space to open a dialogue around death and dying. In 2019 Adria
 nna’s coworker Roberta asked if she wanted to go to Disneyland and South
  Korea to celebrate getting off chemo for stage four breast cancer\; Rober
 ta had a year to live and wanted a companion to get through her bucketlist
  and of course Adrianna said yes and embraced being a Death Doula for her 
 friend. Holding liminal space and being comfortable in the discomfort has 
 led Adrianna to become a hospice volunteer and grief counselor. She is cur
 rently in a fast-tracked Bachelor’s of Social Work to become a grief the
 rapist to complement all the training she has done as a death worker. Her 
 practice is anti-oppressive\, radically feminist\, and magically authentic
  to ensure she centers her companions where they are at on their care jour
 ney. Join the death positive conversation with her: @LadyDeathDoula on Tik
 Tok\, Instagram\, SubStack\nJames Johnson\, Reiki practitioner\nJames is a
 n Intuitive Energy Practitioner specializing in traditional Reiki.  His de
 ep commitment to energy healing modalities provides clients with an inclus
 ive and supportive environment for healing.  James enables individuals to 
 explore their own self healing process\; fostering personal growth and a c
 learer sense of identity.  Through his sessions clients are encouraged to 
 discover their unique paths to wellbeing and empowerment. James has been a
  Reiki practitioner for over 20 years. He is excited to be a part of the I
 nner Arts Collective hive to support and share healing journeys while he c
 ontinues to study other modalities. Currently he hosts the Inner Arts’ R
 eiki Share every last Tuesday of the month. It has been profound experienc
 es and new insights supporting people with grief that have inspired him to
  continue helping people through their grieving process.
LOCATION:The Plant Mystic
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/grief-rest-stop-plus-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
