BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Indicators - A Photography Exhibition by Benjamin Gibson - Part of
  CONTACT Photography Festival 2026
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T180000
UID:blogto-233171@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/06/original_imagece0bb4db-e149-46ef-bf0d-08dad166f2
 d2.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Proudly part of the CONTACT Photography Festival\, Indicators 
 is a large-format photography exhibition by Benjamin Gibson\, presented in
  partnership with Crown Property Management and TENSANO.\nThe exhibition t
 akes place in a raw 22nd-floor space overlooking the city\, offering a str
 iking setting for a series that explores transformation within Canada’s 
 glacial landscapes. The show runs during the opening weeks of the festival
  from May 2–12\, 2026\, and is free to the public.\nAn opening reception
  for Indicators will be held on May 5 at 6PM. RSVP via the artist’s webs
 ite to attend.\n"Indicators is a photography series examining two of Canad
 a’s most significant glacial landscapes—the Athabasca Glacier and the 
 Victoria Glacier at Lake Louise—at a moment of visible transformation. I
  photographed these sites in spring 2023\, drawn to the tension between th
 eir immense beauty and the evidence of rapid environmental change embedded
  within them.\nBy presenting these photographs at scale\, I invite viewers
  to slow down and look closely\, to sit with the possibility that what fee
 ls timeless is\, in fact\, transient. Indicators is not intended as a warn
 ing\, but as an act of witnessing—an opportunity to reflect on change al
 ready underway and on the uncertain future of landscapes long assumed to b
 e permanent." - Benjamin Gibson\, Photographer\nDates: May 2–12\, 2026\n
 Location: 180 Dundas St W\, 22nd Floor\, Toronto\, ON\nHours: Tuesday–Su
 nday\, 12PM–6PM (Closed Mondays)\nAdmission: Free\nAccess: Dedicated ele
 vator access to event floor (limited restrooms)\nOpening Reception: May 5\
 , 2026 at 6PM (RSVP via artist website)
LOCATION:180 Dundas St. W. - The 22nd Floor
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/indicators-a-photography-exhibition-by-b
 enjamin-gibson-part-of-contact-photography-festival-2026-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Kahaani Cafe: Table#7
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T220000
UID:blogto-232625@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/24/original_image37795f94-6e6a-4799-96d5-4792d408fa
 fb.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Kahaani Cafe: Table #7 – The Stories We Carry. A vision by A
 nkita Nandawat brought to life by ArtsyCulture Society\, this one of a kin
 d live stage production blends nostalgia\, emotion and live music into an 
 evening that feels like your own story unfolding on stage.\nBuilt on the b
 elief that South Asian stories deserve a world class stage\, this one nigh
 t of live music\, live storytelling and pure magic you cannot afford to mi
 ss. Set inside an intimate café\, one table becomes a witness to life’s
  changing desires\, through stories of youth\, responsibility\, love and s
 urrender.\nBacked by a phenomenal live band\, the entire production is dri
 ven by live\, heart-pounding music. Performed in Hindi\, Urdu and English\
 , this is a space for anyone who has lived between worlds\, carrying memor
 ies of home\, family and becoming.\nThe Kahaani Cafe Crew is ready. The st
 age is set.\nAll that is missing is you. Reserve your seats now.
LOCATION:Paradise Theatre
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/kahaani-cafe-table7-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Let's Move\, Willowdale: Move-a-thon & BBQ
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T140000
