 gto.com/events/2026/04/07/original_image32df093e-4b2a-4f84-bd38-a26f41c383
 af.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Duo Chromatika is the dynamic partnership of violinist Julia M
 irzoev and violinist/violist/guitarist Russell Iceberg — two versatile a
 rtists who blur the boundaries between classical tradition\, jazz virtuosi
 ty\, and the freedom of improvisation.\nFormed at the Schulich School of M
 usic\, Trio Timia is based in Montreal and is united by a shared love for 
 chamber music and a commitment to creating meaningful musical experiences.
  Taking place in the Aperture Room\, a light filled space on the top floor
  of a beautifully restored building just north of Yonge and Dundas Square\
 , each COSE event will be as much a social gathering as it will be an oppo
 rtunity for musical discovery.\n“Off the Page” and “On the Road to O
 saka” programs\nJulia Mirzoev - violin\, Russell Iceberg - violin/viola/
 guitar\, Itamar Prag - piano\, June Lee -violin and François Lamontagne 
 – cello\nINFO: 416-214-1660\n$40 (3-ticket COSE pass: $100)
LOCATION:Aperture Room
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/music-toronto-cose-celebration-of-small-
 ensembles-duo-chromatika-trio-timia-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Optimistic Writing Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T153000
UID:blogto-231882@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/07/original_image2dd5bad0-a9ef-4ab8-845d-ec3bc545ba
 f5.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Writing is an excellent way to change our perception of certai
 n moments in our life\, a way to transform them into supporting elements. 
 Optimistic writing is an autobiographical mode of writing\, leading us to 
 focus more on all the little happy events of our daily life\, even the lea
 st perceptible ones.\nThe goal is not to learn how to write in a specific 
 literary style\, but to learn how to shift our gaze away from our problems
  and to get used to approaching life with gratitude.\nPutting the words on
  the paper allows us to better anchor positive emotions in our body. Then 
 follows a moment of sharing with the group\, because happiness is amplifie
 d when it is shared.\nFree. Registration required. Register online\, in-pe
 rson\, or by phone at (416) 394-5120.
LOCATION:Toronto Public Library - Richview Branch
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/optimistic-writing-workshop-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
