BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Traditional Parsi Jamvanu with Niloufer Mavalvala
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T210000
UID:blogto-230965@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/02/15/original_imagee70fcbdc-16b3-4433-af07-1b8df40eee
 68.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Parsis are a Zoroastrian community descended from Persians who
  migrated from Persia around 7th century\, with most settling on the west 
 coast of India. Over the past 1300 years\, while it has adopted many India
 n culinary ingredients and techniques\, Parsi food has remained a unique r
 egional cuisine that still echos flavours and techniques from ancient Pers
 ia. Jamvanu refers both to the food itself\, but also to the act of intent
 ional gathering and coming together to enjoy collective sustenance.\nNilou
 fer Mavalvala is the award-winning author of several books on Parsi cookin
 g and our guide this evening she shares a traditional family style meal of
  traditional Parsi dishes\, along with stories about the food and Parsi cu
 lture. This is a unique opportunity to dive into a rare and fascinating cu
 linary tradition and learn about Parsi culture\, traditions\, customs\, an
 d heritage.\n----\nParsi Eggs Florentine\nThe Parsi take on this classic F
 rench preparation retains the essential components of eggs\, a protein and
  béchamel sauce atop a bed of spinach\, but with some distinctive twists.
  In this version\, the eggs are hard-boiled (not poached) and served Per E
 edu - a quintessential Parsi (Zoroastrian) culinary concept that literally
  translates to "eggs on top." This dish highlights the Parsi community's l
 ove for eggs while blending Persian roots and Indian spices.\nSau Badam Ni
  Curry\nImpossibly rich and said to be a "tale of one-hundred almonds" thi
 s savoury chicken curry is thickened and flavoured with almonds and is the
  one Parsi curry that has no coconut. We will enjoy with fresh Naan or Rot
 i for scooping up and dipping into the sauce!\nSaas Khichri\nA traditional
  seafood dish cooked weekly in most Parsi homes. This time it is made with
  prawns and served with khichri - a South Asian blend of spiced rice and l
 entils cooked to an almost porridge consistency. Crunchy vegetables and ta
 ngy pickles are served on the side to contrast the richness of the dish.\n
 Ravo\nParsi homes often celebrate the start of auspicious days and special
  occasions with sweets. Ravo is an irresistible milk and semolina pudding\
 , spiked with cardamom\, nutmeg and vanilla\, sometimes decoratively toppe
 d with ghee-roasted nuts and fruits.\n----\nNiloufer Mavalvala is an exper
 ienced home cook and a multiple “Best In The World” cookbook award-win
 ning author\, who believes her passion has a purpose. Her passion is teach
 ing cooking\, and her purpose is to spread ancient Parsi cuisine far and w
 ide. She enjoys cooking for others\, having been influenced by her family 
 of good home cooks\, particularly her mother and aunt. She was born and ra
 ised in Karachi and has lived in several cities\, including Dubai\, London
 \, and Toronto. Niloufer enjoys welcoming people from other cultures and c
 uisines because she feels that food connects us all and that breaking brea
 d together is the easiest way to bond. Follow her on Instagram\, Facebook\
 , and her website\, Niloufer’s Kitchen. nilouferskitchen.com | @niloufer
 skitchen\n—–\nEvery weekend The Depanneur invites a guest chef to host
  a fun\, family-style dinner party.\n@thedepanneur
LOCATION:The Depanneur
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/traditional-parsi-jamvanu-with-niloufer-
 mavalvala-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Unleash Your Inner Artist: A Butterfly Drawing Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T160000
UID:blogto-233014@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/01/original_image0049d617-14ac-42c8-8972-32e09e40b0
 79.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Overview\nJoin Toronto artist\, Alan Li\, for an immersive 3-h
 our graphite & ink drawing workshop. Discover the intricate beauty of butt
 erfly specimens as you learn to capture their delicate details with precis
 ion and creativity.\nUnder Alan's expert guidance\, you'll master essentia
 l drawing techniques and explore the nuances of shading and texture. Wheth
 er you're a seasoned artist or just starting your creative journey\, this 
 workshop is designed to inspire you.\nKey Highlights\nHands-on instruction
 : Learn from a skilled artist and receive personalized feedback.\nHigh-qua
 lity materials: All necessary supplies are included with the cost of the c
 lass.\nA unique experience: Explore the intricacies of butterflies and the
 ir anatomy.\nA fun and supportive atmosphere: Connect with fellow artists.
 \nDon't miss this opportunity to hone your drawing skills and create stunn
 ing works of art. Sign up now and let your imagination soar!\nNo prior exp
 erience required. All materials provided.\nWho is this for\n🦋 Open to a
 rtists of all levels\, or as a Mother’s Day gift. Come draw together or 
 gift a spot to someone who loves art and quiet creativity.\nAbout your ins
 tructor\nArtist and conservationist Alan Li uses pencils and paint to docu
 ment the wonders of the natural world. Alan’s mission is to build connec
 tions to nature through art-based education. Since 2015\, he has been part
 nering with non-profit environmental organizations to teach nature focused
  art programs and workshops.\nSee more of his works here: https://www.alan
 lidrawings.com/\nHow to get here\nWe are at College and Spadina. The 506 a
 nd 510 streetcar are the closest options. At College\, just head South on 
 Spadina. You will find us on the West side at 448 Spadina Avenue.\nLimited
  street parking is available.
LOCATION:Gwartzman's Art Supplies
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/unleash-your-inner-artist-a-butterfly-dr
 awing-workshop-toronto-2/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
