 traordinary linguistic and cultural diversity.\nEach edition brings togeth
 er participants with diverse mother tongues who read excerpts of poetry\, 
 theatre\, fiction\, philosophy\, and song lyrics in both their original la
 nguage and in English translation. This chapter’s theme is “Freedom”
 .\nFollowing the event\, we’ll gather for an informal reception to conne
 ct and continue the conversation over light snacks and refreshments.\nJoin
