BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Author Discussion: Radical Antiquity with Christopher Zeichmann
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260505T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260505T200000
UID:blogto-232723@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/26/original_image89d22ad3-0ec5-43a7-b16c-4fd9f5356b
 a7.jpg
DESCRIPTION:TPL presents historian Christopher Zeichmann in conversation w
 ith Nahlah Ayed at the Toronto Reference Library's Jack Rabinovitch Readin
 g Room.\nIn his groundbreaking book Radical Antiquity: Free Love Zoroastri
 ans\, Farming Pirates\, and Ancient Uprisings\, historian and religious st
 udies scholar Christopher Zeichmann takes us on an uncommon ground-level t
 our through the ancient Greco-Roman world. Instead of viewing this period 
 through the lens of elites\, Zeichmann recovers the stories of escaped sla
 ves\, self-governing pirates\, radical religious sects\, and reclusive com
 munities who rejected the state entirely. From Spartacus and the uprisings
  of the enslaved to "free love" Zoroastrians who practiced radical gender 
 equality\, these communities sought an egalitarian way of life that avoide
 d the coercion\, hierarchy\, and exploitation that characterized the empir
 es around them.\nJoin Toronto Metropolitan University professor Christophe
 r Zeichmann and CBC IDeas host Nahlah Ayed for a revelatory conversation t
 hat radically expands our understanding of the ancient world and what it m
 eans to live freely.\nQ&A and book signing to follow. Books available for 
 purchase.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, Jack Robinovitch Reading Room (4th fl
 oor)
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/author-discussion-radical-antiquity-with
 -christopher-zeichmann-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
