BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Yoga & Acupuncture - spring renewal
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260505T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260505T200000
UID:blogto-232963@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/31/original_image36453470-2dde-40ac-9a28-7c9a849e3e
 0b.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an immersive evening to rejuvenate your spirit thr
 ough the ancient practice of yoga and acupuncture. These techniques will b
 e paired with hands on assistance while you're in postures to deepen the s
 tretch\, yoga nidra\, and sound bowls.\nA thoughtfully curated experience 
 that weaves together the sweet release of yin yoga and healing acupuncture
  to create balance through the body's vital energy and target deep connect
 ive tissues.\nWhat to expect\nWe'll connect to the breath and move through
  an hour long yin yoga class that'll restore and give access to deeper\, s
 tiffer connective tissues. During this time\, you'll receive hands on assi
 stance (massage techniques) as you hold the postures to encourage further 
 release and space.\nDuring Savasana\, Katya will offer acupuncture in comm
 only stressed points of the body while Andrea guides the group through yog
 a nidra (yogic sleep).\nTo close\, sound bowls will accompany the efforts 
 to relax and renew the body.\nMats and props will be provided. You're more
  than welcome to bring your own as well.\nDoors will open at 6:15pm to all
 ow time to settle in. Please plan to arrive at least a couple minutes befo
 re 6:30pm.\nDetailed entry instructions for Kula Yoga Studio will be share
 d via email one day prior to the event\, as well as\, a consent form.\nWe 
 look forward to welcoming you! 🌱\nYour guides\nAndrea is a yoga\, medit
 ation\, and breathwork instructor who brings an infectious enthusiasm to h
 er classes and workshops in hopes of inspiring students with the dynamic p
 rinciples of yoga so they can begin to build their own practices with conf
 idence. Andrea's classes are intelligently sequenced\, accessible for stud
 ents of all levels\, while being challenging and informative.\nKatya is a 
 massage therapist\, acupuncturist\, and sound facilitator. Working for 10 
 years in Toronto's wellness space\, Katya's treatments have always been in
 fluenced by different spiritual practices and conscious expansion. Through
  her combination of skills\, namely\, massage\, lymphatic drainage\, acupu
 ncture\, and spinal energetics\, her work has been described as very hands
 -on and deeply relaxing.\nReserve your spot\nExchange: $70 + Eventbrite Fe
 es\nSpace is limited due to the practices and techniques that will be offe
 red.
LOCATION:Kula Yoga Studio
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/yoga-acupuncture-spring-renewal-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
