END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Finding Common Ground: Where Music & Love Meet
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260508T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260508T210000
UID:blogto-231809@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/06/original_image7fd8f2c8-0e1e-4ab4-a0b4-7421e639fc
 b2.jpg
DESCRIPTION:A plea and guiding map for humanity\, expressed in music\, rec
 eives its world premiere when the Upper Canada Choristers and their accomp
 lished Latin ensemble Cantemos premiere "Common Ground"\, a 6-movement cyc
 le written for them by their music director\, Laurie Evan Fraser. The new 
 work is dedicated to the insightful and widely followed U.S. historian Hea
 ther Cox Richardson\, who advocates for “art as joyful resistance”. Th
 e music features settings of poetry in English by Jacqui Atkin and in Span
 ish by Jacinto Salcedo. With the instrumental participation of the choir
 ’s pianist Hye Won (Cecilia) Lee\, and guest oboist Karen Ages.\nIn line
  with the theme of empathy and understanding\, the choir performs Broadway
  numbers by Richard Rodgers\, Lerner and Lowe\, and others. Cantemos sings
  Venezuela’s energetic unofficial national anthem\, Alma llanera (Soul o
 f the Plains).\nTICKETS\, $30\, are available from https://tinyurl.com/Eve
 ntbrite-FindingCommonGround.  Children and youths 16 and under are admitte
 d free when accompanied by an adult.\nACCESSIBILITY: Accessible entrance o
 n east side of the church.\nALSO STREAMING LIVE: The performance also stre
 ams online via https://www.uppercanadachoristers.org and https://bit.ly/4l
 22UT0. There is no charge\, but donations are most welcome.\nSponsored by 
 The Mills Team\, Royal Lepage Signature Realty.
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/finding-common-ground-where-music-love-m
 eet-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
