BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bad Girls of History: A Burlesque Tribute
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260509T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260509T210000
UID:blogto-231231@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/02/22/original_imagefb627572-0d08-4853-a6ae-aa53583a88
 5a.jpg
DESCRIPTION:"Well-behaved women seldom make history". - Laurel Thatcher Ul
 rich\nScarlett LaFlamme Burlesque's beloved biennial Bad Girls of History 
 show is back with a brand-new edition!\nWomen have had disproportionate ru
 les and limits placed on our behaviour and the way we live our lives in pa
 triarchal societies for too big a chunk of history. To dare to step out of
  line and rebel has historically been the only way for women to claim agen
 cy and the chance to live extraordinary lives. We may be maligned or punis
 hed for it\, but to not take the chance is not an option. Come see the pro
 of of that onstage at Revival on May 9!\nBad Girls of History is not a sho
 w about good girls\, but it's also not a show about true villains. This is
  a no-fascist zone. This is a show celebrating messy\, complicated\, brave
 \, rebellious\, adventurous women who made an impact by refusing to be mee
 k and subservient. And what better way to celebrate them but through the o
 nly art form that truly applauds women behaving the opposite of how we're 
 supposed to in public: burlesque!\nSTARRING a stunning cast of history...b
 uffs:\nCOCO LA CREME\nFANNIE FULLENWEIDER\nFATIMA NOOR MAHMOUD\nHELEN OF T
 RONNA\nOPTIMAL TEASE\nPEPPER LA DUKE\nPRINCESS PALMSIES\nSASS E. SILVER\nS
 CARLETT LAFLAMME\n\nSNACKBABY THICCUMS\n\nHOSTED BY:\nALLYSIN CHAYNES\nSPO
 NSORED BY:\nANY KEY PRESS\nMORE TBA!\nVENDORS:\nCHRIS ROBERTS\, TAROT READ
 ER\nMORE TBA!\nSATURDAY\, MAY 9\, 2026\nREVIVAL EVENT VENUE\, 783 COLLEGE 
 ST.\nDOORS 6:00\, SHOW 7:00 SHARP\nTICKETS: https://events.com/r/en_US/tic
 kets/bad-girls-of-history-a-burlesque-tribute-toronto-may-1029750\nGENERAL
  ADMISSION: $20 advance\, $30 door\nVIP THEATRE (guaranteed seating in a s
 pecial section up front): $40 advance\nVIP BOOTH (ONE available\, cushy ho
 rseshoe booth up front for just you and your group\, comfortably seats 5-6
 ): $200 advance\nThis series has been running since 2014\, including being
