BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:We\, Otherwise - Music& Art Residency at Tranzac
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260510T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260510T213000
UID:blogto-232165@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/13/original_image32bf8dea-0318-4c85-84d8-3ad3cac881
 93.jpg
DESCRIPTION:What happens when music becomes a place to meet?\nWe are a col
 lective of three culturally diverse women working across music\, curation\
 , and arts administration\, brought together by a shared interest in creat
 ing spaces where artists and audiences can encounter one another more deep
 ly.\nThis project proposes a recurring\, intimate Sunday series designed a
 s a cultural meeting point. Each month\, we invite two artists from differ
 ent cultural backgrounds to share an evening where performance\, dialogue\
 , and gathering are intentionally woven together.\nThe evening unfolds in 
 three parts:\n-  a conversation where the invited musicians speak about th
 eir practice\, lineage\, and influences\;\n-  a live musical exchange wher
 e they respond to one another in real time\;\n-  a participatory artistic 
 activation that invites the audience to move from observers to co-holders 
 of the space.\nOur intention is to create nights that feel thoughtful\, al
 ive\, and relational\, where artists are not only presented\, but genuinel
 y hosted\, and where cultural difference becomes a place for curiosity\, l
 istening\, and connection.
LOCATION:Tranzac Club
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/we-otherwise-music-art-residency-at-tran
 zac-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
