BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Five Day Cake Baking & Decorating Masterclass
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260511T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260511T150000
UID:blogto-231764@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/04/original_image3a8de528-2ce2-4d9b-8a8c-82d662a988
 21.jpg
DESCRIPTION:If you've always dreamed of being a cake decorator\, this 5-da
 y masterclass is the perfect introduction to Cakes!\nThis class is perfect
  for absolute beginners! This is a 5 day course running for 5 hours each d
 ay.\nOUTLINE\nDAY 1: FOUNDATIONS OF CAKE BAKING AND BUTTERCREAM MAKING\nDA
 Y 2: MAKING A RAINBOW STRIPED CAKE\nDAY 3: FLORAL BUTTERCREAM PIPING TECHN
 IQUES\nDay 4: INTRODUCTION TO GUMPASTE AND FONDANT\nDay 5: STACKING & DECO
 RATING A TWO TIERED CAKE\nDAY 1: FOUNDATIONS OF CAKE BAKING AND BUTTERCREA
 M MAKING\nMix\, colour and bake a vanilla cake\nMake swiss meringue butter
 cream in groups\nLearn how to colour buttercream\nLearn how to use a pipin
 g bag and practicing piping design techniques\nDAY 2: MAKING A RAINBOW STR
 IPED CAKE\nLearn how to cut and layer your colourful cake\nLearn how to us
 e essential cake tools to achieve smooth straight sides on your cake\nLear
 n how create rainbow coloured stripes on the sides of your cake\nDAY 3: FL
 ORAL BUTTERCREAM PIPING TECHNIQUES\nHow to use piping bags and tips to dec
 orate cupcakes with buttercream\nHow to pipe a rose\, 5 petal flower and m
 um\nHow to pipe leaves and foliage to complete your cupcakes\nDay 4: INTRO
 DUCTION TO GUMPASTE AND FONDANT\nWhere to buy and how to store fondant and
  gumpaste\nHow to colour and mix fondant and gumpaste\nHow to use essentia
 l cake tools to achieve smooth straight sides on your cake\nHow to cover y
 our cake in fondant and which tools to use\nHow to use fondant cutouts to 
 decorate and finish your cake\nHow to add proper supports to your gumpaste
  teddy bear before placing on your finished cake\nDay 5: STACKING & DECORA
 TING A TWO TIERED CAKE\nHow to use piping bags and colours to decorate you
 r cake\nHow to use essential cake tools to achieve smooth straight sides o
 n you cake\nHow to properly add supports and stack a two tiered cake\nYou 
 will go home with:\nA one tier 6’’ round tall rainbow cake that you wi
 ll have decorated yourself on Day 2\nbuttercream flower cupcakes from Day 
 3\nA  fondant cake with gumpaste topper that you will have created on Day 
 4\nA two tiered buttercream cake flower cake on Day 5\nChocolate cake reci
 pe\, vanilla cake recipe\, Swiss meringue and American buttercream recipe\
 , emailed to you at the time of your booking\n‘How to use piping tips’
  recipe emailed to you at the time of your booking\nPictures are for displ
 ay purposes only. Your teacher will talk you through design elements in an
 y picture shown\, but for efficient running of this class\, you will be gu
 ided by her in terms of design.\nAll ingredients and equipment\, including
  transport boxes\, for your cake course are provided\, you do not need to 
 bring anything with you. The teacher will ensure that you work at a pace s
 uitable for you.\nIf you would like\, you can bring a large bag to carry y
 our cake(s) home. We provide sturdy cardboard boxes\, but you may find it 
 easier to carry your cake(s) in a reusable tote bag especially if taking p
 ublic transit to class.\n$899 + HST
LOCATION:Le Dolci Culinary School
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/five-day-cake-baking-decorating-mastercl
 ass-toronto-4/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
