BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Lulaworld 2026: Gianluca Occhipinti Album Release Concert
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260512T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260512T220000
UID:blogto-233444@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/10/original_image33d1ae1e-f89e-4271-b9c2-11f2f7f7c4
 c7.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Joined by bassist Jordan Pelunksy and drummer Marito Marques\,
  Gianluca Occhipinti performs repertoire from his new jazz release Dissolu
 tion.\nSHOW DETAILS\nThe debut release\n7:00 PM - Doors open for dinner an
 d drinks. Reserve a table at lula.ca.\n8:00 PM - Concert Begins - 2 sets w
 ith intermission\n$20 EARLY BIRD\, $25 ADVANCE\, $35 AT THE DOOR\nTICKETS 
 ARE GENERAL ADMISSION AND DO NOT GUARANTEE SEATING.\nJoin us before the sh
 ow to enjoy Lula's tropical-inspired dinner and drinks menu. Dinner reserv
 ations available at lula.ca/reservations\nLulaworld Festival (May 11 to 17
 )\nJoin us at Lula Lounge to celebrate the 20th annual Lulaworld festival\
 , marking two decades of local and international jazz\, Latin\, Brazilian\
 , soul and folk from around the globe and around the corner.\nGianluca Occ
 hipinti\nGianluca Occhipinti is a Toronto-based pianist and composer whose
  work reflects a foundation in both classical and jazz traditions. Immerse
 d in music from an early age\, he has developed a distinctive voice shaped
  by a wide range of influences\, mentors\, and performance experiences.\nO
 ver the past seven years\, Gianluca has studied with JUNO Award-winning pi
 anist Jeremy Ledbetter\, whose mentorship has been central to his developm
 ent as a composer and improviser. He has also studied with Amanda Tosoff\,
  Manuel Valera\, and Hilario Durán\, further deepening his musical langua
 ge.\nIn recent years\, Gianluca has focused on developing and presenting h
 is original compositions across Toronto\, collaborating and performing wit
 h internationally recognized artists including Felix Pastorius\, Don Byron
 \, Alex Dean\, and Larnell Lewis.\nAlbum: Dissolution\n“ Dissolution is 
 about the breaking down of different aspects into one uniform artwork\,”
  Gianluca explains. “From learning Beatles tunes with my dad\, to playin
 g bass in the orchestra\, to studying Hermeto Pascoal with my teacher\, or
  making beats with my friends.”\nBlending genres and influences\, the al
 bum moves fluidly across musical languages: “There’s jazz in the way w
 e interact\, there’s R&B in the groove\, there’s gospel in the harmony
 \, and there’s classical in the way the album flows.”\nThe project fea
 tures an exceptional group of collaborators\, including drummers Larnell L
 ewis and Jinu Isac (featured on the recording)\, with Marito Marques appea
 ring on the release performance. Longtime collaborators Jacob Lee and Jami
 e Wells also contribute to the album’s creative direction\, alongside Jo
 rdan Pelunsky\, who helped workshop the material over the past year.\n“M
 y very first instrument was the drums\, and that certainly shows here\,”
  he notes. “These musicians have all elevated me and my music to the nex
 t level.”\nComprising 12 tracks plus a bonus track available on Bandcamp
  and CD\, Dissolution is conceived as a live experience. “I’ve crafted
  the album with the intention of it being a live show\,” Gianluca says. 
 “This is where the music will be at its best.”\nFollow Gianluca Occhip
 inti on Instagram and Facebook.
LOCATION:Lula Lounge
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/lulaworld-2026-gianluca-occhipinti-album
 -release-concert-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
