BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Lecture: The Edges of The Roman Empire
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260513T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260513T210000
UID:blogto-232274@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/17/original_image855bb006-0d6b-4eb0-8c4a-0a3675baf7
 4d.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Join us for The Edges of the Roman Empire\, a dynamic lecture 
 with Dr. Kate Cooper\, Mirkopoulos Associate Curator of Ancient Greece & R
 ome at the Royal Ontario Museum. Discover how the Romans expanded across c
 ontinents—occupying distant lands and diverse peoples\, building new cit
 ies\, and interacting with local cultures. From Britain to Syria to North 
 Africa\, explore what life was like for the communities living on the fron
 tiers of the Roman Empire.\nThis is a great event for history lovers\, edu
 cators\, and anyone curious about the complexities of empire and cultural 
 exchange.\nTickets include museum access during the event.
LOCATION:Bata Shoe Museum
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/lecture-the-edges-of-the-roman-empire-to
 ronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
