SUMMARY:Lulaworld 2026: AIZA & Mira Mela
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260513T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260513T220000
UID:blogto-233445@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/10/original_imagecc14e07f-a008-4398-8cae-885693060a
 ca.jpg
DESCRIPTION:A night of upbeat Afrobop\, R&B and Soul. Prepare to sing your
  heart out and melt your worries on the dancefloor!\nSHOW DETAILS\n7:00 PM
  - Doors open for dinner and drinks. Reserve a table at lula.ca.\n8:00 PM 
 - Concert Begins\n$20 EARLY BIRD\n$25 ADVANCE\, $35 AT THE DOOR (DOES NOT 
 GUARANTEE SEATING)\nEnjoy Lula's tropical-inspired dinner and drinks menu 
 before the show. Dinner reservations available at lula.ca/reservations\nLu
 laworld Festival (May 11 to 17)\nJoin us at Lula Lounge to celebrate the 2
 0th annual Lulaworld festival\, marking two decades of local and internati
 onal jazz\, Latin\, Brazilian\, soul and folk from around the globe and ar
 ound the corner.\nAIZA\nA high vibe and upbeat afropop experience\, sprink
 led with R&B and a little bit of French. Prepare to sing your hearts out a
 nd melt your worries on the dancefloor. �\nAiza is an Afrobop Queen on a
  mission to empower with her signature sound\, a catchy and playful fusion
  of bilingual afropop and R&B. In Fall 2023\, the Toronto-based songstress
  released her much-anticipated debut album Sovereignty\, which garnered ov
 er 2.5 million streams across digital platforms and remained on the !earsh
 ot national radio charts for 28 weeks\, peaking at #10 in the Top 50. The 
 project features Divinity Roxx (former musical director and bassist for Be
 yoncé) and its second single\, “Majimbo” landed in the CBC Music Top 
 20 charts for six weeks. While cooking up her next batch of bops\, Aiza wa
 s admitted into the Recording Academy's NEXT CLASS of 2025 (Los Angeles Ch
 apter)\, cementing her place as one of the rising leaders shaping the futu
 re of global music.\nFollow AIZA on Instagram and Facebook.\nListen on Spo
 tify AIZA
LOCATION:Lula Lounge
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/lulaworld-2026-aiza-mira-mela-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
