BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Juggle is Real: A Networking Event For The Sandwich Generation
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260513T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260513T210000
UID:blogto-233009@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/01/original_image0e76e354-9a27-4162-adf1-b60e27f916
 de.jpg
DESCRIPTION:You’re building your career\, supporting aging parents\, may
 be raising children of your own - and somehow trying to stay grounded thro
 ugh it all. The Juggle Is Real is a refreshing spring evening designed spe
 cifically for professionals navigating life in the “in-between” years.
 \n​Join us for an elevated cocktail and networking event that blends mea
 ningful conversation with a genuinely enjoyable night out. Connect with pe
 ers who understand the unique pressures of balancing career ambition\, fam
 ily responsibility\, and the evolving needs of aging parents.\n​The even
 ing will feature a dynamic panel of experts from the aging and care space 
 who will share practical guidance on preparing for what’s ahead\, naviga
 ting tough conversations\, managing stress\, and building sustainable supp
 ort systems - without sacrificing your own goals or well-being.\n​What t
 o expect:\n- A curated cocktail reception with intentional networking\n- A
  candid\, solutions-focused expert panel\n- ​Practical insights you can 
 apply immediately\n- A supportive\, professional community that “gets it
 ”\n- An energizing atmosphere - good vibes only\n​This is not a semina
 r. It’s a smart\, modern space to learn\, connect\, and feel less alone 
 in the juggle.\nThank you to Elderado for joining us as a community partne
 r for this event. Elderado is dedicated to making the process of finding t
 he right senior care easier so you can spend less time searching for infor
 mation and more time with your loved ones.
LOCATION:Society Clubhouse
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/the-juggle-is-real-a-networking-event-fo
 r-the-sandwich-generation-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
