 ns available at lula.ca/reservations\, A la carte menu available.\n(GENERA
 L ADMISSION TICKETS DO NOT GUARANTEE SEATING)\n$79 + 18% GRATUIDY DINNER P
 RIX FIX TICKETS AVAILABLE\nPrix fixe tickets include gratuity\, concert an
 d dance lesson.\nLulaworld Festival (May 11 to 17)\nJoin us at Lula Lounge
  to celebrate the 20th annual Lulaworld festival\, marking two decades of 
 local and international jazz\, Latin\, Brazilian\, soul and folk from arou
 nd the globe and around the corner.\nDayme Arocena\nGrammy-nominated and J
 uno Award-winning Afro-Cuban singer\, composer\, and choir director Daymé
  Arocena is a powerful voice in contemporary Latin music.\nCelebrated for 
 her genre-blending creativity and deep connection to her Cuban roots\, Aro
 cena's 2024 album\, Alkemi\, marked a bold reinvention of her sound\, blen
 ding neo-soul\, Afro-Caribbean rhythms\, and modern pop in collaboration w
 ith renowned producer Eduardo Cabra and featuring guest vocals by Vicente 
 García and Rafa Pabön. A track from that album\, “A Fuego Lento\,” r
 eceived a Latin Grammy nomination for Song of the Year.\nFollow Dayme Aroc
 ena on Instagram and Facebook.\nDayme Arocena on Spotify
