BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Lulaworld 2026: Late Night with Kumionik featuring ALIKA
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260515T230000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260516T030000
UID:blogto-233448@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/10/original_image39e2729c-8221-43f0-a68c-7d582ca546
 a1.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Experimental cumbia\, heavy bass\, and raw electronics featuri
 ng Buenos Aires-based artist ALIKA with XOLO\, ESCOBUTT and JUANITO.\nLula
 world Festival (May 11 to 17)\nJoin us at Lula Lounge to celebrate the 20t
 h annual Lulaworld festival\, marking two decades of local and internation
 al jazz\, Latin\, Brazilian\, soul and folk from around the globe and arou
 nd the corner.\nToronto's Weekly Global Afterparty!\nEvery Friday night at
  11 PM\, Lula elevates the party to the next level!\nFollowing our weekly 
 live Latin band\, Lula now features local and international bands and DJs 
 playing high-energy global beats to keep the dance floor moving late into 
 the night.\nLULAWORLD X KUMBIONIK\nThis is not a regular party. No recycle
 d sets. No safe sounds.\nKumbionik brings experimental cumbia\, heavy bass
 \, and raw electronics into one space — built for the dancefloor\, no fi
 ller. Every hit\, loop\, and frequency lands harder.\nFrom the Latin Ameri
 can underground to the city’s core\, this night is for those seeking int
 ensity\, dance\, and controlled chaos.\nA night where everything hits hard
 er.\nALIKA\nAlika is a key artist in Spanish-language reggae and dancehall
 . Born in Montevideo\, Uruguay\, and musically developed in Buenos Aires\,
  Argentina\, she has established herself as one of the most respected voic
 es in Latin America’s sound system culture.\nFrom the beginning\, she ha
 s worked independently\, building her own path based on self-management\, 
 artistic integrity\, and a message of social and spiritual awareness. Her 
 music blends reggae roots and dancehall with a distinctly Latin American i
 dentity.\nThroughout her career\, she has performed across the Americas an
 d Europe\, standing out for her live format rooted in sound system culture
 .\nAt Kumbionik\, she presents a different side: a special set alongside A
 ngel Zepeda\, where her sound crosses into experimental cumbia and electro
 nic textures. An evolution that connects roots with the future without los
 ing its essence.\nXOLO\nXolo is a cultural project born from the collabora
 tive vision of Aldo Camarena and Ashley McKay. Aldo\, originally from Mexi
 co\, and Ashley\, a Canadian chef\, joined forces to build Xolo as a space
  where urban Latin‑American cuisine meets curated musical selections\, o
 ffering experiences that blend flavour\, rhythm\, and community.\nAs a pop
 ‑up concept\, Xolo combined dishes influenced by Chicano and Latin Ameri
 can culture with thoughtful musical curation\, bringing a fresh\, authenti
 c vibe to Toronto’s cultural landscape. Their presence at local events a
 nd the way they blended food and sound helped establish Xolo as an innovat
 ive creative force in the city.\nOver time\, this momentum evolved into a 
 permanent restaurant called Antylia\, a space dedicated to exploring the f
 lavours of the Americas and strengthening the cultural ties of community. 
 The story of Xolo reflects boundless creativity\, shared identity\, and th
 e impact of Latin‑American culture in Toronto.\nESCOBUTT\nColombian-born
  and Toronto-based\, Escobutt is a DJ\, producer and promoter who dismantl
 es genres to rebuild the dance. Her arsenal moves through electronic cumbi
 a\, neo-guaracha\, dembow\, raptor house\, reggaetón and jungle\, always 
 from a queer and conceptual perspective.\nFounder of Lewdline\, a series a
 mplifying QTBIPOC+ artists\, and creator of the album ID-ASS (2024)\, a wo
 rk that breaks binaries and remixes Latin rhythms with glitch-hop\, hyperp
 op and downtempo.\nShe has played Boiler Room Toronto\, N10AS Montréal an
 d Shift Radio\, and collaborated with networks like Kumbia Net\, Club Feli
 nas and Santa Sede. For Kumbionik\, she brings cyber-sonidero fire: concep
 tual cumbia and queer groove opening new logics of the Latin ritual.\nJUAN
 ITO\nFrom Toronto\, Juani Juani Juani (Juanito) lights up the floor with s
 treet cumbia and tropical edits breathing barrio and fiesta. His Instagram
  is a living archive of cumbia vibes\, spontaneous reels and sessions for 
 dancing while cooking or showering.\nHe collaborated with Escobutt on the 
 track “Baddiewock”\, a badass fusion of sonidero cumbia and urban ener
 gy. As part of projects like Pequephone\, his style merges homemade sponta
 neity with club fire.\nFor Kumbionik\, Juanito brings a set loaded with st
 reet edits\, nocturnal beats and tropical vibes: more than music\, it’s 
 heritage in motion.\nArrive at 11 pm and enjoy some of the Luis Franco & D
 ianela Hernandez's performance before the late-night global party begins!\
 nBottle Service\nReservations for bottle service can be made by calling 41
 6 588 0307.\nPlease note that these tickets are general admission and do n
 ot guarantee seating. Buy early and get the early bird discount!
LOCATION:Lula Lounge
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/lulaworld-2026-late-night-with-kumionik-
 featuring-alika-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Lulaworld 2026: Luis Franco with special guest Dianela Hernandez
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260515T203000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260515T230000
UID:blogto-233447@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/10/original_image4ac03453-b896-4729-b8a9-7d08bdd32b
 f4.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Lulaworld Festival (May 11 to 17)\nJoin us at Lula Lounge to c
 elebrate the 20th annual Lulaworld festival\, marking two decades of local
  and international jazz\, Latin\, Brazilian\, soul and folk from around th
 e globe and around the corner.\nCanada’s premier Latin music and dance c
 lub invites you to experience an unforgettable night of salsa — dinner\,
  dancing\, and live music all under one roof!\nBook a table for dinner and
  dancing\, or arrive after 9 PM to head straight to the dance floor.\nEven
 ing Schedule\n� 7:00 PM – Doors open for dinner and drinks\n� 9:00 P
 M – Salsa lesson (no partner needed!)\n� 10:00 PM – Live salsa set\n
 � 11:00 PM – Keep the energy going with Lula's Global Late Night Party
 !\nLuis Franco\nVenezuelan-born singer and composer Luis Franco boasts a 3
 0-year musical career that has taken him to stages around the globe. Luis 
 now brings his Worldwide Salsa show to audiences across Canada to further 
 expand his musical journey and bring hard-hitting salsa to Toronto's dance
  floors.\nDianela Hernandez\nHaving performed extensively in Cuba and Turk
 ey’s top hotels\, Dianela is a newer contributor to Toronto’s ever-evo
 lving Latin music community\, singing everything from Cuban classics\, cha
  cha cha and merengue\, to pop\, soul and disco. For tonight’s performan
 ce\, Dianela will join Luis Franco’s ensemble on three of her favourite 
 pieces from Franco's high-energy repertoire.\nWhy Lula is unique:\nThe onl
 y venue of its kind in North America\, Lula Lounge features a rotating ros
 ter of more than a dozen full salsa orchestras every Friday and Saturday
 —year-round. Our stage welcomes the best local talent alongside special 
 guests from across Canada and the Americas\, offering a one-of-a-kind sals
 a experience in a warm\, colourful\, and inclusive space
LOCATION:Lula Lounge
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/lulaworld-2026-luis-franco-with-special-
 guest-dianela-hernandez-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
