BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bees: A Story of Survival
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260516T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260516T170000
UID:blogto-227972@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2025/12/09/original_imageb9c0b697-be9e-4241-9696-3dbc7859b1
 2f.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Bringing some buzz into your summer.\nJourney into the world o
 f bees in a stunning new immersive experience that brings together the bea
 uty of art with the power of science. Created by the National Museums Live
 rpool in partnership with award-winning artist and sculptor\, Wolfgang But
 tress\, the exhibition highlights 120-million years of bee adaptation and 
 survival\, telling the epic tale of these incredible creatures and their r
 elationship to us and the natural world.\nBased on science and full of ima
 gination\, the experiential exhibition presents a fusion of nature\, art\,
  music\, and architecture that transports visitors into the world of bees 
 - from the tiny\, fascinating anatomy of a single bee and the magical wond
 er of honey bee colonies to the important roles bees play in our lives and
  the everyday threats they face.\nThrough immersive environments\, art ins
 tallations\, soundscapes\, and more\, learn about the life of bees and the
  world they inhabit. See an ancient\, fossilized bee encased in amber\, en
 ter a stylized honeycomb\, take a moment to hear "like a honey bee"\, and 
 experience changing patterns of light generated from the sounds of over 30
 \,000 bees.\nSmall but mighty\, bees are a critical ingredient of a health
 y natural world but are under continued and increasing threat. Powerful in
  what they can provide\, and yet powerless to overcome the threats to thei
 r existence\, the exhibition takes a closer look at bees - including some 
 local specimens from the collections at ROM - to help guide a better under
 standing of what we can do to help prevent bee species from disappearing f
 orever.\nBees: A Story of Survival is an evocative\, engaging feast for th
 e senses guaranteed to take the sting out of getting better acquainted wit
 h our buzz-worthy friends.
LOCATION:Royal Ontario Museum
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/bees-a-story-of-survival-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:BMX Contest at Lake Wilcox Skatepark
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260516T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260516T180000
UID:blogto-232696@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/25/original_image6e583eeb-2932-4e9c-b667-95c3b97d13
 89.jpg
DESCRIPTION:A community BMX event is inviting the public to take part in a
 n open\, all ages summer kickoff at Lake Wilcox Skatepark in Richmond Hill
 .\nWard10’s Annual Summer Jam returns on May 16\, 2026\, starting at 12 
 p.m.\, with a strong emphasis on accessibility and participation. The even
 t is free to attend and open to everyone whether you are an experienced BM
 X rider\, just starting out\, or simply looking to watch and enjoy the atm
 osphere.\nUnlike traditional competitions\, the jam style format encourage
 s riders of all skill levels to drop in\, ride at their own pace\, and tak
 e part in activities throughout the day. Featured highlights include a Bes
 t Trick contest and a Highest Air challenge\, both designed to be inclusiv
 e and welcoming rather than highly structured or exclusive.\nSpectators ar
 e equally part of the experience\, with a casual\, festival like environme
 nt built around the skatepark. Giveaways will run throughout the event\, a
 longside a frame raffle offering cash or equivalent prizes. Free drinks wi
 ll also be available for attendees\, helping create a relaxed\, community 
 oriented setting.\nThe event is supported by a range of BMX and lifestyle 
 brands including MacNeil\, Merritt\, Northern Hydration\, OGC BMX\, Harves
 ter Bikes\, Fifteen Distribution\, and Rixin\, reflecting strong grassroot
 s support for the local BMX scene.\nWith no barriers to entry (free) and a
  welcoming atmosphere\, Ward10’s Summer Jam aims to bring together rider
 s\, families\, and curious onlookers alike for an afternoon that is as muc
 h about participation as it is about performance.
LOCATION:Lake Wilcox Skatepark
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/bmx-contest-at-lake-wilcox-skatepark-tor
 onto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
