 f8.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The biggest\, boldest\, most gloriously over-the-top music com
 petition on Earth is back\, and Toronto is watching it together.\nJoin us 
 for a free watch party on Saturday\, May 16\, with doors opening at 2 p.m.
  and the live broadcast starting at 3 p.m. We’ll have flags and scorecar
 ds for you to make meticulous notes and cheer on your old favorite or new 
 favorite countries.\nYou never know what to expect with the Eurovision Son
 g Contest\, but there is no experience required! We invite both longtime f
 ans and total newbies to watch the weird\, the wonderful\, and the brillia
 nce that is Eurovision.\nPegasus on Church will be serving up delicious dr
 inks\, so please support this fabulous venue! Outside food is permitted\, 
 but outside beverages are not.\nWhether you’ve been watching Eurovision 
 for decades or you just want to understand why 150+ million people lose th
 eir minds over it every year\, this is the place to be.\nEVENT DETAILS\nWh
 en:\n🗓 Saturday\, May 16\, 2026\n🕑 Doors open: 2 p.m.\n📺 Live wat
 ch party + broadcast begins around 3 p.m.\nWhere:\nPegasus on Church (upst
 airs)\, 489B Church Street\, Toronto\, ON\nNear Church & Wellesley\nAdmiss
 ion & Age:\n🍸 Free\n🚪 19+ event (venue policy)\nWHAT TO EXPECT\n🎶
  Live screening of the Eurovision Grand Final\n🌈 A room full of fans wh
 o get it\n📣 Cheering\, gasping\, clapping\, singing along (good-natured
  vibes only)\n✨ Maximum camp\, zero judgment\nFeel free to add your favo
 rite country’s colors\, accessories\, or mini flag to your look! (Can’
 t hurt to bring a little spark.)\nHOUSE RULES\n✨ Cheer for\, not against
 \n✨ Be kind\, inclusive\, and welcoming\n✨ Support the venue by buying
  drinks (outside food OK\, outside drinks not allowed)\nLove\, Love.\nPeac
 e\, Peace\nSee you on May 16
