BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:CHOCOLATE Kintsugi: Mindful Art You Can Eat
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260517T123000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260517T150000
UID:blogto-231804@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/05/original_imagedd02b419-df20-48c5-9678-a8e9378cc2
 f8.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Forget fragile tea sets - this is kintsugi you can eat. 🍫
 ✨\nPaint your own handcrafted chocolate tile\, then break it (yep\, on p
 urpose) before mending it with edible gold. It’s part mindfulness\, part
  art therapy\, and 100% delicious. You’ll create an edible piece of art 
 that celebrates imperfection - and tastes like resilience.\n✨ WHAT MAKES
  THIS UNIQUE ✨\nInspired by the Japanese art of Kintsugi\, this workshop
  blends creativity\, reflection\, and chocolate. No stuffy art studio vibe
 s here - just cozy tunes\, laid-back energy\, and golden symbolism you can
  snack on.\n⭐ WHO IT’S FOR ⭐\n• Anyone craving a mindful\, creativ
 e experience that still feels fun\n• Couples looking for a deeper connec
 tion (and dessert)\n• Friends or solos who want to slow down and create 
 something meaningful\n⭐ REASONS YOU’LL LOVE IT ⭐\n1️⃣ A great wa
 y to unwind after a crazy week\n2️⃣ No art skills needed\n3️⃣ It's
  essentially chocolate therapy\n💫 Celebrating something? Birthday\, ann
 iversary\, or just life? Tell the team and they’ll make it extra sweet.
LOCATION:QUEST XO
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/chocolate-kintsugi-mindful-art-you-can-e
 at-toronto-6/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
