BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:bol\, brown boy\, bol
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260520T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260521T170000
UID:blogto-230967@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/02/15/original_imagef0a4da97-3804-4543-84d0-ed64718d95
 92.jpg
DESCRIPTION:bol\, brown boy\, bol is a cheeky\, heartfelt solo show about 
 Nawaaz's journey of reclaiming his voice and cultural inheritance through 
 learning tabla\, a northern Indian percussion instrument.\nTwenty years of
  being a “coconut” has caught up to Nawaaz\, who’s crashed into a du
 al crisis of identity and faith. Divine intervention sends him a musical G
 uru\, who guides him on a journey towards self-acceptance and love. Direct
 ed by Tiffany Wu\, bol\, brown boy\, bol offers a rich musical landscape m
 erging Indian classical music with 90s Bollywood nostalgia\, grunge\, rap\
 , and hip hop. Weaving storytelling with the rhythms of tabla\, creator an
 d performer Nawaaz speaks up about the impact of Canadian racism on his id
 entity and shares his story of finding his way back to himself.
LOCATION:Native Earth's Aki Studio
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/bol-brown-boy-bol-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Live Fashion Illustration 101
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260520T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260520T203000
UID:blogto-232278@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/17/original_imageb67e1103-4de9-47d2-aff9-de8bba203c
 d3.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Learn the unique art of live fashion illustration with Toronto
 -based illustrator Nessa Lilly\, known for capturing the elegance and ener
 gy of fashion moments. Inspired by the Bata Shoe Museum’s new exhibition
  André Perugia: A Design Legend Unveiled\, this hands-on workshop will te
 ach you how to bring fashion to life through quick\, expressive sketches i
 n 5 minutes or less. Nessa will guide participants through the dynamic pro
 cess of live fashion illustration — a rare skill that blends speed\, int
 uition\, and artistry to capture style in motion to create original editor
 ial style portraits.\nIn this workshop you will:\n- Learn how professional
  illustrators capture movement\, texture\, and design in real time\, creat
 ing a complete drawing in less than 5 minutes\n- Practice gesture and prop
 ortion techniques inspired by Perugia’s sculptural shoe forms\n- Gain in
 sight into what it’s like to work as a live fashion illustrator at shows
 \, events\, and brand activations\n- No prior drawing experience is needed
  — just curiosity and creativity.\nThis is a unique opportunity to learn
  a skill rarely taught in traditional art programs\, while exploring the l
 egacy of one of fashion’s most innovative designers.
LOCATION:Bata Shoe Museum
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/live-fashion-illustration-101-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
