BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:WWYW - The Untold Collection
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260520T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260521T000000
UID:blogto-230087@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/01/30/original_image2f5858b1-730c-428e-a6aa-54db2921f1
 fe.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The Untold Collection is a fashion exhibition reimagined — a
  night where style becomes art\, presence becomes power\, and every guest 
 becomes part of the story. This year’s theme\, Art Gallery Couture\, inv
 ites attendees to arrive in their most daring\, expressive\, and editorial
  looks.\nFor generations\, society has tried to explain sexual violence th
 rough fabric\, hemlines\, and outfits.\nBut clothing has never been the ca
 use of assault — power\, entitlement\, and violence are.\nThe myth that 
 “what someone wore” provokes assault is one of the most damaging forms
  of victim-blaming. It shifts responsibility away from those who choose to
  harm and places it onto those who were harmed. Research\, lived experienc
 e\, and survivor testimony all reveal the same truth:\nAssault occurs in s
 chool uniforms\, sweatpants\, winter coats\, pyjamas\, work scrubs\, and e
 very outfit imaginable.\nClothing doesn’t create violence.\nClothing doe
 sn’t invite it.\nClothing doesn’t consent.\nThis exhibit challenges th
 e myth directly. By presenting everyday outfits worn during moments of tra
 uma\, we expose the truth: the clothes were never the story — the harm w
 as.
LOCATION:The El Mocambo
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/wwyw-the-untold-collection-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bealtaine Theatre Festival
