 gto.com/events/2026/04/10/original_image8ec61a30-9d2b-4bce-9817-c83e852d63
 38.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The Canada Ireland Foundation's annual Bealtaine Theatre Festi
 val brings the best of Irish theatre to Toronto. The Festival runs from Ma
 y 21 to June 7 at the Corleck — a brand new venue for arts\, cultural an
 d heritage programming on Toronto’s waterfront. Festival attendees will 
 be among the first to experience this state-of-the-art performance space\,
  officially opening in November 2026.\nBealtaine Lineup:\nCHICKEN\nMay 21-
 24\nThis award-winning production from Sunday’s Child Theatre had a sold
 -out run at the 2023 Edinburgh Fringe Festival and exemplifies the origina
 lity of Ireland’s independent theatre scene.\nBELLOW\nMay 27-30\nFrom Du
 blin’s boundary-breaking Brokentalkers comes BELLOW\, a new theatre perf
 ormance exploring the beauty and weight of keeping traditional Irish music
  alive\, featuring expert accordionist Danny O’Mahony.\nYOU'LL SEE...\nJ
 une 6&7\nAn extraordinary adaptation of the story of Ulysses for children 
 and adults alike. In Branar’s YOU’LL SEE...\, James Joyce’s epic sto
 ry is reinvented for ages 8 and up.
LOCATION:Corleck
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/bealtaine-theatre-festival-toronto-2/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
