 gto.com/events/2025/07/27/original_imageb0f995ac-20ee-4b32-8f0f-0a711ba51c
 94.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The Penderecki String Quartet began their journey in Poland\, 
 winning the prestigious Penderecki Prize at the 1986 National Chamber Musi
 c Competition in Łódź. Since 1991\, they have been Quartet-in-Residence
  at Wilfrid Laurier University\, shaping one of Canada’s leading string 
 programs. Renowned for their commitment to contemporary music\, the Pender
 ecki Quartet has commissioned and performed over 100 new works. This seaso
 n\, they present a world premiere collaboration with rapper Shad and compo
 ser Nicole Lizée\, featuring the suite Something Good Is Gonna Happen…I
  Don’t Know When… Closing the program\, Roman Borys—cellist of the G
 ryphon Trio and Artistic Director of Music TORONTO—joins the quartet to 
 perform Schubert’s sublime Quintet in C Major. Experience an inspiring e
 vening of innovative new music alongside timeless classical masterpieces.\
 nTickets: $60-$65\n416-366-7723
LOCATION:Jane Mallett Theatre\, St. Lawrence Centre for the Arts
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/music-toronto-penderecki-string-quartet-
 toronto/
