 e1.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Benevolence Opera Project & Redwood Theatre Present Don Giovan
 ni\nA One-Night-Only Opera Event Supporting the Redwood Women’s Shelter\
 nToronto\, ON — Benevolence Opera Project and Redwood Theatre are proud 
 to present a special\, one-night-only one-of-a-kind performance of Don Gio
 vanni\, featuring Canadian Baritone Alexander Hajek in the titular role of
  Mozart’s electrifying masterpiece of seduction\, power\, and consequenc
 e\, on Friday\, May 22 at 8:00 PM at the Redwood Theatre.\nThis unique per
 formance serves as both an exceptional artistic event and a meaningful fun
 draiser in support of the Redwood Women’s Shelter. Featuring some of Can
 ada’s finest operatic talent\, this intimate production invites audience
 s into a thrilling “chess match” of wit\, desire\, and morality—brou
 ght vividly to life in the vibrant Redwood Theatre space.\nA pre-performan
 ce talk will be given at 7:15 PM by Opera Canada’s Michael Jones\, offer
 ing insight into the opera’s enduring legacy and themes.\nCast & Creativ
 e Team:\nDon Giovanni — Alexander Hajek\nLeporello — Luke Noftall\nMas
 etto — James Coole-Stevenson\nCommendatore — Andrew Tees\nDonna Anna 
 — Susan Elizabeth Brown\nDon Ottavio — Cameron Mazzei\nDonna Elvira 
 — Mary Ferrari\nZerlina — Kathryn Rose Johnston\nMusical Director & Pi
 anist — Brahm Goldhamer\nNarrator & Producer — Ryan Hofman\nEvent Deta
 ils:\nDate: Friday\, May 22\nTime: 8:00 PM (Pre-talk at 7:15 PM given by O
 pera Canada editor\, Michael Jones)\nLocation: Redwood Theatre\, 1300 Gerr
 ard St E.\, Toronto
LOCATION:The Redwood Theatre
