BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Supernauts Black Sabbath Tribute Opens for Who Made Who Ac/Dc Trib
 ute May 22
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260522T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260522T235900
UID:blogto-233123@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/04/original_image28a279a2-7fbb-4707-b888-4f3b5881b0
 1c.jpg
DESCRIPTION:https://www.ticketweb.ca/event/who-made-who-acdc-rockpile-rock
 -bar-tickets/14744353?REFID=clientsitewp&embed=1775282380626\nImmediate Re
 lease\nSUPERNAUTS\nopening for WHO MADE WHO The Definitive Tribute to AC/D
 C\nMay 22nd\, The Rockpile\, 5555 Dundas Street Toronto\nhttps://www.ticke
 tweb.ca/event/who-made-who-acdc-rockpile-rock-bar-tickets/14744353?REFID=c
 lientsitewp&embed=1775282380626\nFrom the dark heart of Peterborough\, Ont
 ario\, SUPERNAUTS brings the thunder of\nBlack Sabbath to life. Channeling
  the power\, precision\, and raw energy of Ozzy-era Sabbath\, they deliver
  a live experience that’s as heavy as it is haunting. With crushing riff
 s\, soaring vocals\, and that unmistakable groove\, SUPERNAUTS takes audie
 nces on a journey through the classics — from War Pigs and Paranoid to C
 hildren of the Grave and Snowblind. Whether it’s the sweaty intimacy of 
 a local club or the roar of a packed festival\, they’re here to keep the
  spirit of Sabbath alive for a new generation\nhttps://supernauts.band/\nS
 UPERNAUTS - Member Bios:\nDevin McManus - Ozzy (vocals)\nDevin never set o
 ut to be a singer — he started on guitar and only picked up the mic beca
 use he could never find anyone else willing to do it. Somewhere along the 
 way\, he discovered he could hit the high notes\, and there was no turning
  back. A lifelong fan of Black Sabbath\, Devin’s obsession began in grad
 e 10\, spending countless nights after school singing and playing along to
  We Sold Our Soul for Rock ’n’ Roll. That passion eventually grew into
  a mission: to channel the raw power and eerie charisma of Ozzy himself. H
 aving gigged on and off since high school\, Devin has shared stages with C
 anadian rock legends like Pat Travers and I Mother Earth. With\nSUPERNAUTS
 \, he brings decades of experience\, reverence\, and a true fan’s energy
  to every performance.\nBen Foss - Tony Iommy (Guitar)\nAs the Earth coole
 d he stood alone with his low slung Les Paul… Ben Foss is a multi-instru
 mentalist from Peterborough\, Ontario. He has been playing professionally 
 for over 20 years. He has been a member of tribute acts such as The Grunge
  Project\, and 8 Track Mined.  Ben has played in the pit band for Evil Dea
 d: The musical\, and in the house band for Harmony for Healing. He also pl
 ays in cover bands such as Sexbomb\, and Vern's Comb\, and also plays with
  singer/songwriter Chad Driscoll.\nLiam Archer - Bill Ward (Drums)\nBorn a
 nd raised in Trent Hills Ontario\, Liam began drumming at a young age. Dra
 wing inspiration from classic 70’s and 80’s metal he honed his craft w
 ith 2 of his brothers in a ‘family’ metal band. Going on to study at H
 umber College\, Liam combines classic metal drumming with precision and fi
 nesse to create a truly driving force. When not pounding the skins he enjo
 ys cycling\, baseball and hanging out with family and friends.\nand\nDawso
 n McManus - Geezer Butler (bass)\nDawson is a multi-instrumentalist\, voca
 list\, and songwriter. He studied Jazz Bass Performance at Mohawk College\
 , before beginning to tour extensively throughout Canada and the US.suppor
 ting heavy hitter Canadian artist\; Maple Blues award winner\, and Juno no
 minee Emily Burgess\, and Canadian/American Rock staples The Weber Brother
 s. Playing legendary venues such as The Mezzanine in SF\, The Viper Room i
 n LA\, The Sony Pictures Event Space in LA\, and Blue Bomber's Stadium in 
 Winnipeg Alberta. Opening for such iconic acts as April Wine\, David Wilco
 x\, Pat Travers\, I Mother Earth\, Big Wreck\, Stone Temple Pilots and mor
 e! With the exception of the COVID lockdowns\, has never taken more than a
  month off of performing in the last 16 years. Dawson has also been tapped
  to write original pieces for award winning indie film soundtracks\, inclu
 ding "Hunting Darkness" and "Fish Bowl". Dawson is not relegated to off ca
 mera either\, he has also starred in independent films and TV shows\, such
  as "Behind My Eyes" and "Northwood".Having dedicated his entire life to t
 he arts\, Dawson has traveled from coast to coast\, to see and do incredib
 le things that don't normally come to kids raised in a low income rural En
 nismore Ontario. From highrise rooftops to docked yachts and even a privat
 e tour of Skywalker Ranch\, Dawson is grateful for the opportunities music
  has provided him\, but has never lost sight of the most important thing\,
  to be the best player he can be. Dawson discovered his love for heavy mus
 ic and desire for every day to be Halloween simultaneously at the age of 1
 2 with the darker side of 90s rock and grunge. He is currently the bassist
  for The Bowie Lives\, Sarah Jayne Riley\, and The Sling Sisters\, as well
  as a session player for hire. When he's not on stage\, or in the practice
  space\, Dawson can be found hosting his Podcast "646 With Dawson McManus"
  on Pet Rock Radio\, training Muay Thai and Brazilian Jiu-jitsu\, or enjoy
 ing his family man life.
LOCATION:Rockpile Nightclub
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/supernauts-black-sabbath-tribute-opens-f
 or-who-made-who-acdc-tribute-may-22-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
