BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:WORK IT GIRL Summit
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260523T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260523T160000
UID:blogto-233284@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/07/original_image947f9296-f65e-42e3-8b93-df5e3f5a39
 23.jpg
DESCRIPTION:✨ Get ready to shine\, rise\, and connect — the WORK IT Gi
 rl Summit: LIGHT UP! is coming\, and it's going to be unforgettable.\nThis
  is more than an event — it's a movement. The WORK IT GIRL Summit is a p
 owerful\, one-of-a-kind experience designed to uplift\, inspire\, and LIGH
 T UP the brilliance in every girl.\nThrough dynamic speakers\, performance
 s\, and hands-on interactive experiences\, attendees dive into leadership\
 , movement\, and self-expression. Every moment is thoughtfully curated to 
 help girls and their families step boldly into their most authentic\, conf
 ident\, and fully expressed selves.\nLeave the day feeling seen\, celebrat
 ed\, and unstoppable — armed with leadership tools\, bold strategies\, a
 nd the courage to lead with heart\, dream without limits\, and dance fearl
 essly into your future.\nGirls will experience:\n• Confidence and leader
 ship skills\n• Creative expression through music\, movement and other cu
 rated discovery stations\n• Meaningful connection with other girls and f
 amilies\nWhat the Day Looks Like:\nWelcome & Opening Energy Session – In
 troduction to the WORK IT Girl Mindset\nInspiring Speakers – Real storie
 s about confidence and leadership\nMovement & Expression Sessions – Danc
 e and creative activities\nLive Performances – Celebrating empowerment a
 nd the courage to LIGHT UP!\nConnection Activities – Building friendship
 s and community\, celebrating every girl's voice\nWho Should Attend:\n• 
 Girls ages 6–12 who want to grow their confidence\n• Girls who enjoy m
 usic\, dance\, creativity\, and self-expression\n• Parents who want thei
 r daughters to develop leadership skills and are interested in personal gr
 owth\n• Families seeking a positive and empowering community experience\
 nHosted at YWCA Toronto\, an organization dedicated to improving the lives
  of women\, girls and gender diverse people.\nSpots are limited to ensure 
 a meaningful and interactive experience for every girl.\nEach ticket inclu
 des a WORK IT Girl swag bag.\nAcross communities\, a new generation of gir
 ls is stepping forward with confidence\, creativity\, and leadership — a
 nd WORK IT Girl is helping light the way.
LOCATION:YWCA Toronto
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/work-it-girl-summit-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
