 e7.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Join us at the 14th annual Sashbear Walk on May 24 at Sir Casi
 mir Gzowski Park from 9 am to 1 pm. The Sashbear Walk has been an annual e
 vent since 2013\, bringing together families\, friends\, those with lived 
 experience\, mental health providers and supporters throughout the communi
 ty to create a sea of orange in support of those with emotion dysregulatio
 n.\nThis annual walk is the largest event of its kind in Canada for emotio
 n dysregulation and borderline personality disorder. People come together 
 to raise awareness\, reduce stigma\, and make waves for mental health—a 
 journey to provide hope of a life worth living\, for all.
