BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Fiddler on the Roof in Yiddish
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260525T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260525T140000
UID:blogto-230386@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/02/05/original_image44475e1c-ce78-463d-bb4f-82de0e1543
 8e.jpg
DESCRIPTION:One of the most electrifying theatrical events of the last dec
 ade is finally coming to Canada. The internationally celebrated revival of
  The National Yiddish Theatre Folksbiene production of Fiddler on the Roof
  in Yiddish with English subtitles arrives at Toronto’s historic Elgin T
 heatre from May 25 to June 7\, 2026. Presented by the Harold Green Jewish 
 Theatre Company (HGJTC)\, this landmark production is directed by the lege
 ndary Tony and Academy Award winner\, Joel Grey. The show runs for a limit
 ed engagement from May 25 to June 7\, 2026. Tickets range from $36 - $18
 0 (additional fees may apply) and are on sale now via Ticketmaster. Perfor
 med entirely in its original language with English and Russian subti
 tles\, this landmark production has been described as a “revelation”
  for returning one of Broadway’s most beloved musicals back to its cul
 tural roots in a powerfully authentic theatrical event.  This landmark p
 roduction brings one of Broadway’s most beloved musicals back to its cul
 tural roots in a powerfully authentic theatrical event. In an increasingly
  fragmented world\, this story stands as a powerful unifying force - c
 ultivating empathy\, deepening cultural understanding\, and giving voice t
 o the wisdom passed from parent to child amid constant change.  Followin
 g widespread acclaim in New York City\, Fiddler on the Roof in Yiddish mak
 es its Canadian debut this Spring.
LOCATION:The Elgin Theatre
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/fiddler-on-the-roof-in-yiddish-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
