BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Human Edge: A conversation on AI and the future of work
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260526T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260526T210000
UID:blogto-233062@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/04/02/original_image081615ae-c6ef-486d-a3cf-109a4a002b
 bc.jpg
DESCRIPTION:​Presented by Re-Work during Toronto Tech Week 2026\n​AI i
 s moving faster than most people are ready for.\n​The productivity gains
  are real. But so are the consequences of that productivity. Since the ind
 ustrial revolution\, we’ve used productivity as a measure of the value a
 nd worth of an individual\, it’s no wonder that the looming evolutionary
  threat of AI feels so scary for many modern workers. How do we respond to
  a future of work where productivity is achieved through agentic AI instea
 d of human effort.\n​As a career and work wellbeing organization\, we ha
 ve thoughts.\n​In this curated and honest conversation we’ll discuss w
 here work is heading and what that means for the people doing it. And the 
 ways we’ll need to shift our thinking around work and productivity.\n​
 Join us for a keynote and facilitated discussion exploring the intersectio
 n of AI\, automation\, and human well-being. We'll get into the big pictur
 e and bring it back to what leaders and individuals can do to navigate the
  AI revolution in work.\n​​​About Re-Work\n​Re-Work is a Community
  First\n​We're a professional (and personal) development community helpi
 ng people redefine work\, ambition\, and success on their own terms. We wa
 nt you to get to a healthier\, less stress-filled place with the thing we 
 spend most of our lives doing: working. Move beyond burnout toward work th
 at is meaningful and fulfilling as your fullest self. Through a proven pro
 cess and framework\, we help you craft a more sustainable and values-align
 ed relationship with work. Through workshops\, training\, storytelling\, c
 oaching and community spaces\, Re-Work invites you to explore a healthier\
 , more sustainable way of working and living.\nLet’s build a future of w
 ork that works for you.
LOCATION:It's Ok* Studios
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/the-human-edge-a-conversation-on-ai-and-
 the-future-of-work-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:An Evening With Eckhart Tolle
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260527T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260527T210000
UID:blogto-230886@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/02/14/original_imagea8e9ba06-6618-4e3c-a096-bdb16776be
 7f.jpg
DESCRIPTION:With his hallmark warmth\, humour and compassion\, this evenin
 g will connect you with the peace and serenity that arises from living in 
 the moment.\nEckhart’s profound\, yet simple teachings have helped count
 less people from around the globe awaken to a vibrantly alive inner peace 
 in their daily lives. The New York Times has called Eckhart Tolle “the m
 ost popular spiritual author in the United States\,” and the Watkins Rev
 iew named him as “the most spiritually inﬂuential person in the world
 ”.\nEckhart Tolle’s writings and life-changing public events have touc
 hed millions of lives\, garnering fans to the likes of Oprah\, the Dalai L
 ama and Deepak Chopra. He is the best-selling author of The Power of Now a
 nd A New Earth that are widely regarded as the most transformational books
  of our time.\nTickets available @ https://eventschaser.com/tickets/Eckhar
 t-Tolle-Meridian-Hall-Toronto-ON/7458198/
LOCATION:Meridian Hall
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/an-evening-with-eckhart-tolle-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bellow
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260527T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260527T212500
UID:blogto-231954@blogto.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://blogto-production2-baselayer-display.blo
 gto.com/events/2026/03/09/original_imagec593b0a1-9764-4b76-8b2f-422c585442
 c8.jpg
DESCRIPTION:A new theatre performance exploring the weight of keeping trad
 itional Irish music alive and the artist’s need to express their true se
 lf.\nDanny O’Mahony has dedicated his life to the mastery of his instrum
 ent as well as to the preservation and performance of Irish traditional mu
 sic. Now\, after 40 years of breathing life into centuries-old tunes to ho
 nour the memory of those who have come before him\, this walking repositor
 y is finally taking a breath\, a moment to stop and consider what this lif
 elong dedication has cost him.\n"The piece in a most untraditional way is 
 a hymn of praise to the accordion in Irish music tradition." — No More W
 orkhorse\nThis play is part of the Canada Ireland Foundation’s Bealtaine
  Theatre Festival\, which brings the best of Irish Theatre to Toronto. Lea
 rn more: https://www.canadairelandfoundation.com/explore/bealtaine-theatre
 -festival-2026/\nOn Stage May 27-30\, 2026\nSingle tickets starting at jus
 t $55 (incl. tax & fees)\nBellow\nby Brokentalkers\nWritten by Feidlim Can
 non\, Gary Keegan & Danny O’Mahony\nFeaturing Danny O’Mahony\, Gary Ke
 egan & Emily Kilkenny Roddy
LOCATION:Corleck
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/bellow-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bruno Mars - The Romantic Tour 2026
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260527T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260527T220000
