DESCRIPTION:The Change Leadership Conference 2026 returns to Toronto for i
 ts 10th anniversary\, bringing together leaders\, change practitioners\, a
 nd professionals responsible for driving transformation within their organ
 izations.\nThis year’s theme\, “The Art and Science of Leading Change:
  From Theory to Practice\,” explores how leaders can bridge proven frame
 works with real-world application in today’s fast-changing environment s
 haped by AI\, digital transformation\, and workforce evolution.\nAttendees
  will gain practical insights\, hear real-world case studies\, and partici
 pate in interactive discussions focused on leading change with confidence 
 and credibility.\nConference highlights include:\n•	Expert-led sessions 
 and panel discussions\n•	Facilitated roundtable conversations\n•	Pract
 ical workshops and applied learning\n•	Networking opportunities with lea
 ders across industries\n•	The Change Leader Awards presentation\nDesigne
 d for leaders in business\, technology\, healthcare\, government\, and pro
 fessional services\, this conference offers actionable strategies and mean
 ingful connections for those navigating complex change.
LOCATION:Westin Harbour Castle
