 29.jpg
DESCRIPTION:New voices shine in this bold mixed programme as Jera Wolfe\, 
 a Métis Canadian choreographer\, joins Helen Pickett to present works cre
 ated for The National Ballet of Canada. Wolfe unveils a major world premie
 re after the success of his piece Soul in 2020\, while Pickett brings back
  her riveting Emma Bovary following its debut in 2023 with additional scen
 es. Together\, these pieces offer fresh and powerful storytelling\, sharin
 g the unique artistry and perspectives of two compelling creators of today
 .\nTickets available @ https://eventschaser.com/?s=New+Work+by+Jera+Wolfe+
 and+Emma+Bovary
