 ali (pronounced: Lay-Vin Kah-Li) is a Dutch-born\, L.A.-based singer\, son
 gwriter\, producer\, and multi-instrumentalist whose work fuses classic so
 ul musicianship with forward- thinking experimentation. He first broke thr
 ough with his Low Tide (2019) and HIGHTIDE (2020) mixtapes\, earning accla
 im for reintroducing emotional depth and live instrumentation to modern so
 ul.\nA sought-after collaborator\, Leven has written and produced for arti
 sts including Beyoncé\, Disclosure\, Teddy Swims\, and Playboi Carti\, re
 ceiving multiple GRAMMY® nominations for his work on Renaissance and COWB
 OY CARTER. In March\, Leven is set to release his highly anticipated new a
 lbum LK99\, following LK99: The Prelude and standout tracks like “Are U 
 Still\,” a project that expands his genre-fluid vision across funk\, R&B
 \, jazz\, and psychedelic soul while firmly positioning him as one of the 
 most innovative voices in contemporary music.
