DESCRIPTION:Baking Camp for kids at Le Dolci Culinary Classroom\nDo your k
 ids need a creative baking outlet? Sign up your children to bake and decor
 ate a variety of delicious treats while having fun!\nDetails:\nClass time:
   9:00 am - 4:00pm\nEarly drop off starting at 8:00 am available\nAges: id
 eal for kids 6-11 years old\nParents to pack peanut-free lunches and snack
 s\nLocation: Camp will take place at our 12 Sousa Mendes St. Culinary Clas
 sroom location in the Junction.\n📆 2026 Dates:\nFebruary 13 - Lambeth L
 ove Cake or Jellycat Cakes!\nJune 5 - Ice Cream Cone Cake\nJune 26 - Schoo
 ls Out Cake\nKids will stack\, mask and ice a delicious buttercream cake. 
 🧡 ⁠\nYour kids will work with fondant\, buttercream\, piping bags and
  their creativity.\nThey bring home an AMAZING CAKE and you will be a prou
 d parent. ⁠\nYOU WILL WIN THE PARENT FLEX AWARD!⁠\nYou're welcome. ⁠
 \nThere will be meditation at the start of each day for all campers and th
 ere will be music & outdoor activities.\nMore Than Just Baking – Life Sk
 ills Learned in the Kitchen!\nAt Le Dolci’s PA Day Baking Camp\, kids do
  more than just mix\, bake\, and decorate—they gain valuable life skills
  that will stay with them forever! Our hands-on baking sessions help child
 ren develop essential skills in a fun and creative environment.\n🧑🍳 
 Confidence & Independence – From measuring ingredients to decorating the
 ir cakes\, kids take ownership of their creations\, boosting their confide
 nce and sense of accomplishment. There’s nothing like seeing their hard 
 work turn into a beautifully decorated cake they can proudly take home!\n
 🔢 Math & Science in Action – Baking is a delicious way to reinforce m
 ath and science skills! Kids practice measuring\, counting\, and fractions
  while learning about chemical reactions that make cakes rise and buttercr
 eam smooth.\n🎨 Creativity & Artistic Expression – Each child gets to 
 design and decorate their cake with buttercream\, fondant\, and piping tec
 hniques\, allowing their imagination to shine. Whether they create a paste
 l dream or a bold and colorful masterpiece\, the sky’s the limit!\n🗣 
 Teamwork & Communication – Baking is a social activity! Our campers work
  together\, share tools\, and learn the importance of patience\, listening
 \, and following instructions\, all while making new friends in the proces
 s.\n🍰 Resilience & Problem-Solving – Not every cake turns out perfect
 ly the first time! Kids learn how to adapt\, troubleshoot\, and turn mista
 kes into delicious successes\, an important life lesson in resilience and 
 perseverance.\n🌿 Mindfulness & Fun – We start each camp day with medi
 tation\, helping kids feel relaxed and focused before diving into baking. 
 Plus\, with outdoor activities (weather permitting)\, they’ll get a bala
 nce of hands-on learning and active play.\nBy the end of the day\, your ch
 ild will have gained confidence\, creativity\, and problem-solving skills
 —all while having an absolute blast. And of course\, they’ll bring hom
 e an incredible cake to show off their hard work!\nSign up now—because l
 earning is sweeter when it’s hands-on and covered in buttercream! 🍰
 ✨\nWe can't wait to host your kids!\n$139 + HST
