 gto.com/events/2026/03/09/original_image3fa3d857-6ff0-4c4c-8e84-9eea39291f
 76.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Ulysses for children? Yes\, Ulysses for children.\nJames Joyce
 ’s epic story of one day in one city is brought to life in this inventiv
 e new show\, bringing Ireland’s most notorious book to audiences aged 8 
 and upwards\, and to all those who haven’t got around to reading it yet.
 \nCombining live performance\, intricate paper design\, an original score 
 and Joyce’s odyssey\, this is theatre that will excite both young and ol
 d.\n“Ulysses for children: has the world gone mad?... Branar has gone an
 d done it.” ★★★★ — The Irish Times\nThis play is part of the C
 anada Ireland Foundation’s Bealtaine Theatre Festival\, which brings the
  best of Irish Theatre to Toronto. Learn more: https://www.canadairelandfo
 undation.com/explore/bealtaine-theatre-festival-2026/\nOn Stage May 27-30\
 , 2026\nSingle tickets starting at just $30 (incl. tax & fees)\nYou'll See
 \nby Branar\nAdapted by Marc Mac Lochlainn and Helen Gregg\nDirected by Ma
 rc Mac Lochlainn\nFeaturing Helen Gregg
LOCATION:Corleck
URL:https://www.blogto.com/events/youll-see-toronto/
X-SOURCE:blogTO
END:VEVENT
